WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:03.936 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.936 --> 00:00:07.380 align:middle line:90%


00:00:07.380 --> 00:00:09.350 align:middle line:84%
>> Hi, it's James here
from Food Matters.

00:00:09.350 --> 00:00:12.170 align:middle line:10%
And today I'm here
with Artie Wu.

00:00:12.170 --> 00:00:14.072 align:middle line:10%
Artie is an avid meditator.

00:00:14.072 --> 00:00:15.530 align:middle line:84%
He's been doing it
for a long time,

00:00:15.530 --> 00:00:19.010 align:middle line:84%
and it took him into the
field of emotional healing.

00:00:19.010 --> 00:00:20.690 align:middle line:84%
He's the founder
of Preside Life,

00:00:20.690 --> 00:00:23.210 align:middle line:84%
which helps people deal with
emotional trauma and helps.

00:00:23.210 --> 00:00:26.150 align:middle line:84%
Them transform it into
ultimately finding

00:00:26.150 --> 00:00:27.770 align:middle line:84%
their true bliss
and today, we're

00:00:27.770 --> 00:00:30.770 align:middle line:84%
going to be talking about
just that and much, much more.

00:00:30.770 --> 00:00:31.610 align:middle line:90%
Hello, Artie.

00:00:31.610 --> 00:00:32.930 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi, James.

00:00:32.930 --> 00:00:35.840 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm excited to chat today,
and particularly interested

00:00:35.840 --> 00:00:40.370 align:middle line:84%
in how you came upon sort of
this idea that meditation can

00:00:40.370 --> 00:00:42.710 align:middle line:84%
be a powerful tool
for transformation.

00:00:42.710 --> 00:00:45.510 align:middle line:90%
How did this start for you?

00:00:45.510 --> 00:00:52.760 align:middle line:84%
>> So for me, I grew up in an
environment where meditation,

00:00:52.760 --> 00:00:56.390 align:middle line:84%
healing type things
were kind of the norm.

00:00:56.390 --> 00:01:00.080 align:middle line:84%
I grew up in New
York, and my mom

00:01:00.080 --> 00:01:02.780 align:middle line:84%
had this constant what
I called a carnival

00:01:02.780 --> 00:01:08.000 align:middle line:84%
parade of Taoist masters,
Shaolin monks, Tibetan priests

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:09.500 align:middle line:90%
coming through.

00:01:09.500 --> 00:01:14.870 align:middle line:84%
And as a child, they
would be doing the rounds

00:01:14.870 --> 00:01:17.330 align:middle line:84%
around the world to raise money
for their temples at home.

00:01:17.330 --> 00:01:20.990 align:middle line:84%
And they would show up in
our living room with my mom.

00:01:20.990 --> 00:01:26.000 align:middle line:84%
And in the course of
peddling their wares--

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:27.860 align:middle line:90%
and I say that with love--

00:01:27.860 --> 00:01:31.890 align:middle line:84%
they would say, Mrs. Wu, it's
perfectly safe, these practices

00:01:31.890 --> 00:01:32.690 align:middle line:90%
I teach.

00:01:32.690 --> 00:01:33.950 align:middle line:90%
Don't listen to my rivals.

00:01:33.950 --> 00:01:35.242 align:middle line:90%
They're all scoundrels.

00:01:35.242 --> 00:01:37.700 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, you boy, how old
are you, about eight or nine?

00:01:37.700 --> 00:01:38.330 align:middle line:90%
Come here.

00:01:38.330 --> 00:01:39.497 align:middle line:90%
Even a child could learn it.

00:01:39.497 --> 00:01:41.380 align:middle line:90%
Allow me to demonstrate.

00:01:41.380 --> 00:01:45.530 align:middle line:84%
I would be exposed
to all this stuff.

00:01:45.530 --> 00:01:48.170 align:middle line:84%
So growing up, it
seemed very normal

00:01:48.170 --> 00:01:50.720 align:middle line:84%
that people would
meditate, that people would

00:01:50.720 --> 00:01:52.730 align:middle line:90%
do these kinds of practices.

00:01:52.730 --> 00:01:54.205 align:middle line:84%
It just seemed like
a normal thing,

00:01:54.205 --> 00:01:55.580 align:middle line:84%
just like when
you grow up eating

00:01:55.580 --> 00:01:59.060 align:middle line:84%
a certain kind of
traditional food

00:01:59.060 --> 00:02:01.970 align:middle line:84%
that you don't realize
not everyone eats.

00:02:01.970 --> 00:02:05.300 align:middle line:90%


00:02:05.300 --> 00:02:08.690 align:middle line:84%
And so it wasn't
till I was in my 20s

00:02:08.690 --> 00:02:15.050 align:middle line:84%
when I realized that not only
does not everyone meditate

00:02:15.050 --> 00:02:17.510 align:middle line:84%
and have these common
practices, it's

00:02:17.510 --> 00:02:23.630 align:middle line:84%
actually the fact that most
people don't do these things.

00:02:23.630 --> 00:02:26.887 align:middle line:90%
And it was a shock to me.

00:02:26.887 --> 00:02:28.970 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't like, oh my gosh,
the world's messed up.

00:02:28.970 --> 00:02:33.260 align:middle line:84%
I was like, oh, the people
who brush their teeth

00:02:33.260 --> 00:02:36.020 align:middle line:84%
in this manner are
in the minority.

00:02:36.020 --> 00:02:38.990 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, that
explains a lot.

00:02:38.990 --> 00:02:41.600 align:middle line:90%


00:02:41.600 --> 00:02:46.510 align:middle line:84%
And so I just tucked that
away, went about my business,

00:02:46.510 --> 00:02:48.860 align:middle line:84%
you know, had a
career in high tech.

00:02:48.860 --> 00:02:53.630 align:middle line:84%
And after that phase
kind of stopped for me,

00:02:53.630 --> 00:02:55.620 align:middle line:84%
I was looking for
the next thing to do.

00:02:55.620 --> 00:03:00.290 align:middle line:84%
And the thing that keep kept
coming up for me was this idea

00:03:00.290 --> 00:03:04.820 align:middle line:84%
of somehow teaching not
just meditation in general,

00:03:04.820 --> 00:03:10.520 align:middle line:84%
but the practices that I've
come to rely on in myself

00:03:10.520 --> 00:03:15.320 align:middle line:84%
as a corporate executive,
high-tech founder,

00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:17.660 align:middle line:84%
family person in
the modern world--

00:03:17.660 --> 00:03:21.060 align:middle line:84%
people with just not a lot
of time and a lot of stress.

00:03:21.060 --> 00:03:23.870 align:middle line:84%
And what I realized is there
is a subset of practices

00:03:23.870 --> 00:03:27.540 align:middle line:84%
that I just have come to
lean on in my own life.

00:03:27.540 --> 00:03:31.760 align:middle line:84%
And those are the ones
that I started teaching.

00:03:31.760 --> 00:03:36.030 align:middle line:84%
And it's just been,
for me, this peak

00:03:36.030 --> 00:03:39.410 align:middle line:84%
into my bliss,
this emerging peak.

00:03:39.410 --> 00:03:42.350 align:middle line:84%
Because at the time,
I was just like--

00:03:42.350 --> 00:03:44.850 align:middle line:84%
after I sold my last
company in 2011, I was like,

00:03:44.850 --> 00:03:48.410 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to take another
year off and figure out

00:03:48.410 --> 00:03:52.100 align:middle line:90%
what else I might want to do.

00:03:52.100 --> 00:03:54.530 align:middle line:84%
And this meditation
thing kept coming up,

00:03:54.530 --> 00:03:56.660 align:middle line:84%
to the point where
I finally started

00:03:56.660 --> 00:03:58.010 align:middle line:90%
putting some things online.

00:03:58.010 --> 00:04:00.700 align:middle line:90%


00:04:00.700 --> 00:04:02.840 align:middle line:90%
And then that grew.

00:04:02.840 --> 00:04:09.110 align:middle line:84%
And then I got this strand
of feedback from people--

00:04:09.110 --> 00:04:12.610 align:middle line:84%
first in the hundreds,
then in the thousands--

00:04:12.610 --> 00:04:16.790 align:middle line:84%
were what they would
say is basically,

00:04:16.790 --> 00:04:18.980 align:middle line:84%
already these
techniques have helped

00:04:18.980 --> 00:04:22.250 align:middle line:84%
me calm the quiet
chatter and voice inside.

00:04:22.250 --> 00:04:23.660 align:middle line:90%
So that's great.

00:04:23.660 --> 00:04:25.940 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, great.

00:04:25.940 --> 00:04:27.290 align:middle line:90%
You're happy, I'm happy.

00:04:27.290 --> 00:04:29.000 align:middle line:90%
Let's just keep rolling.

00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:33.530 align:middle line:84%
And to a person they would
say, well, hang on a minute.

00:04:33.530 --> 00:04:34.740 align:middle line:90%
I actually have a question.

00:04:34.740 --> 00:04:37.280 align:middle line:84%
And my question
is, now that I've

00:04:37.280 --> 00:04:39.590 align:middle line:84%
quieted this chattering
voice intermittently

00:04:39.590 --> 00:04:41.840 align:middle line:84%
with meditation-- because
it always comes back anyway.

00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:44.930 align:middle line:90%
It's a part of you, right?

00:04:44.930 --> 00:04:46.810 align:middle line:84%
I realized I actually
have a second problem.

00:04:46.810 --> 00:04:48.950 align:middle line:90%
I was like, OK, what's that?

00:04:48.950 --> 00:04:50.570 align:middle line:84%
And they would say,
my problem is not

00:04:50.570 --> 00:04:53.866 align:middle line:84%
that my inner voice is
chattering and nervous,

00:04:53.866 --> 00:04:56.960 align:middle line:84%
because I can quiet
that now when I need to.

00:04:56.960 --> 00:05:02.000 align:middle line:84%
My problem is that the tone and
content of what it says to me

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:06.790 align:middle line:90%
is basically abusive.

00:05:06.790 --> 00:05:09.640 align:middle line:90%
And it's in my head.

00:05:09.640 --> 00:05:11.110 align:middle line:84%
With a couple of
shots of whiskey,

00:05:11.110 --> 00:05:12.777 align:middle line:84%
I can kind of hit it
with a two by four.

00:05:12.777 --> 00:05:17.980 align:middle line:84%
But it is a part of me, and I am
kind of not reconciled with it,

00:05:17.980 --> 00:05:19.450 align:middle line:84%
or it is not
reconciled with me--

00:05:19.450 --> 00:05:21.700 align:middle line:84%
however you want
to think about it.

00:05:21.700 --> 00:05:24.100 align:middle line:84%
And this, to me,
is the quintessence

00:05:24.100 --> 00:05:28.480 align:middle line:90%
of not having inner peace.

00:05:28.480 --> 00:05:30.010 align:middle line:90%
You have inner conflict.

00:05:30.010 --> 00:05:31.580 align:middle line:84%
It's not like, oh my gosh,
you have inner conflict.

00:05:31.580 --> 00:05:31.990 align:middle line:90%
No, no, no.

00:05:31.990 --> 00:05:33.760 align:middle line:84%
There are voices and
forces within you,

00:05:33.760 --> 00:05:37.850 align:middle line:84%
and they love you and they
do not agree with each other.

00:05:37.850 --> 00:05:41.500 align:middle line:84%
So it's like a tug of war
constantly back and forth.

00:05:41.500 --> 00:05:48.795 align:middle line:84%
So like any good tech business
person, I ignored the feedback.

00:05:48.795 --> 00:05:50.670 align:middle line:84%
I was like, well, just
keep trying, you know?

00:05:50.670 --> 00:05:52.900 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what to do.

00:05:52.900 --> 00:05:56.800 align:middle line:84%
Until it became this
torrent, this pattern

00:05:56.800 --> 00:05:58.110 align:middle line:90%
across thousands of people.

00:05:58.110 --> 00:06:01.370 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, I
think this is a thing.

00:06:01.370 --> 00:06:06.670 align:middle line:84%
And so I started really
diving into this,

00:06:06.670 --> 00:06:08.710 align:middle line:84%
reading anything I
could get my hands on--

00:06:08.710 --> 00:06:11.740 align:middle line:84%
the whole range of
scientific all the way

00:06:11.740 --> 00:06:17.922 align:middle line:84%
to the really kind
of more alternative.

00:06:17.922 --> 00:06:19.630 align:middle line:84%
I would just intake
everything, because I

00:06:19.630 --> 00:06:22.820 align:middle line:90%
was chewing on this problem.

00:06:22.820 --> 00:06:33.520 align:middle line:84%
And what basically happened
was that I got to this point

00:06:33.520 --> 00:06:36.620 align:middle line:84%
where, I think in
hindsight, it had just

00:06:36.620 --> 00:06:40.180 align:middle line:84%
stated enough within
me that at one point,

00:06:40.180 --> 00:06:45.730 align:middle line:84%
it just came gushing out of
me basically fully formed.

00:06:45.730 --> 00:06:51.070 align:middle line:90%


00:06:51.070 --> 00:06:56.040 align:middle line:84%
My family and I were on the
island of Hawaii in 2014

00:06:56.040 --> 00:07:00.340 align:middle line:84%
in Hilo, literally
visiting the volcano there,

00:07:00.340 --> 00:07:02.780 align:middle line:84%
which itself is this symbol
of a well of healing.

00:07:02.780 --> 00:07:05.440 align:middle line:84%
I didn't realize that at the
time, but I was on a volcano

00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:06.610 align:middle line:90%
while all of this happened.

00:07:06.610 --> 00:07:09.250 align:middle line:90%
It just came gushing out of me.

00:07:09.250 --> 00:07:12.200 align:middle line:84%
And I was just typing to save
my life, just to get it down

00:07:12.200 --> 00:07:13.000 align:middle line:90%
on paper.

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:18.280 align:middle line:90%


00:07:18.280 --> 00:07:21.730 align:middle line:84%
And as I was reading
what I was writing,

00:07:21.730 --> 00:07:26.600 align:middle line:84%
I was fascinated
but also mortified.

00:07:26.600 --> 00:07:30.400 align:middle line:84%
Because I was like,
this is not meditation.

00:07:30.400 --> 00:07:31.870 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what this.

00:07:31.870 --> 00:07:33.000 align:middle line:90%
Is this emotional healing?

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:35.920 align:middle line:84%
Is this talking about inner
wounds, why your voice is

00:07:35.920 --> 00:07:38.600 align:middle line:90%
negative, what to do about it?

00:07:38.600 --> 00:07:45.460 align:middle line:84%
And I basically just
barfed it all out,

00:07:45.460 --> 00:07:47.740 align:middle line:84%
and then closed it and
put it in my desk drawer

00:07:47.740 --> 00:07:49.480 align:middle line:84%
and left it alone
for six months.

00:07:49.480 --> 00:07:51.730 align:middle line:90%
I was like, I can't do that.

00:07:51.730 --> 00:07:56.800 align:middle line:84%
I mean, as a former tech person,
being a meditation teacher

00:07:56.800 --> 00:08:01.330 align:middle line:84%
is pretty much already the
last word in poor taste, right?

00:08:01.330 --> 00:08:04.120 align:middle line:84%
So I was like, I can't take
this next step forward.

00:08:04.120 --> 00:08:07.820 align:middle line:84%
I just-- you know, I have
this muse that I refer to.

00:08:07.820 --> 00:08:09.190 align:middle line:90%
And I was just like, I'm sorry.

00:08:09.190 --> 00:08:09.990 align:middle line:90%
I can't.

00:08:09.990 --> 00:08:12.220 align:middle line:90%
This is too much.

00:08:12.220 --> 00:08:14.770 align:middle line:84%
So I left it in the
drawer for six months.

00:08:14.770 --> 00:08:21.130 align:middle line:84%
And in December of
2014, I got an email

00:08:21.130 --> 00:08:23.770 align:middle line:84%
from one of my
student's advisees

00:08:23.770 --> 00:08:27.190 align:middle line:84%
who was taking one of
my meditation courses.

00:08:27.190 --> 00:08:29.060 align:middle line:84%
And in these courses,
you can email me

00:08:29.060 --> 00:08:31.750 align:middle line:84%
and I'll kind of give you
pointers and adjustments.

00:08:31.750 --> 00:08:35.539 align:middle line:90%
And so this woman emailed.

00:08:35.539 --> 00:08:38.272 align:middle line:84%
I was giving her
help with meditation.

00:08:38.272 --> 00:08:39.730 align:middle line:84%
And as these things
go, she started

00:08:39.730 --> 00:08:42.810 align:middle line:84%
getting into her background and
her life story and everything.

00:08:42.810 --> 00:08:46.870 align:middle line:90%


00:08:46.870 --> 00:08:51.070 align:middle line:84%
I'll spare you all the detail,
but basically, the thumbnail

00:08:51.070 --> 00:08:55.000 align:middle line:84%
of her life story is
that from age four to 18

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:58.450 align:middle line:84%
had been sexually
abused and assaulted

00:08:58.450 --> 00:09:04.870 align:middle line:84%
by basically every adult male in
her family and extended family.

00:09:04.870 --> 00:09:07.750 align:middle line:90%
Lifelong alcoholic, drug user.

00:09:07.750 --> 00:09:11.350 align:middle line:90%
Had recently graduated to meth.

00:09:11.350 --> 00:09:15.220 align:middle line:90%
Single mom, six-year-old son.

00:09:15.220 --> 00:09:22.060 align:middle line:84%
And just this very
much salt of the earth,

00:09:22.060 --> 00:09:30.460 align:middle line:84%
good-hearted, good, just
solid person at the core

00:09:30.460 --> 00:09:35.050 align:middle line:84%
but with an internal voice that
basically would rip into her

00:09:35.050 --> 00:09:38.710 align:middle line:90%
like 150 times a day.

00:09:38.710 --> 00:09:41.320 align:middle line:84%
And she said, you know,
I've been to AA three times.

00:09:41.320 --> 00:09:44.920 align:middle line:90%
I've been to rehab three times.

00:09:44.920 --> 00:09:47.320 align:middle line:84%
This warehouse that I work
in, I have great benefits

00:09:47.320 --> 00:09:50.320 align:middle line:84%
and everything so I
can go to therapy.

00:09:50.320 --> 00:09:55.090 align:middle line:84%
I'm just trying to
stay alive for my son.

00:09:55.090 --> 00:10:00.190 align:middle line:84%
And so nothing else worked, and
I came across your meditation.

00:10:00.190 --> 00:10:04.320 align:middle line:84%
And I'm trying it, and it's
sort of started to work.

00:10:04.320 --> 00:10:08.970 align:middle line:84%
And at that point I
was just like, OK.

00:10:08.970 --> 00:10:10.320 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:10:10.320 --> 00:10:14.715 align:middle line:90%
Just give me a week.

00:10:14.715 --> 00:10:15.840 align:middle line:90%
And she's like, no, no, no.

00:10:15.840 --> 00:10:18.150 align:middle line:84%
I'm fine doing-- I
was like, meditation

00:10:18.150 --> 00:10:20.220 align:middle line:90%
is not what you need.

00:10:20.220 --> 00:10:21.060 align:middle line:90%
Just give me a week.

00:10:21.060 --> 00:10:22.320 align:middle line:90%
I'll come up with something.

00:10:22.320 --> 00:10:24.445 align:middle line:84%
And she's like, well, I'm
not asking for a handout.

00:10:24.445 --> 00:10:29.400 align:middle line:90%
I was like, just give me a week.

00:10:29.400 --> 00:10:31.140 align:middle line:90%
And she was like, OK.

00:10:31.140 --> 00:10:34.350 align:middle line:84%
So at the end of 2014 and
the week between Christmas

00:10:34.350 --> 00:10:37.290 align:middle line:84%
and New Year's, I holed up
in my studio with my mic

00:10:37.290 --> 00:10:42.055 align:middle line:84%
and I basically recorded
this Eleven talk series.

00:10:42.055 --> 00:10:43.680 align:middle line:84%
And I don't name her,
but I'm basically

00:10:43.680 --> 00:10:44.930 align:middle line:90%
talking to her the whole time.

00:10:44.930 --> 00:10:50.590 align:middle line:90%


00:10:50.590 --> 00:10:55.060 align:middle line:84%
In that, I basically outline
the full arc of everything

00:10:55.060 --> 00:10:59.350 align:middle line:84%
I barfed out in
Hilo on the volcano.

00:10:59.350 --> 00:11:03.190 align:middle line:84%
And to me, that was
basically the muse, if you

00:11:03.190 --> 00:11:06.280 align:middle line:84%
want to call her that, coming in
and saying, well, that's fine.

00:11:06.280 --> 00:11:07.900 align:middle line:90%
I've given you this.

00:11:07.900 --> 00:11:09.400 align:middle line:90%
I've sent you all these signals.

00:11:09.400 --> 00:11:11.150 align:middle line:84%
I've pulled all the
stuff out of you,

00:11:11.150 --> 00:11:13.160 align:middle line:84%
and you're still
being chickenshit.

00:11:13.160 --> 00:11:13.960 align:middle line:90%
And that's fine.

00:11:13.960 --> 00:11:18.230 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you're just
human, and a man.

00:11:18.230 --> 00:11:20.860 align:middle line:90%
It's all fine.

00:11:20.860 --> 00:11:23.740 align:middle line:84%
But I just want to make
it clear that if you

00:11:23.740 --> 00:11:29.330 align:middle line:84%
turn your back on me, you're
turning your back on her too.

00:11:29.330 --> 00:11:31.550 align:middle line:90%
Fuck with me.

00:11:31.550 --> 00:11:34.430 align:middle line:90%
And I was like, fine.

00:11:34.430 --> 00:11:37.135 align:middle line:90%
Fine.

00:11:37.135 --> 00:11:38.810 align:middle line:90%
So I recorded the Eleven talks.

00:11:38.810 --> 00:11:41.840 align:middle line:90%
I sent them to her.

00:11:41.840 --> 00:11:48.570 align:middle line:90%
Long story short, she did well.

00:11:48.570 --> 00:11:49.370 align:middle line:90%
She did well.

00:11:49.370 --> 00:11:50.245 align:middle line:90%
She stopped drinking.

00:11:50.245 --> 00:11:54.540 align:middle line:84%
She stopped using, the
whole roller coaster.

00:11:54.540 --> 00:11:56.840 align:middle line:90%
And to me, every now and then--

00:11:56.840 --> 00:11:57.770 align:middle line:90%
I mean, we're friends.

00:11:57.770 --> 00:12:00.720 align:middle line:84%
Every now and then, she'll
still email me saying, well,

00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:02.180 align:middle line:90%
I fell off the wagon.

00:12:02.180 --> 00:12:04.370 align:middle line:84%
I had half a shot,
and I spit it out.

00:12:04.370 --> 00:12:05.630 align:middle line:90%
It just tasted disgusting.

00:12:05.630 --> 00:12:06.713 align:middle line:90%
But I'm such a bad person.

00:12:06.713 --> 00:12:10.940 align:middle line:84%
And I'm just like, every
time I get an email from you,

00:12:10.940 --> 00:12:14.060 align:middle line:84%
I do a happy dance around
my office because I'm like,

00:12:14.060 --> 00:12:16.160 align:middle line:90%
you're unkillable.

00:12:16.160 --> 00:12:19.340 align:middle line:84%
I'm just so happy every day
I know you're still alive

00:12:19.340 --> 00:12:22.260 align:middle line:84%
and you're with your
son and all of that.

00:12:22.260 --> 00:12:26.990 align:middle line:84%
And so that's how I got
pulled kicking and screaming

00:12:26.990 --> 00:12:29.240 align:middle line:90%
into healing.

00:12:29.240 --> 00:12:31.758 align:middle line:84%
And after I shot
that, I just gave

00:12:31.758 --> 00:12:33.050 align:middle line:90%
it to all my meditation people.

00:12:33.050 --> 00:12:35.300 align:middle line:84%
And they were like, this is
like the best meditation.

00:12:35.300 --> 00:12:37.400 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, it's
not a meditation.

00:12:37.400 --> 00:12:38.370 align:middle line:90%
It's-- never mind.

00:12:38.370 --> 00:12:39.170 align:middle line:90%
Fine.

00:12:39.170 --> 00:12:42.100 align:middle line:90%


00:12:42.100 --> 00:12:44.240 align:middle line:84%
And so the way I
characterize what

00:12:44.240 --> 00:12:54.290 align:middle line:84%
I do is that the main arrow that
I care about that my bliss is

00:12:54.290 --> 00:12:59.430 align:middle line:84%
is to help people to the
extent that they want--

00:12:59.430 --> 00:13:02.750 align:middle line:84%
and many people don't
want this, and that's OK--

00:13:02.750 --> 00:13:04.430 align:middle line:84%
to help people get
to a point where

00:13:04.430 --> 00:13:08.060 align:middle line:84%
they are able to basically
ask the question of,

00:13:08.060 --> 00:13:08.990 align:middle line:90%
what is my bliss?

00:13:08.990 --> 00:13:11.870 align:middle line:84%
What is my meaning
and purpose in life?

00:13:11.870 --> 00:13:13.580 align:middle line:84%
And then arrange
things in their life

00:13:13.580 --> 00:13:17.310 align:middle line:84%
to be able to actually pursue
it and fulfill it, if they want.

00:13:17.310 --> 00:13:18.110 align:middle line:90%
There is no should.

00:13:18.110 --> 00:13:19.700 align:middle line:84%
If you don't want to do this,
you're not a bad person.

00:13:19.700 --> 00:13:21.050 align:middle line:90%
You're not wasting your life.

00:13:21.050 --> 00:13:23.275 align:middle line:84%
I don't believe in any
of that finger-wagging.

00:13:23.275 --> 00:13:24.650 align:middle line:84%
But for the people
who want to do

00:13:24.650 --> 00:13:31.400 align:middle line:84%
that, my job is to be
this kind of Mercury,

00:13:31.400 --> 00:13:35.480 align:middle line:84%
kind of Hermes kind
of guide advisor

00:13:35.480 --> 00:13:39.090 align:middle line:90%
to help them along that path.

00:13:39.090 --> 00:13:40.760 align:middle line:84%
And what I've
discovered along the way

00:13:40.760 --> 00:13:46.220 align:middle line:84%
is that when you hear
about bliss, it's like, oh,

00:13:46.220 --> 00:13:50.330 align:middle line:84%
it's so wonderful, and rainbows
and unicorns on the one hand.

00:13:50.330 --> 00:13:52.830 align:middle line:84%
And on the other hand, you have
a whole school folks wagging

00:13:52.830 --> 00:13:54.455 align:middle line:84%
the finger, well, if
you don't do this,

00:13:54.455 --> 00:13:55.510 align:middle line:90%
you're wasting your life.

00:13:55.510 --> 00:13:59.090 align:middle line:84%
And I don't subscribe
to either of those.

00:13:59.090 --> 00:14:02.030 align:middle line:84%
My view of bliss is
that to really get

00:14:02.030 --> 00:14:07.220 align:middle line:84%
on the path of following your
bliss, it is a messy business.

00:14:07.220 --> 00:14:08.530 align:middle line:90%
It is a messy business.

00:14:08.530 --> 00:14:10.280 align:middle line:84%
Because when we're
brought into this world

00:14:10.280 --> 00:14:15.080 align:middle line:84%
as it is and we're trained to
conform and put on a mask--

00:14:15.080 --> 00:14:17.930 align:middle line:84%
women are typically told
to put on the mask that

00:14:17.930 --> 00:14:21.635 align:middle line:84%
basically says "The Good
Girl" across the top, right?

00:14:21.635 --> 00:14:23.840 align:middle line:84%
And we could talk for
hours about all that.

00:14:23.840 --> 00:14:25.490 align:middle line:84%
And guys are basically
given this mask

00:14:25.490 --> 00:14:29.030 align:middle line:84%
saying "The Strong Boy"
or "The Strong Man."

00:14:29.030 --> 00:14:31.670 align:middle line:84%
Note that it's the "strong
man," not necessarily

00:14:31.670 --> 00:14:33.770 align:middle line:90%
the good man, right?

00:14:33.770 --> 00:14:39.200 align:middle line:84%
And if you realize
underneath the mask,

00:14:39.200 --> 00:14:40.940 align:middle line:84%
your bliss takes you
in a direction which

00:14:40.940 --> 00:14:45.320 align:middle line:84%
requires you to
take that mask off,

00:14:45.320 --> 00:14:48.320 align:middle line:90%
you're in for a lot of trouble.

00:14:48.320 --> 00:14:51.530 align:middle line:84%
And the older you
are, the more time

00:14:51.530 --> 00:14:56.420 align:middle line:84%
you have allowed to
elapse for your world

00:14:56.420 --> 00:15:01.730 align:middle line:84%
to accrete around you, presuming
that mask is the real you.

00:15:01.730 --> 00:15:04.070 align:middle line:84%
When you start to take
that off, your entire world

00:15:04.070 --> 00:15:06.170 align:middle line:90%
starts to wobble.

00:15:06.170 --> 00:15:15.800 align:middle line:84%
And so for me, when
I sort of offer

00:15:15.800 --> 00:15:20.480 align:middle line:84%
resources and tools for people
to do self-reflection and maybe

00:15:20.480 --> 00:15:24.800 align:middle line:84%
try to self-heal some
things to the extent

00:15:24.800 --> 00:15:29.270 align:middle line:84%
that they're comfortable,
the goal in my mind

00:15:29.270 --> 00:15:36.860 align:middle line:84%
is always to see if you feel
ready and desirous of actually

00:15:36.860 --> 00:15:38.030 align:middle line:90%
following your bliss.

00:15:38.030 --> 00:15:43.730 align:middle line:84%
To me, the purpose of healing
is not the cessation of pain.

00:15:43.730 --> 00:15:49.910 align:middle line:84%
The purpose of healing is
to recover your own fulsome

00:15:49.910 --> 00:15:51.315 align:middle line:90%
wholeness.

00:15:51.315 --> 00:15:53.690 align:middle line:84%
And it's with that wholeness
that you're able to actually

00:15:53.690 --> 00:15:56.180 align:middle line:84%
figure out, who
am I actually now

00:15:56.180 --> 00:15:59.270 align:middle line:84%
that I've accounted
for everyone within me?

00:15:59.270 --> 00:16:01.730 align:middle line:84%
And what do we
actually want to do?

00:16:01.730 --> 00:16:04.250 align:middle line:84%
And what are the pitfalls
and risks and threats

00:16:04.250 --> 00:16:08.900 align:middle line:84%
if we go down that path, and
do we actually want to do that?

00:16:08.900 --> 00:16:11.770 align:middle line:84%
The answer may be
no, and that's OK.

00:16:11.770 --> 00:16:14.000 align:middle line:84%
So that to me,
healing is a means

00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:17.630 align:middle line:84%
to the end of getting you to
the point where you can actually

00:16:17.630 --> 00:16:20.330 align:middle line:84%
even make consciously
the choice of go or no go

00:16:20.330 --> 00:16:24.200 align:middle line:84%
on the full flowering
of why you're here.

00:16:24.200 --> 00:16:26.500 align:middle line:84%
Healing is not just
the cessation of pain.

00:16:26.500 --> 00:16:27.850 align:middle line:90%
A pill will do that, right?

00:16:27.850 --> 00:16:33.590 align:middle line:84%
A couple of martinis
will do that temporarily.

00:16:33.590 --> 00:16:38.270 align:middle line:84%
And so when people
come to me with things

00:16:38.270 --> 00:16:40.460 align:middle line:84%
that they feel meditation
will help with,

00:16:40.460 --> 00:16:42.620 align:middle line:84%
finding their bliss
will help with,

00:16:42.620 --> 00:16:47.100 align:middle line:84%
recovering exiled parts of
themselves will help with,

00:16:47.100 --> 00:16:47.900 align:middle line:90%
that's great.

00:16:47.900 --> 00:16:51.330 align:middle line:84%
I'm a nerd, and I love
discussing all of that stuff.

00:16:51.330 --> 00:16:55.310 align:middle line:84%
But at the end of the
day, it is with this half

00:16:55.310 --> 00:17:06.650 align:middle line:84%
an eye to get you to willingly,
or in some cases accidentally,

00:17:06.650 --> 00:17:11.420 align:middle line:84%
stumble across this glimmer
of a vision of like, oh, I

00:17:11.420 --> 00:17:18.140 align:middle line:84%
think I'm actually here to do
something along this direction.

00:17:18.140 --> 00:17:27.140 align:middle line:84%
And once you have that
glimmer, it's hard to forget.

00:17:27.140 --> 00:17:30.690 align:middle line:84%
That's what makes me
happy and excited.

00:17:30.690 --> 00:17:31.490 align:middle line:90%
>> That's cool.

00:17:31.490 --> 00:17:34.860 align:middle line:90%


00:17:34.860 --> 00:17:35.660 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for that.

00:17:35.660 --> 00:17:38.687 align:middle line:84%
It helps describe, I guess, the
mission and the guiding force

00:17:38.687 --> 00:17:40.520 align:middle line:84%
behind what you do,
which you've discovered,

00:17:40.520 --> 00:17:42.770 align:middle line:84%
which is to help really
people align with their place.

00:17:42.770 --> 00:17:45.710 align:middle line:84%
And this sort of meditation
to emotional trauma component

00:17:45.710 --> 00:17:48.590 align:middle line:84%
is just a stepping
stone, in a way.

00:17:48.590 --> 00:17:50.930 align:middle line:84%
So let's speak to
that a little bit.

00:17:50.930 --> 00:17:55.130 align:middle line:84%
How typically do people
develop emotional wounds,

00:17:55.130 --> 00:17:56.510 align:middle line:90%
as you call them?

00:17:56.510 --> 00:18:00.890 align:middle line:84%
And what sort of environments
might that happen in?

00:18:00.890 --> 00:18:03.890 align:middle line:84%
Like, is it the environment
of the narcissistic father

00:18:03.890 --> 00:18:05.600 align:middle line:84%
or the split
personality this or the

00:18:05.600 --> 00:18:09.390 align:middle line:84%
bipolar this or in the language
that gets spoken to them?

00:18:09.390 --> 00:18:12.770 align:middle line:84%
How do people develop these type
wounds, in your understanding?

00:18:12.770 --> 00:18:14.525 align:middle line:90%
>> You know, it's interesting.

00:18:14.525 --> 00:18:17.060 align:middle line:90%


00:18:17.060 --> 00:18:19.070 align:middle line:84%
I'll give you kind of
this headline first,

00:18:19.070 --> 00:18:21.330 align:middle line:84%
and then I want to
dive in a little bit.

00:18:21.330 --> 00:18:25.280 align:middle line:84%
But the headline
for me is that I've

00:18:25.280 --> 00:18:28.410 align:middle line:84%
worked with tens of thousands
of people at this point.

00:18:28.410 --> 00:18:32.990 align:middle line:84%
And I don't consider myself
a professional or expert.

00:18:32.990 --> 00:18:34.370 align:middle line:84%
I've just seen a
lot of patterns.

00:18:34.370 --> 00:18:37.520 align:middle line:84%
And in my non-expert,
non-professional kind

00:18:37.520 --> 00:18:44.580 align:middle line:84%
of feeling of the
things I've seen,

00:18:44.580 --> 00:18:52.830 align:middle line:84%
my sense is that
everyone has a wound.

00:18:52.830 --> 00:18:56.670 align:middle line:84%
And that's OK, and
that's actually normal.

00:18:56.670 --> 00:19:00.240 align:middle line:90%


00:19:00.240 --> 00:19:05.100 align:middle line:84%
It's not a-- it's hard
to find the right words,

00:19:05.100 --> 00:19:08.310 align:middle line:84%
but it's not a tragedy
of epic proportions

00:19:08.310 --> 00:19:13.180 align:middle line:84%
that everyone in humanity
ends up having a wound.

00:19:13.180 --> 00:19:17.070 align:middle line:84%
It is tragic in the sense of
the severity of some people's

00:19:17.070 --> 00:19:19.580 align:middle line:90%
wounds, right?

00:19:19.580 --> 00:19:23.782 align:middle line:84%
You can't help but have
empathy for that and compassion

00:19:23.782 --> 00:19:24.990 align:middle line:90%
and feel that pain with them.

00:19:24.990 --> 00:19:31.980 align:middle line:84%
But it's almost, to me at
this point with everything

00:19:31.980 --> 00:19:35.160 align:middle line:84%
I've seen, a kind of universal
anatomical feature, if you

00:19:35.160 --> 00:19:36.670 align:middle line:90%
will.

00:19:36.670 --> 00:19:41.550 align:middle line:84%
And this is, in its own
way, a beautiful thing,

00:19:41.550 --> 00:19:47.040 align:middle line:84%
because the wound is what
sets you up for bliss.

00:19:47.040 --> 00:19:51.330 align:middle line:84%
I think Joseph Campbell
used to quote someone else--

00:19:51.330 --> 00:19:52.280 align:middle line:90%
and I don't remember.

00:19:52.280 --> 00:19:53.480 align:middle line:90%
I don't think I even know.

00:19:53.480 --> 00:19:56.910 align:middle line:84%
But the thing he used
to say over and over

00:19:56.910 --> 00:20:08.420 align:middle line:84%
is that your deepest wound is
the source of your greatest

00:20:08.420 --> 00:20:11.360 align:middle line:90%
gift to the world.

00:20:11.360 --> 00:20:18.560 align:middle line:84%
And so it's your wound that
basically throws the penny

00:20:18.560 --> 00:20:22.350 align:middle line:84%
into the deep end
of the pool for you

00:20:22.350 --> 00:20:25.040 align:middle line:84%
then to dive down in terms
of fulfilling and finding

00:20:25.040 --> 00:20:26.810 align:middle line:90%
your bliss.

00:20:26.810 --> 00:20:31.130 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how it turned
out to be like that,

00:20:31.130 --> 00:20:33.990 align:middle line:84%
but that's the pattern
I see in everyone.

00:20:33.990 --> 00:20:36.650 align:middle line:90%


00:20:36.650 --> 00:20:38.900 align:middle line:84%
And so to your question of
how do these wounds develop

00:20:38.900 --> 00:20:42.350 align:middle line:84%
in general, I don't
think of it as like, oh,

00:20:42.350 --> 00:20:45.353 align:middle line:84%
there's this part
of the population.

00:20:45.353 --> 00:20:46.770 align:middle line:84%
We know what's
going on with them,

00:20:46.770 --> 00:20:48.650 align:middle line:90%
but everyone else is all right.

00:20:48.650 --> 00:20:50.120 align:middle line:90%
For me, it's universal.

00:20:50.120 --> 00:20:55.250 align:middle line:84%
And for me, the basic thumbnail
of how I have seen it happen

00:20:55.250 --> 00:21:00.010 align:middle line:84%
and I have heard it kind
of relayed thousands

00:21:00.010 --> 00:21:05.030 align:middle line:84%
upon thousands of
times is this idea of,

00:21:05.030 --> 00:21:07.670 align:middle line:84%
you're born into the
world as a child.

00:21:07.670 --> 00:21:12.482 align:middle line:84%
As a child, you have no control
over your outer environment.

00:21:12.482 --> 00:21:13.940 align:middle line:84%
You don't get to
pick your parents.

00:21:13.940 --> 00:21:16.970 align:middle line:84%
You certainly don't get to
pick your siblings or any

00:21:16.970 --> 00:21:18.530 align:middle line:90%
of that stuff, right?

00:21:18.530 --> 00:21:20.600 align:middle line:84%
So you're born into
this environment.

00:21:20.600 --> 00:21:27.740 align:middle line:84%
And pretty quickly, the
giants in your world--

00:21:27.740 --> 00:21:33.170 align:middle line:84%
the adults-- look at you and
say, all right, little boy.

00:21:33.170 --> 00:21:36.720 align:middle line:84%
Now we want you to put
this thing on, or else.

00:21:36.720 --> 00:21:38.480 align:middle line:90%
And they hand you this mask.

00:21:38.480 --> 00:21:41.030 align:middle line:90%


00:21:41.030 --> 00:21:43.490 align:middle line:84%
And the mask for boys
will say, you know,

00:21:43.490 --> 00:21:46.520 align:middle line:90%
the strong silent type.

00:21:46.520 --> 00:21:48.980 align:middle line:84%
For women, it will be
the good girl typically,

00:21:48.980 --> 00:21:51.710 align:middle line:90%
some form of the good girl.

00:21:51.710 --> 00:21:55.160 align:middle line:84%
And you learn pretty
quickly that this mask comes

00:21:55.160 --> 00:21:58.910 align:middle line:84%
with a set of expectations
around your behavior,

00:21:58.910 --> 00:22:03.680 align:middle line:84%
around things you'll
say, around things you're

00:22:03.680 --> 00:22:07.370 align:middle line:90%
allowed to think and not think.

00:22:07.370 --> 00:22:11.570 align:middle line:84%
And the consequences for when
you take it off and speak your

00:22:11.570 --> 00:22:16.520 align:middle line:84%
mind as a child, especially
in the wrong environment--

00:22:16.520 --> 00:22:20.750 align:middle line:84%
touching things that you're
not supposed to touch,

00:22:20.750 --> 00:22:22.670 align:middle line:84%
saying things, being
curious about things

00:22:22.670 --> 00:22:25.662 align:middle line:84%
that you're not supposed
to be curious about.

00:22:25.662 --> 00:22:27.620 align:middle line:84%
What you realize as a
young person is that when

00:22:27.620 --> 00:22:30.950 align:middle line:84%
you start to take that
mask off, justice is swift.

00:22:30.950 --> 00:22:36.260 align:middle line:90%


00:22:36.260 --> 00:22:39.710 align:middle line:84%
The mask then comes with
its own penal code of like,

00:22:39.710 --> 00:22:43.910 align:middle line:84%
if you take it off, here are
the escalating levels of voltage

00:22:43.910 --> 00:22:45.680 align:middle line:84%
that will be applied
to you to get you

00:22:45.680 --> 00:22:48.380 align:middle line:90%
to put the damn thing back on.

00:22:48.380 --> 00:22:50.730 align:middle line:84%
Now, for me there's nothing
wrong with this mask.

00:22:50.730 --> 00:22:54.440 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we all need masks to
put on to get on with the world.

00:22:54.440 --> 00:22:56.510 align:middle line:90%
Society has to work.

00:22:56.510 --> 00:23:04.500 align:middle line:84%
It's just a natural part of
getting on as a social species.

00:23:04.500 --> 00:23:06.980 align:middle line:84%
But the issue that
often happens is

00:23:06.980 --> 00:23:11.820 align:middle line:84%
that because you're being
asked to put this mask on--

00:23:11.820 --> 00:23:14.450 align:middle line:84%
if you're my child, I may
enforce it pretty strictly, but

00:23:14.450 --> 00:23:16.340 align:middle line:90%
because I want to protect you.

00:23:16.340 --> 00:23:18.530 align:middle line:84%
I don't want you to get
beaten up in the schoolyard

00:23:18.530 --> 00:23:19.100 align:middle line:90%
after school.

00:23:19.100 --> 00:23:20.570 align:middle line:84%
I don't want you
to be ostracized.

00:23:20.570 --> 00:23:23.602 align:middle line:84%
I want you to have prestige
and money and all the things

00:23:23.602 --> 00:23:24.560 align:middle line:90%
you want in this world.

00:23:24.560 --> 00:23:29.120 align:middle line:84%
And that requires the
participation and cooperation

00:23:29.120 --> 00:23:31.460 align:middle line:84%
and even adulation
of people around you,

00:23:31.460 --> 00:23:34.760 align:middle line:84%
and you need to put a certain
kind of mask on for that.

00:23:34.760 --> 00:23:40.910 align:middle line:84%
But where the wound comes
in then is where as a kid

00:23:40.910 --> 00:23:45.890 align:middle line:90%
you're like, holy crap.

00:23:45.890 --> 00:23:52.380 align:middle line:84%
Every time I take this thing
off, I get cattle prodded hard.

00:23:52.380 --> 00:23:56.090 align:middle line:84%
So it must mean that they
want me to put this on.

00:23:56.090 --> 00:24:01.520 align:middle line:84%
And as a child, if nobody pulls
you aside to explain all this--

00:24:01.520 --> 00:24:03.360 align:middle line:90%
kids are not stupid.

00:24:03.360 --> 00:24:07.160 align:middle line:84%
They can connect the
dots and do the math.

00:24:07.160 --> 00:24:09.590 align:middle line:84%
And for most kids
who are thinking

00:24:09.590 --> 00:24:14.330 align:middle line:84%
about it, which is pretty much
all kids, they will conclude--

00:24:14.330 --> 00:24:16.730 align:middle line:90%
and not unreasonably so--

00:24:16.730 --> 00:24:22.610 align:middle line:84%
that if I take this mask
off, I will lose love.

00:24:22.610 --> 00:24:24.590 align:middle line:90%
I will not be worthy of love.

00:24:24.590 --> 00:24:26.330 align:middle line:90%
I will not be a good person.

00:24:26.330 --> 00:24:30.890 align:middle line:84%
And the message for many people
is, you won't deserve love--

00:24:30.890 --> 00:24:34.030 align:middle line:84%
which means, don't expect
love from anyone around you.

00:24:34.030 --> 00:24:37.760 align:middle line:84%
But also, if you intrinsically
don't deserve love,

00:24:37.760 --> 00:24:41.000 align:middle line:84%
you shouldn't even
love yourself.

00:24:41.000 --> 00:24:44.840 align:middle line:84%
You within you shouldn't
even love yourself.

00:24:44.840 --> 00:24:47.890 align:middle line:90%
And that's poisonous.

00:24:47.890 --> 00:24:51.590 align:middle line:84%
Now, unbeknownst to the
little six-year-old,

00:24:51.590 --> 00:24:53.440 align:middle line:84%
the parents around
them could be perfectly

00:24:53.440 --> 00:24:55.940 align:middle line:84%
willing to die for them, take
a bullet for them or whatever.

00:24:55.940 --> 00:24:58.488 align:middle line:84%
But you don't know that as a
kid, because you've never held

00:24:58.488 --> 00:25:00.780 align:middle line:84%
your own little newborn in
your arms where you're like,

00:25:00.780 --> 00:25:04.780 align:middle line:84%
oh my gosh, I would die for
this little peanut, right?

00:25:04.780 --> 00:25:06.730 align:middle line:84%
So for you as a kid
you're like, well,

00:25:06.730 --> 00:25:08.685 align:middle line:90%
it feels like I'm losing love.

00:25:08.685 --> 00:25:10.060 align:middle line:84%
When I don't get
to have dessert,

00:25:10.060 --> 00:25:12.790 align:middle line:84%
when I get sent to my room,
when I get physically punished,

00:25:12.790 --> 00:25:15.175 align:middle line:90%
it feels like I'm not loved.

00:25:15.175 --> 00:25:18.280 align:middle line:90%


00:25:18.280 --> 00:25:20.500 align:middle line:90%
Of course it feels like that.

00:25:20.500 --> 00:25:24.520 align:middle line:84%
So in the absence of an elder
pulling them aside to say,

00:25:24.520 --> 00:25:26.900 align:middle line:84%
look, you are loved
without condition.

00:25:26.900 --> 00:25:29.170 align:middle line:84%
You are loved without
condition, period.

00:25:29.170 --> 00:25:32.230 align:middle line:84%
Any of us here would
die for you, period.

00:25:32.230 --> 00:25:34.150 align:middle line:84%
And if we wouldn't,
or if you think

00:25:34.150 --> 00:25:36.560 align:middle line:84%
we wouldn't, or if we actually
wouldn't, that's on us.

00:25:36.560 --> 00:25:37.360 align:middle line:90%
That's not on you.

00:25:37.360 --> 00:25:38.920 align:middle line:90%
That's a wound that we have.

00:25:38.920 --> 00:25:40.930 align:middle line:90%
It's a defect that we carry.

00:25:40.930 --> 00:25:43.660 align:middle line:84%
It has nothing to do with
your intrinsic loveability.

00:25:43.660 --> 00:25:48.220 align:middle line:84%
Your love without
condition, period.

00:25:48.220 --> 00:25:50.300 align:middle line:90%
Now, with that aside--

00:25:50.300 --> 00:25:51.830 align:middle line:90%
love's not on the table--

00:25:51.830 --> 00:25:54.310 align:middle line:84%
let's talk about how
we keep your mask on.

00:25:54.310 --> 00:25:58.900 align:middle line:84%
Because I want you to have
all the things you want.

00:25:58.900 --> 00:26:00.890 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about how to--

00:26:00.890 --> 00:26:03.790 align:middle line:84%
and at that point,
you're their advisor,

00:26:03.790 --> 00:26:09.650 align:middle line:84%
helping them, in their pit crew
while they're driving the race

00:26:09.650 --> 00:26:13.090 align:middle line:84%
car, helping them win the
race that they choose to run.

00:26:13.090 --> 00:26:16.270 align:middle line:90%


00:26:16.270 --> 00:26:20.680 align:middle line:84%
But for most people, they
don't pull their kids aside

00:26:20.680 --> 00:26:23.320 align:middle line:84%
to explain that, because it
was never explained to them.

00:26:23.320 --> 00:26:25.630 align:middle line:84%
They're still running
for their lives thinking,

00:26:25.630 --> 00:26:28.540 align:middle line:84%
I need to make my
revenue this quarter

00:26:28.540 --> 00:26:32.026 align:middle line:84%
or I will not deserve love,
even from my own self.

00:26:32.026 --> 00:26:35.520 align:middle line:90%
And that's a great motivator.

00:26:35.520 --> 00:26:36.520 align:middle line:90%
It's great for earnings.

00:26:36.520 --> 00:26:38.020 align:middle line:84%
It's great for
your bank account.

00:26:38.020 --> 00:26:41.850 align:middle line:90%
It's great for a lot of things.

00:26:41.850 --> 00:26:46.210 align:middle line:84%
And it's not that I am
against any economic growth

00:26:46.210 --> 00:26:47.350 align:middle line:90%
and thriving or whatever.

00:26:47.350 --> 00:26:49.105 align:middle line:84%
But it's just a
question of the cost.

00:26:49.105 --> 00:26:51.700 align:middle line:90%


00:26:51.700 --> 00:26:56.390 align:middle line:84%
To have that sort of
fear hanging over you

00:26:56.390 --> 00:27:00.610 align:middle line:84%
and have that be the reason you
are so productive in your life,

00:27:00.610 --> 00:27:04.450 align:middle line:90%
that to me is too high a cost.

00:27:04.450 --> 00:27:07.970 align:middle line:84%
And it's not even an issue
of the practical cost.

00:27:07.970 --> 00:27:11.670 align:middle line:84%
It's the fact that it
isn't actually true.

00:27:11.670 --> 00:27:16.840 align:middle line:84%
No matter how bad your dad was,
how harsh he was, at the end

00:27:16.840 --> 00:27:20.980 align:middle line:84%
of the day he would
give his life for you.

00:27:20.980 --> 00:27:24.320 align:middle line:84%
And every now and then I'll
come across someone who says,

00:27:24.320 --> 00:27:25.240 align:middle line:90%
no, that's not true.

00:27:25.240 --> 00:27:27.407 align:middle line:90%
That's just not true.

00:27:27.407 --> 00:27:28.990 align:middle line:84%
Actually, there was
an actual incident

00:27:28.990 --> 00:27:31.330 align:middle line:84%
where my dad said,
take him and not me.

00:27:31.330 --> 00:27:33.970 align:middle line:90%
I've heard everything.

00:27:33.970 --> 00:27:35.710 align:middle line:84%
And even in that
case I'm like, well,

00:27:35.710 --> 00:27:38.140 align:middle line:84%
it still doesn't impinge on
your inherent loveability.

00:27:38.140 --> 00:27:40.990 align:middle line:90%


00:27:40.990 --> 00:27:44.640 align:middle line:84%
Because if a parent doesn't look
after their kid in that way,

00:27:44.640 --> 00:27:47.950 align:middle line:90%
the parent is wounded.

00:27:47.950 --> 00:27:52.490 align:middle line:84%
And I've never heard anyone say
their parent didn't love them

00:27:52.490 --> 00:27:55.480 align:middle line:84%
and then when I ask them, well,
do you think they were wounded,

00:27:55.480 --> 00:28:00.430 align:middle line:84%
100% of the time they're like,
oh, yeah, let me tell you.

00:28:00.430 --> 00:28:07.282 align:middle line:84%
No normal healthy person
isn't willing at a snap

00:28:07.282 --> 00:28:08.740 align:middle line:84%
to give their life
for their child.

00:28:08.740 --> 00:28:10.840 align:middle line:90%


00:28:10.840 --> 00:28:13.990 align:middle line:90%
Whales will do that.

00:28:13.990 --> 00:28:15.250 align:middle line:90%
Mother bears will do that.

00:28:15.250 --> 00:28:16.708 align:middle line:84%
You don't even have
to be a mammal.

00:28:16.708 --> 00:28:18.698 align:middle line:90%
Chickens will do that.

00:28:18.698 --> 00:28:19.990 align:middle line:90%
And so humans are no different.

00:28:19.990 --> 00:28:22.633 align:middle line:84%
We're wired for protection
of our offspring.

00:28:22.633 --> 00:28:24.550 align:middle line:84%
And to the extent that
that fails in practice,

00:28:24.550 --> 00:28:28.030 align:middle line:90%
it's simply because of a wound.

00:28:28.030 --> 00:28:32.710 align:middle line:84%
But very rare is the
child where someone pulls

00:28:32.710 --> 00:28:35.410 align:middle line:84%
them aside to kind of chalk
talk all this through, to say,

00:28:35.410 --> 00:28:38.690 align:middle line:84%
OK, there's nothing
wrong with you.

00:28:38.690 --> 00:28:40.600 align:middle line:90%
You're actually awesome.

00:28:40.600 --> 00:28:42.820 align:middle line:84%
And despite all this,
there's a little bit

00:28:42.820 --> 00:28:44.500 align:middle line:84%
of navigating we
need to get you out

00:28:44.500 --> 00:28:47.800 align:middle line:84%
of the minefield to go on and
find and follow your bliss.

00:28:47.800 --> 00:28:51.880 align:middle line:84%
Because when you do
that, the importance--

00:28:51.880 --> 00:28:53.830 align:middle line:84%
I mean, as a tech
person, the scalability

00:28:53.830 --> 00:28:57.730 align:middle line:84%
of helping people find
and follow their bliss

00:28:57.730 --> 00:29:05.110 align:middle line:84%
is powerful, because when a
person is following their bliss

00:29:05.110 --> 00:29:07.990 align:middle line:84%
there's kind of two
orders of benefit.

00:29:07.990 --> 00:29:12.700 align:middle line:84%
The first order is, when you
find and follow your bliss,

00:29:12.700 --> 00:29:16.950 align:middle line:84%
it is the things you love
to do for no good reason,

00:29:16.950 --> 00:29:20.980 align:middle line:84%
that you would pay to do if you
had to and you had the means--

00:29:20.980 --> 00:29:25.780 align:middle line:84%
which also, as a byproduct,
as a sort of happy accident,

00:29:25.780 --> 00:29:29.450 align:middle line:90%
creates value for other people.

00:29:29.450 --> 00:29:32.200 align:middle line:84%
So there's all these things
you love to do, some of which

00:29:32.200 --> 00:29:34.520 align:middle line:90%
create value for people.

00:29:34.520 --> 00:29:36.920 align:middle line:84%
And then at the
bottom is what I call

00:29:36.920 --> 00:29:38.990 align:middle line:84%
a bliss target, or
an empathy target,

00:29:38.990 --> 00:29:42.040 align:middle line:84%
which is a
constituency of people

00:29:42.040 --> 00:29:47.770 align:middle line:84%
that you have just
disproportionate empathy for.

00:29:47.770 --> 00:29:50.980 align:middle line:84%
You will drop everything to
help this stranger, friend

00:29:50.980 --> 00:29:54.190 align:middle line:84%
of a friend of a friend,
build their backyard

00:29:54.190 --> 00:30:01.960 align:middle line:84%
deck for barbecuing, if that
happens to be your bliss.

00:30:01.960 --> 00:30:04.420 align:middle line:84%
You have those three
things together

00:30:04.420 --> 00:30:08.110 align:middle line:84%
and you've got a
complete bliss circuit.

00:30:08.110 --> 00:30:12.520 align:middle line:84%
And so when you find
and follow your bliss,

00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:17.410 align:middle line:84%
the first order of benefit
is your empathy target.

00:30:17.410 --> 00:30:20.020 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they are benefiting
all the live long day

00:30:20.020 --> 00:30:23.530 align:middle line:84%
from you just doing the
thing you love selfishly.

00:30:23.530 --> 00:30:25.510 align:middle line:84%
But then the
second-order benefit

00:30:25.510 --> 00:30:30.040 align:middle line:84%
is that you become a signpost
to other people around you.

00:30:30.040 --> 00:30:32.905 align:middle line:84%
When you're finding and
following your bliss, you are--

00:30:32.905 --> 00:30:34.780 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we talk about
soothing and shielding.

00:30:34.780 --> 00:30:38.200 align:middle line:84%
Following your bliss is
the ultimate soothing,

00:30:38.200 --> 00:30:41.890 align:middle line:84%
because it feels good
minute to minute.

00:30:41.890 --> 00:30:43.630 align:middle line:84%
And it's also the
ultimate shielding,

00:30:43.630 --> 00:30:46.690 align:middle line:84%
because you have this
goofy smile on your face

00:30:46.690 --> 00:30:48.340 align:middle line:84%
the whole time, and
you really don't

00:30:48.340 --> 00:30:49.660 align:middle line:90%
care what other people think.

00:30:49.660 --> 00:30:51.327 align:middle line:84%
I mean, someone taps
you on the shoulder

00:30:51.327 --> 00:30:55.780 align:middle line:84%
and asks you who your mother
is, and you don't know,

00:30:55.780 --> 00:30:59.620 align:middle line:84%
because you're so in the
flow of what you're doing.

00:30:59.620 --> 00:31:03.970 align:middle line:84%
And people can smell
that a mile away.

00:31:03.970 --> 00:31:07.990 align:middle line:90%


00:31:07.990 --> 00:31:11.030 align:middle line:84%
You can feel it when you're
sitting in the room with them.

00:31:11.030 --> 00:31:13.450 align:middle line:84%
And so that is to me
an even more powerful--

00:31:13.450 --> 00:31:14.770 align:middle line:90%
because it's more generalized.

00:31:14.770 --> 00:31:16.728 align:middle line:84%
When you're following
your bliss, your own sort

00:31:16.728 --> 00:31:19.150 align:middle line:84%
of nerdy empathy
target benefits,

00:31:19.150 --> 00:31:20.830 align:middle line:84%
you become a
signpost for everyone

00:31:20.830 --> 00:31:23.920 align:middle line:84%
around you, because
people look at you when

00:31:23.920 --> 00:31:25.510 align:middle line:90%
you're following your bliss.

00:31:25.510 --> 00:31:29.350 align:middle line:84%
And hopefully, the reaction is,
first of all, they're inspired.

00:31:29.350 --> 00:31:31.520 align:middle line:84%
Like, oh my gosh,
she's so amazing.

00:31:31.520 --> 00:31:35.110 align:middle line:84%
But then hopefully, their next
reaction is like, and I mean,

00:31:35.110 --> 00:31:36.460 align:middle line:90%
what's so special about him?

00:31:36.460 --> 00:31:39.220 align:middle line:84%
If he could do it,
I must have a shot.

00:31:39.220 --> 00:31:41.590 align:middle line:90%
I must have shot.

00:31:41.590 --> 00:31:43.600 align:middle line:84%
In an ideal world, we
reach a tipping point

00:31:43.600 --> 00:31:46.180 align:middle line:84%
where enough people
are doing it where

00:31:46.180 --> 00:31:49.270 align:middle line:84%
there's a critical
mass, where it becomes

00:31:49.270 --> 00:31:50.620 align:middle line:90%
more of this normal thing.

00:31:50.620 --> 00:31:54.730 align:middle line:90%


00:31:54.730 --> 00:31:59.260 align:middle line:84%
And there is this constant
tug of war between the two

00:31:59.260 --> 00:32:01.210 align:middle line:90%
forces of bliss--

00:32:01.210 --> 00:32:06.570 align:middle line:84%
doing the thing you do out
of love, not fear, and fear,

00:32:06.570 --> 00:32:09.820 align:middle line:84%
doing the thing you do
out of just abject fear,

00:32:09.820 --> 00:32:14.060 align:middle line:84%
fear of being
poor, being shamed.

00:32:14.060 --> 00:32:18.010 align:middle line:84%
But basically, it all boils
down to fear of loss of love,

00:32:18.010 --> 00:32:19.970 align:middle line:90%
fear of, again, that mask.

00:32:19.970 --> 00:32:22.702 align:middle line:84%
You keep the mask
on out of fear.

00:32:22.702 --> 00:32:24.160 align:middle line:84%
And that's where
the problem comes,

00:32:24.160 --> 00:32:28.600 align:middle line:84%
because you're keeping it
on, in my opinion, based

00:32:28.600 --> 00:32:35.350 align:middle line:84%
on a false pretense, which is
that your love is conditional.

00:32:35.350 --> 00:32:38.930 align:middle line:90%
And that's just false.

00:32:38.930 --> 00:32:42.320 align:middle line:84%
>> You're really decoupling
a lot of the activity

00:32:42.320 --> 00:32:43.120 align:middle line:90%
of the world.

00:32:43.120 --> 00:32:45.453 align:middle line:84%
Like you said, it's productive
for people to be fearful,

00:32:45.453 --> 00:32:46.390 align:middle line:90%
in a way.

00:32:46.390 --> 00:32:47.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:32:47.710 --> 00:32:50.320 align:middle line:84%
>> If they're out
there being successful

00:32:50.320 --> 00:32:52.988 align:middle line:84%
because they're trying to make
up for a lack of self-love

00:32:52.988 --> 00:32:55.030 align:middle line:84%
in their own household
when they were growing up,

00:32:55.030 --> 00:32:56.280 align:middle line:90%
that's great for shareholders.

00:32:56.280 --> 00:32:57.910 align:middle line:90%
You know what I mean?

00:32:57.910 --> 00:32:58.840 align:middle line:90%
>> In the short-term.

00:32:58.840 --> 00:32:59.725 align:middle line:90%
>> In the short-term.

00:32:59.725 --> 00:33:02.080 align:middle line:84%
And it's horrible for
that guy's midlife crisis,

00:33:02.080 --> 00:33:03.120 align:middle line:84%
because he's going
to hit this wall

00:33:03.120 --> 00:33:04.480 align:middle line:84%
and go, oh my god,
I'm not loved.

00:33:04.480 --> 00:33:05.080 align:middle line:90%
What's going on?

00:33:05.080 --> 00:33:06.010 align:middle line:90%
Or just break down.

00:33:06.010 --> 00:33:09.023 align:middle line:84%
Or just tough it out long
enough until he dies, right?

00:33:09.023 --> 00:33:10.690 align:middle line:84%
Or until the brain
start shutting down--

00:33:10.690 --> 00:33:14.170 align:middle line:84%
which is dementia, there's
even some studies now showing

00:33:14.170 --> 00:33:16.780 align:middle line:84%
it's just because their body
is just like, I can't handle--

00:33:16.780 --> 00:33:19.750 align:middle line:84%
I can't reconcile this anymore,
this heart-head situation,

00:33:19.750 --> 00:33:22.110 align:middle line:90%
so I'm just going to atrophy.

00:33:22.110 --> 00:33:23.170 align:middle line:90%
Too deep.

00:33:23.170 --> 00:33:24.810 align:middle line:90%
Let's pull it back a second.

00:33:24.810 --> 00:33:28.120 align:middle line:84%
Four types of emotional trauma
that you sort of identified,

00:33:28.120 --> 00:33:30.490 align:middle line:84%
because I like how you
bring an analysis to this.

00:33:30.490 --> 00:33:33.342 align:middle line:84%
You're like, we can chunk
emotional trauma down

00:33:33.342 --> 00:33:34.300 align:middle line:90%
into these four things.

00:33:34.300 --> 00:33:35.160 align:middle line:90%
I'd like to speak to that.

00:33:35.160 --> 00:33:37.540 align:middle line:84%
How do you sort of categorize
these emotional traumas?

00:33:37.540 --> 00:33:40.250 align:middle line:84%
Because I think people will
connect with one of those four.

00:33:40.250 --> 00:33:41.050 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:33:41.050 --> 00:33:50.140 align:middle line:84%
So I think in terms of just a
self-negative inner voice and I

00:33:50.140 --> 00:33:52.690 align:middle line:84%
think less in terms
of trauma per se,

00:33:52.690 --> 00:33:54.970 align:middle line:90%
because to me that's more of a--

00:33:54.970 --> 00:33:56.440 align:middle line:90%
it may be that.

00:33:56.440 --> 00:33:58.330 align:middle line:84%
But that's more of
kind of a medical term.

00:33:58.330 --> 00:34:01.350 align:middle line:90%


00:34:01.350 --> 00:34:03.350 align:middle line:84%
People mean different
things when they say that.

00:34:03.350 --> 00:34:05.200 align:middle line:84%
So for me, there's
this voice that's

00:34:05.200 --> 00:34:08.929 align:middle line:84%
just giving you a hard
time, like, all the time.

00:34:08.929 --> 00:34:12.130 align:middle line:90%


00:34:12.130 --> 00:34:17.969 align:middle line:84%
So it's more of a commonsensical
kind of level of it.

00:34:17.969 --> 00:34:22.989 align:middle line:84%
And for me when I
talk about this,

00:34:22.989 --> 00:34:28.030 align:middle line:84%
when the voice comes at you and
starts doing this blistering,

00:34:28.030 --> 00:34:31.542 align:middle line:84%
multipronged attack, it's
like the splits in chess,

00:34:31.542 --> 00:34:33.250 align:middle line:84%
where it's like the
bishop is hitting you

00:34:33.250 --> 00:34:36.370 align:middle line:84%
and the queen's coming around
behind you, and just everything

00:34:36.370 --> 00:34:39.520 align:middle line:90%
all at once from all directions.

00:34:39.520 --> 00:34:42.489 align:middle line:84%
If you break it down, the
self-negative inner critic

00:34:42.489 --> 00:34:47.000 align:middle line:84%
force will typically come
at you across four channels.

00:34:47.000 --> 00:34:49.780 align:middle line:84%
And the four are
competence, body, identity,

00:34:49.780 --> 00:34:52.380 align:middle line:84%
and relationship is
how I think about them.

00:34:52.380 --> 00:34:58.360 align:middle line:84%
Competence is the idea that you
should be better at something

00:34:58.360 --> 00:35:00.090 align:middle line:90%
than you actually are.

00:35:00.090 --> 00:35:01.840 align:middle line:84%
So it could be your
grades, how much money

00:35:01.840 --> 00:35:08.810 align:middle line:84%
you make, prestige, popularity,
sociability, cooking, skill

00:35:08.810 --> 00:35:09.610 align:middle line:90%
as a lover--

00:35:09.610 --> 00:35:11.170 align:middle line:90%
any of these things.

00:35:11.170 --> 00:35:15.100 align:middle line:84%
But generally, it's something
that has to do with competence.

00:35:15.100 --> 00:35:17.830 align:middle line:90%
You have some power over it.

00:35:17.830 --> 00:35:18.700 align:middle line:90%
It is a skill.

00:35:18.700 --> 00:35:21.250 align:middle line:84%
It is something you can
work on, theoretically.

00:35:21.250 --> 00:35:22.750 align:middle line:90%
So that's the first one.

00:35:22.750 --> 00:35:26.020 align:middle line:84%
The second one is body, which
is this feeling that there's

00:35:26.020 --> 00:35:29.710 align:middle line:84%
something intrinsically wrong
with your body-- that you're

00:35:29.710 --> 00:35:34.390 align:middle line:84%
either too fat or too thin,
too tall or too short,

00:35:34.390 --> 00:35:37.570 align:middle line:84%
the wrong body shape, the wrong
body color, a feature is too

00:35:37.570 --> 00:35:38.740 align:middle line:90%
big, your nose or your ears.

00:35:38.740 --> 00:35:42.232 align:middle line:84%
It could be you're too
hairy or not hairy enough.

00:35:42.232 --> 00:35:43.190 align:middle line:90%
So any of these things.

00:35:43.190 --> 00:35:44.940 align:middle line:84%
But basically, this
idea that there's just

00:35:44.940 --> 00:35:47.320 align:middle line:84%
something wrong with
my body that, again,

00:35:47.320 --> 00:35:50.920 align:middle line:90%
makes me not worthy of love.

00:35:50.920 --> 00:35:53.410 align:middle line:84%
The third is identity,
which is the idea there's

00:35:53.410 --> 00:35:56.380 align:middle line:84%
something intrinsically wrong
with basically something

00:35:56.380 --> 00:35:59.830 align:middle line:84%
about you as a person that
you're basically not going

00:35:59.830 --> 00:36:00.940 align:middle line:90%
to change.

00:36:00.940 --> 00:36:02.330 align:middle line:90%
So it could be your gender.

00:36:02.330 --> 00:36:05.320 align:middle line:90%
It could be your ethnicity.

00:36:05.320 --> 00:36:08.290 align:middle line:84%
It could be your
religious affiliation.

00:36:08.290 --> 00:36:09.970 align:middle line:84%
It could even be
your personality,

00:36:09.970 --> 00:36:12.190 align:middle line:84%
where it's like,
I'm intrinsically

00:36:12.190 --> 00:36:14.890 align:middle line:90%
kind of an introvert.

00:36:14.890 --> 00:36:17.080 align:middle line:84%
But I'm a sales guy
or an executive,

00:36:17.080 --> 00:36:21.810 align:middle line:84%
so I'm expected to play golf
and do all these things.

00:36:21.810 --> 00:36:23.650 align:middle line:84%
So I do them
begrudgingly, but I feel

00:36:23.650 --> 00:36:24.700 align:middle line:84%
like there's something
wrong with me

00:36:24.700 --> 00:36:26.325 align:middle line:84%
because I actually
like sitting at home

00:36:26.325 --> 00:36:27.400 align:middle line:90%
and just reading a book.

00:36:27.400 --> 00:36:30.040 align:middle line:90%


00:36:30.040 --> 00:36:32.470 align:middle line:84%
The fourth is a little
bit in its own category,

00:36:32.470 --> 00:36:35.190 align:middle line:84%
and that's what I
call relationship.

00:36:35.190 --> 00:36:38.470 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
idea that you have

00:36:38.470 --> 00:36:44.770 align:middle line:84%
this core belief in your
mind that I will only

00:36:44.770 --> 00:36:50.130 align:middle line:90%
be worthy of love if blank.

00:36:50.130 --> 00:36:53.920 align:middle line:84%
I will only be lovable and
worthy of love if blank.

00:36:53.920 --> 00:36:56.555 align:middle line:84%
And this blank
conflates beautifully

00:36:56.555 --> 00:36:57.430 align:middle line:90%
with the first three.

00:36:57.430 --> 00:37:00.070 align:middle line:84%
I will only be lovable if I'm
competent-- if I make money,

00:37:00.070 --> 00:37:02.710 align:middle line:84%
if I'm rich, if I'm smart,
if I get good grades, if I

00:37:02.710 --> 00:37:06.340 align:middle line:84%
score a lot of goals on the
athletic field, if I'm popular.

00:37:06.340 --> 00:37:09.100 align:middle line:84%
Or body-- I'll only be
lovable if I'm tall,

00:37:09.100 --> 00:37:12.370 align:middle line:84%
if I'm hot, if I'm skinny, if
I've got a full head of hair--

00:37:12.370 --> 00:37:14.470 align:middle line:90%
all these things, right?

00:37:14.470 --> 00:37:19.270 align:middle line:84%
Identity-- I'll only be lovable
if I'm not the gender I am,

00:37:19.270 --> 00:37:22.040 align:middle line:84%
because boys are more
valuable than girls.

00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:24.790 align:middle line:84%
Siblings talk about
this all the time.

00:37:24.790 --> 00:37:26.950 align:middle line:84%
If I'm a different
ethnicity, if I'm

00:37:26.950 --> 00:37:30.620 align:middle line:84%
a different religion, if I'm
a different personality type.

00:37:30.620 --> 00:37:33.580 align:middle line:84%
And so the poison
of this last one--

00:37:33.580 --> 00:37:37.330 align:middle line:84%
I will only be
lovable if black--

00:37:37.330 --> 00:37:39.970 align:middle line:84%
is not from what you
put in the blank.

00:37:39.970 --> 00:37:41.650 align:middle line:90%
That's irrelevant.

00:37:41.650 --> 00:37:45.000 align:middle line:84%
So for instance,
even if I said, I

00:37:45.000 --> 00:37:48.840 align:middle line:84%
will only be lovable if I
find the cure for cancer,

00:37:48.840 --> 00:37:53.658 align:middle line:84%
solve global warming, and save
7 billion people on the planet--

00:37:53.658 --> 00:37:55.950 align:middle line:84%
even if that's what's in the
blank-- because it's like,

00:37:55.950 --> 00:37:57.060 align:middle line:90%
who wouldn't want that?

00:37:57.060 --> 00:37:57.860 align:middle line:90%
Please.

00:37:57.860 --> 00:37:58.690 align:middle line:90%
Please do that.

00:37:58.690 --> 00:37:59.490 align:middle line:90%
Whip you.

00:37:59.490 --> 00:38:01.110 align:middle line:90%
Whip you harder.

00:38:01.110 --> 00:38:03.900 align:middle line:84%
Even that's poison,
because the poison is not

00:38:03.900 --> 00:38:05.730 align:middle line:90%
what you put in the blank.

00:38:05.730 --> 00:38:09.085 align:middle line:90%
The poison is in the "if."

00:38:09.085 --> 00:38:14.100 align:middle line:84%
The "if" is what implies that
before you've done anything--

00:38:14.100 --> 00:38:17.160 align:middle line:84%
competence, identity,
anything-- that you as you

00:38:17.160 --> 00:38:19.833 align:middle line:84%
are, before we've
turned over any cards

00:38:19.833 --> 00:38:21.750 align:middle line:84%
to figure out what you're
actually going to do

00:38:21.750 --> 00:38:24.030 align:middle line:84%
or even what you
want to do, that you

00:38:24.030 --> 00:38:28.440 align:middle line:84%
as you are with no additional
bells and whistles, you

00:38:28.440 --> 00:38:32.760 align:middle line:84%
as you are are intrinsically
unworthy of love.

00:38:32.760 --> 00:38:34.060 align:middle line:90%
And that's bullshit.

00:38:34.060 --> 00:38:34.860 align:middle line:90%
That's not true.

00:38:34.860 --> 00:38:38.670 align:middle line:90%


00:38:38.670 --> 00:38:43.200 align:middle line:84%
The trick is when,
as a parent yourself,

00:38:43.200 --> 00:38:45.930 align:middle line:84%
you know this is
true when you hold

00:38:45.930 --> 00:38:50.910 align:middle line:84%
your baby on the day he is born
and you realize, oh my gosh.

00:38:50.910 --> 00:38:53.880 align:middle line:84%
I would give my life for
this slimy little peanut

00:38:53.880 --> 00:38:55.860 align:middle line:90%
that just pooped on me.

00:38:55.860 --> 00:38:59.310 align:middle line:84%
I would do anything
for this little peanut.

00:38:59.310 --> 00:39:02.580 align:middle line:90%
And there is no conditionality.

00:39:02.580 --> 00:39:05.970 align:middle line:84%
You don't know anything
about this little guy.

00:39:05.970 --> 00:39:08.667 align:middle line:84%
And no father or
parent, hopefully,

00:39:08.667 --> 00:39:10.500 align:middle line:84%
says, well, I don't
know if I like this guy.

00:39:10.500 --> 00:39:13.740 align:middle line:84%
Let's see if he gets into
Harvard, and then we'll see.

00:39:13.740 --> 00:39:15.840 align:middle line:90%
Nobody says that, hopefully.

00:39:15.840 --> 00:39:17.740 align:middle line:84%
But if they do,
you know one thing.

00:39:17.740 --> 00:39:19.600 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing wrong
with the kid, right?

00:39:19.600 --> 00:39:21.058 align:middle line:84%
There's a deep
wound in the parent.

00:39:21.058 --> 00:39:23.670 align:middle line:90%


00:39:23.670 --> 00:39:27.420 align:middle line:84%
And so the only reason that
changes as the kid grows up

00:39:27.420 --> 00:39:30.600 align:middle line:84%
is because we have to get
them to put on a mask.

00:39:30.600 --> 00:39:32.430 align:middle line:84%
And then the colossal
misunderstanding

00:39:32.430 --> 00:39:36.270 align:middle line:84%
of, no, no, no, no, no, your
love is not conditional.

00:39:36.270 --> 00:39:38.160 align:middle line:84%
You've got to put on--
we all wear a mask.

00:39:38.160 --> 00:39:39.510 align:middle line:90%
Look at stupid Uncle Bob.

00:39:39.510 --> 00:39:40.590 align:middle line:90%
He wears his mask too.

00:39:40.590 --> 00:39:41.880 align:middle line:90%
Not very well, but.

00:39:41.880 --> 00:39:43.680 align:middle line:90%
You know, all these things.

00:39:43.680 --> 00:39:47.640 align:middle line:84%
But love is not on
the table, right?

00:39:47.640 --> 00:39:50.440 align:middle line:90%
You don't earn your love.

00:39:50.440 --> 00:39:54.490 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing additional you
need to do to earn your love.

00:39:54.490 --> 00:40:02.970 align:middle line:84%
And so what then
happens is that we all--

00:40:02.970 --> 00:40:05.820 align:middle line:84%
so typically when
I give this talk,

00:40:05.820 --> 00:40:07.980 align:middle line:90%
after I describe the four--

00:40:07.980 --> 00:40:10.860 align:middle line:84%
competence, body, identity,
and relationship--

00:40:10.860 --> 00:40:14.327 align:middle line:84%
I see in the audience the blood
draining from everyone's faces,

00:40:14.327 --> 00:40:16.410 align:middle line:84%
because they're thinking,
oh my gosh, I'm screwed.

00:40:16.410 --> 00:40:18.270 align:middle line:90%
I have all four.

00:40:18.270 --> 00:40:21.030 align:middle line:84%
And at that point I always
remember to say, OK, hang on.

00:40:21.030 --> 00:40:23.370 align:middle line:90%
Everyone has all four.

00:40:23.370 --> 00:40:26.760 align:middle line:84%
Everyone has all four, so
there's nothing wrong with you.

00:40:26.760 --> 00:40:30.720 align:middle line:84%
And the trick is that
the four elements

00:40:30.720 --> 00:40:35.680 align:middle line:84%
are blended into a unique
smoothie for each person.

00:40:35.680 --> 00:40:38.850 align:middle line:84%
So we all have all
four, but the mix

00:40:38.850 --> 00:40:43.200 align:middle line:84%
of competence, body, identity,
and relationship is different,

00:40:43.200 --> 00:40:46.790 align:middle line:84%
and the flavor of
each one is different.

00:40:46.790 --> 00:40:49.405 align:middle line:90%
So your competence wound--

00:40:49.405 --> 00:40:51.030 align:middle line:84%
so first of all, as
men, typically it's

00:40:51.030 --> 00:40:54.030 align:middle line:84%
like 80% competence and
everything else is fine.

00:40:54.030 --> 00:40:56.550 align:middle line:90%


00:40:56.550 --> 00:41:01.740 align:middle line:84%
But your flavor of competence
may be artistic achievement.

00:41:01.740 --> 00:41:03.810 align:middle line:84%
Or somebody else's
flavor competence

00:41:03.810 --> 00:41:05.490 align:middle line:90%
may be just brute force money.

00:41:05.490 --> 00:41:08.070 align:middle line:90%


00:41:08.070 --> 00:41:10.620 align:middle line:84%
That's just the topography
of different people's sort

00:41:10.620 --> 00:41:12.930 align:middle line:90%
of makeup.

00:41:12.930 --> 00:41:15.930 align:middle line:84%
But what will happen is
that each person will

00:41:15.930 --> 00:41:21.132 align:middle line:84%
have the same four components,
but the proportions

00:41:21.132 --> 00:41:23.340 align:middle line:84%
will be different, and the
flavors will be different.

00:41:23.340 --> 00:41:26.700 align:middle line:84%
So when I sip my smoothie
and I look at everyone else's

00:41:26.700 --> 00:41:31.560 align:middle line:84%
smoothie, I feel like
I'm the only dumb bunny

00:41:31.560 --> 00:41:35.250 align:middle line:84%
idiot in the room with this
particular inner voice.

00:41:35.250 --> 00:41:38.670 align:middle line:84%
I'm the only one, which
makes me feel even more

00:41:38.670 --> 00:41:40.017 align:middle line:90%
stupid, because nobody--

00:41:40.017 --> 00:41:41.100 align:middle line:90%
I mean, look at Instagram.

00:41:41.100 --> 00:41:43.200 align:middle line:84%
Everyone's having a
great time, right?

00:41:43.200 --> 00:41:48.330 align:middle line:84%
I'm the only dumb bunny
who didn't get the memo,

00:41:48.330 --> 00:41:51.690 align:middle line:84%
and I'm the only one
who says this to myself.

00:41:51.690 --> 00:41:54.210 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is, in
a manner of speaking

00:41:54.210 --> 00:42:00.160 align:middle line:84%
that's true, because each
person's fingerprint is unique.

00:42:00.160 --> 00:42:03.510 align:middle line:84%
But what that
doesn't account for

00:42:03.510 --> 00:42:05.760 align:middle line:84%
is the fact that actually,
everyone has a fingerprint.

00:42:05.760 --> 00:42:08.610 align:middle line:90%
Everyone does have a smoothie.

00:42:08.610 --> 00:42:10.860 align:middle line:84%
My smoothie doesn't look
like yours, so I don't stress

00:42:10.860 --> 00:42:12.318 align:middle line:84%
and obsess about
the things you do.

00:42:12.318 --> 00:42:13.950 align:middle line:84%
I stress about other
stuff that I then

00:42:13.950 --> 00:42:17.610 align:middle line:84%
hide, because I have to
put it behind my mask.

00:42:17.610 --> 00:42:22.080 align:middle line:84%
And so one of the
things I didn't realize

00:42:22.080 --> 00:42:24.720 align:middle line:84%
what happened that's been a
wonderful sort of byproduct

00:42:24.720 --> 00:42:29.400 align:middle line:84%
is that even when people just
hear about the four wounds,

00:42:29.400 --> 00:42:32.640 align:middle line:84%
they breathe this
huge sigh of relief.

00:42:32.640 --> 00:42:34.440 align:middle line:84%
Because it's like
saying, yes, yes, yes,

00:42:34.440 --> 00:42:37.810 align:middle line:84%
your elbow does hurt
in its own unique way.

00:42:37.810 --> 00:42:42.628 align:middle line:90%
But everyone has an elbow.

00:42:42.628 --> 00:42:43.920 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing wrong with you.

00:42:43.920 --> 00:42:45.680 align:middle line:90%
We'll just get it looked at.

00:42:45.680 --> 00:42:48.990 align:middle line:84%
We'll attend to
it, and it's fine.

00:42:48.990 --> 00:42:51.510 align:middle line:84%
And people sort of breathe
this sigh of relief where they

00:42:51.510 --> 00:42:53.910 align:middle line:84%
realize, even though
my thing feels unique--

00:42:53.910 --> 00:42:57.020 align:middle line:90%
and at a certain level it is--

00:42:57.020 --> 00:43:00.690 align:middle line:84%
the phenomenon is
common to everyone.

00:43:00.690 --> 00:43:03.930 align:middle line:84%
So that instead of feeling
alienated and angry

00:43:03.930 --> 00:43:06.810 align:middle line:84%
and potentially acting out from
that, with this perspective

00:43:06.810 --> 00:43:09.690 align:middle line:84%
you're like, first of
all, there's a reason

00:43:09.690 --> 00:43:10.900 align:middle line:90%
you feel like that.

00:43:10.900 --> 00:43:12.960 align:middle line:84%
And the reason is actually
related to the fact

00:43:12.960 --> 00:43:13.877 align:middle line:90%
that we all have that.

00:43:13.877 --> 00:43:17.310 align:middle line:84%
So we bring you back in
with this perspective

00:43:17.310 --> 00:43:21.210 align:middle line:84%
that makes you feel truthfully
that what you're feeling,

00:43:21.210 --> 00:43:24.360 align:middle line:84%
however painful it
is, is what you share

00:43:24.360 --> 00:43:28.670 align:middle line:84%
with the collective sort of mass
of everyone else in humanity,

00:43:28.670 --> 00:43:32.660 align:middle line:84%
where you get back to this
feeling of like, yeah,

00:43:32.660 --> 00:43:34.240 align:middle line:90%
yeah, that's cool.

00:43:34.240 --> 00:43:35.040 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it's awful.

00:43:35.040 --> 00:43:35.840 align:middle line:90%
It's painful.

00:43:35.840 --> 00:43:37.660 align:middle line:84%
But it's like, it's
totally normal.

00:43:37.660 --> 00:43:38.460 align:middle line:90%
It's OK.

00:43:38.460 --> 00:43:40.280 align:middle line:90%
Everyone's got it.

00:43:40.280 --> 00:43:42.640 align:middle line:90%
It won't seem like it.

00:43:42.640 --> 00:43:44.640 align:middle line:90%
It will seem like you're alone.

00:43:44.640 --> 00:43:46.850 align:middle line:90%
And that's normal too.

00:43:46.850 --> 00:43:50.223 align:middle line:84%
So tell me more about
what's going on.

00:43:50.223 --> 00:43:51.390 align:middle line:90%
Let's just get it looked at.

00:43:51.390 --> 00:43:53.980 align:middle line:90%


00:43:53.980 --> 00:43:56.050 align:middle line:84%
>> It is interesting to
come to that realization.

00:43:56.050 --> 00:43:59.440 align:middle line:84%
And I think for a lot of people,
starting to identify that they

00:43:59.440 --> 00:44:02.950 align:middle line:84%
may have, let's say, this
idea of an emotional wound--

00:44:02.950 --> 00:44:06.460 align:middle line:84%
or really, what it is that
you speak to is a lack

00:44:06.460 --> 00:44:09.070 align:middle line:84%
of self-worth at some level,
like a negative self-voice

00:44:09.070 --> 00:44:12.565 align:middle line:84%
or a lack of self-worth, or I'll
only be loved when, et cetera--

00:44:12.565 --> 00:44:14.650 align:middle line:84%
which I think a lot of
people can relate to.

00:44:14.650 --> 00:44:18.670 align:middle line:84%
However, they might only
realize after something happens,

00:44:18.670 --> 00:44:21.670 align:middle line:84%
like a trauma or a mid-life or
something that wakes them up--

00:44:21.670 --> 00:44:23.740 align:middle line:84%
or they have something
transformative happen,

00:44:23.740 --> 00:44:24.700 align:middle line:90%
like a child comes in.

00:44:24.700 --> 00:44:26.117 align:middle line:84%
They're like, why
am I doing this?

00:44:26.117 --> 00:44:27.010 align:middle line:90%
Why am I doing this?

00:44:27.010 --> 00:44:28.670 align:middle line:90%
What's going on?

00:44:28.670 --> 00:44:33.880 align:middle line:84%
And when you identify and talk
to these ideas of shielding

00:44:33.880 --> 00:44:35.830 align:middle line:84%
and soothing, I think
that's where people

00:44:35.830 --> 00:44:38.630 align:middle line:84%
can start to put themselves
into the picture of like,

00:44:38.630 --> 00:44:39.430 align:middle line:90%
no, I'm fine.

00:44:39.430 --> 00:44:39.920 align:middle line:90%
I'm fine.

00:44:39.920 --> 00:44:41.470 align:middle line:84%
And then you explain
the shielding technique.

00:44:41.470 --> 00:44:43.950 align:middle line:84%
You're like, well, why am I
trying to be so successful?

00:44:43.950 --> 00:44:46.300 align:middle line:84%
Oh, to get my father's love,
because he's an accountant

00:44:46.300 --> 00:44:48.717 align:middle line:84%
and it's only if you've got a
big bank balance that you're

00:44:48.717 --> 00:44:49.870 align:middle line:90%
truly loved.

00:44:49.870 --> 00:44:52.330 align:middle line:84%
And so you start
to become aware,

00:44:52.330 --> 00:44:55.090 align:middle line:84%
I think, through these concepts
of shielding and soothing

00:44:55.090 --> 00:44:57.480 align:middle line:84%
that you talk to, because
it's like, well, I

00:44:57.480 --> 00:44:59.230 align:middle line:84%
drink a lot when I've
got emotional issues

00:44:59.230 --> 00:45:00.313 align:middle line:90%
with my significant other.

00:45:00.313 --> 00:45:02.520 align:middle line:84%
Well, maybe I've got
relationship issues to myself

00:45:02.520 --> 00:45:03.580 align:middle line:90%
or my parents did that.

00:45:03.580 --> 00:45:06.470 align:middle line:84%
So these ideas of
shielding and soothing,

00:45:06.470 --> 00:45:10.240 align:middle line:84%
can you explain them out a
little bit in that it might

00:45:10.240 --> 00:45:12.970 align:middle line:84%
help people connect with what
their core wound might be,

00:45:12.970 --> 00:45:15.280 align:middle line:84%
or the specific flavor
of their smoothie?

00:45:15.280 --> 00:45:16.930 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:45:16.930 --> 00:45:19.380 align:middle line:84%
So when you have one
of these smoothies,

00:45:19.380 --> 00:45:21.880 align:middle line:84%
you're sipping it all day long
whether you like to or not.

00:45:21.880 --> 00:45:23.770 align:middle line:90%
I mean, the voice is in you.

00:45:23.770 --> 00:45:26.800 align:middle line:84%
You see somebody
drive a nice car by

00:45:26.800 --> 00:45:30.940 align:middle line:84%
and you're like, oh my
gosh, I feel like an idiot.

00:45:30.940 --> 00:45:33.490 align:middle line:84%
Or you're a mom taking
your kids to school,

00:45:33.490 --> 00:45:37.870 align:middle line:84%
and this other mom brings her
kids and her daughter's hair,

00:45:37.870 --> 00:45:41.380 align:middle line:84%
the hair for her daughters are
all brushed and perfectly fine.

00:45:41.380 --> 00:45:43.540 align:middle line:84%
And you feel like
your daughter's hair

00:45:43.540 --> 00:45:46.240 align:middle line:84%
is like a rat's nest,
and the inner voice just

00:45:46.240 --> 00:45:48.250 align:middle line:90%
starts to eat you alive.

00:45:48.250 --> 00:45:57.580 align:middle line:84%
And so when you have
this smoothie, it hurts.

00:45:57.580 --> 00:46:00.240 align:middle line:84%
When you say these things
to yourself constantly

00:46:00.240 --> 00:46:03.040 align:middle line:84%
with the upshot,
the sort of so-what,

00:46:03.040 --> 00:46:05.020 align:middle line:84%
being, and you're
not worthy of love.

00:46:05.020 --> 00:46:06.490 align:middle line:90%
You're less lovable.

00:46:06.490 --> 00:46:07.340 align:middle line:90%
It hurts.

00:46:07.340 --> 00:46:10.590 align:middle line:84%
And because it
hurts, it's a wound.

00:46:10.590 --> 00:46:13.360 align:middle line:84%
And so for me, when
you have a wound,

00:46:13.360 --> 00:46:16.180 align:middle line:84%
there's two very
natural things you do.

00:46:16.180 --> 00:46:21.080 align:middle line:84%
If I'm a, you know, like
Roman gladiator in the arena,

00:46:21.080 --> 00:46:24.820 align:middle line:84%
and we're fighting and
you cut my chest a little,

00:46:24.820 --> 00:46:26.930 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do two things.

00:46:26.930 --> 00:46:29.740 align:middle line:84%
The first thing I'm going to
do is I'm going to shield.

00:46:29.740 --> 00:46:32.200 align:middle line:90%
Don't hit me again.

00:46:32.200 --> 00:46:33.880 align:middle line:90%
It's perfectly reasonable.

00:46:33.880 --> 00:46:36.010 align:middle line:84%
If you didn't do
that, I would worry.

00:46:36.010 --> 00:46:37.990 align:middle line:90%
So I expect you to shield.

00:46:37.990 --> 00:46:41.200 align:middle line:84%
And the other thing is that
behind the safety of my shield,

00:46:41.200 --> 00:46:45.880 align:middle line:84%
I will try to grab lidocaine
or something, some spray

00:46:45.880 --> 00:46:50.410 align:middle line:84%
or whatever, to make the
pain less so I will soothe.

00:46:50.410 --> 00:46:52.720 align:middle line:84%
And that's perfectly
reasonable too.

00:46:52.720 --> 00:46:54.280 align:middle line:84%
It's not just
humans that do this.

00:46:54.280 --> 00:46:55.340 align:middle line:90%
Earthworms do this.

00:46:55.340 --> 00:46:56.140 align:middle line:90%
Chickens do it.

00:46:56.140 --> 00:46:59.910 align:middle line:84%
If I poke an earthworm, it will
start to move away from me.

00:46:59.910 --> 00:47:01.600 align:middle line:84%
So there's nothing
wrong with a person

00:47:01.600 --> 00:47:04.840 align:middle line:84%
when they soothe or
shield, just like there's

00:47:04.840 --> 00:47:07.530 align:middle line:84%
nothing wrong with a person
when they have this four

00:47:07.530 --> 00:47:10.810 align:middle line:84%
wound, because they were
told to put on a mask.

00:47:10.810 --> 00:47:12.310 align:middle line:84%
And there's nothing
wrong with that.

00:47:12.310 --> 00:47:13.935 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing wrong
with any of this.

00:47:13.935 --> 00:47:16.630 align:middle line:84%
It's just when it
happens in a certain way,

00:47:16.630 --> 00:47:19.960 align:middle line:84%
it causes more pain
than it requires.

00:47:19.960 --> 00:47:24.550 align:middle line:84%
So if you saw a person
soothe and shield,

00:47:24.550 --> 00:47:27.850 align:middle line:84%
my reaction is like
perfectly normal.

00:47:27.850 --> 00:47:31.510 align:middle line:84%
Nothing wrong with I'm
not doing anything wrong.

00:47:31.510 --> 00:47:34.300 align:middle line:84%
If you zoom in on
shielding, there

00:47:34.300 --> 00:47:36.940 align:middle line:90%
are a couple of usual suspects.

00:47:36.940 --> 00:47:39.400 align:middle line:90%
The first is money and prestige.

00:47:39.400 --> 00:47:43.272 align:middle line:84%
You can't argue with
success, especially here

00:47:43.272 --> 00:47:44.480 align:middle line:90%
in the Silicon Valley, right?

00:47:44.480 --> 00:47:48.010 align:middle line:84%
If I IPO'ed my company
for half a billion dollars

00:47:48.010 --> 00:47:53.800 align:middle line:84%
and now I've got a checkbook
funding all these nonprofits,

00:47:53.800 --> 00:47:55.480 align:middle line:84%
no one is going
to poke my wound.

00:47:55.480 --> 00:47:58.020 align:middle line:90%


00:47:58.020 --> 00:48:02.120 align:middle line:84%
It's this auto drone
century mode shield,

00:48:02.120 --> 00:48:04.090 align:middle line:84%
and no one is going to
poke my wound, as long

00:48:04.090 --> 00:48:06.880 align:middle line:84%
as I know everyone in
the room knows who I am

00:48:06.880 --> 00:48:09.610 align:middle line:84%
and what I've done-- which
is why people with prestige

00:48:09.610 --> 00:48:12.850 align:middle line:84%
and money will often
make sure you know that,

00:48:12.850 --> 00:48:15.560 align:middle line:84%
because they're just making
sure that the shield is up.

00:48:15.560 --> 00:48:16.810 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:48:16.810 --> 00:48:18.820 align:middle line:84%
And by the way, there's
nothing wrong with this.

00:48:18.820 --> 00:48:20.980 align:middle line:90%
So money and prestige is one.

00:48:20.980 --> 00:48:26.710 align:middle line:84%
Perfectionism is another, where
if I'm perfect in every way--

00:48:26.710 --> 00:48:32.800 align:middle line:84%
perfect body, perfect spouse,
perfect house, perfect kids,

00:48:32.800 --> 00:48:35.870 align:middle line:84%
put together in
exactly the right way,

00:48:35.870 --> 00:48:39.490 align:middle line:84%
doing all the right activities,
the right kind of job,

00:48:39.490 --> 00:48:43.420 align:middle line:84%
the right kind of volunteer,
kids doing the right thing

00:48:43.420 --> 00:48:44.245 align:middle line:90%
everything--

00:48:44.245 --> 00:48:46.990 align:middle line:90%


00:48:46.990 --> 00:48:50.620 align:middle line:84%
then that is hopefully
an impenetrable shield

00:48:50.620 --> 00:48:53.737 align:middle line:84%
where no arrow criticism
can get through.

00:48:53.737 --> 00:48:55.570 align:middle line:84%
And the issue, of course,
with perfectionism

00:48:55.570 --> 00:48:59.430 align:middle line:84%
is that it's exhausting,
and it's impossible.

00:48:59.430 --> 00:49:01.420 align:middle line:90%
Third on the list is anger.

00:49:01.420 --> 00:49:04.480 align:middle line:84%
So if I'm angry all
the time and I've

00:49:04.480 --> 00:49:07.990 align:middle line:84%
got a scowl and people
know to walk on eggshells,

00:49:07.990 --> 00:49:11.170 align:middle line:84%
that keeps everyone
at a distance.

00:49:11.170 --> 00:49:12.670 align:middle line:84%
And that's functionally
what I want,

00:49:12.670 --> 00:49:15.160 align:middle line:84%
because if you do come
in to swing at me,

00:49:15.160 --> 00:49:17.180 align:middle line:90%
I'm already out of range.

00:49:17.180 --> 00:49:18.980 align:middle line:90%
So that's also very effective.

00:49:18.980 --> 00:49:22.767 align:middle line:84%
But again, the cost is that
estranges my relationships

00:49:22.767 --> 00:49:24.100 align:middle line:90%
and I have no warmth in my life.

00:49:24.100 --> 00:49:26.680 align:middle line:90%


00:49:26.680 --> 00:49:33.060 align:middle line:84%
The last two are invisibility
and people-pleasing.

00:49:33.060 --> 00:49:37.330 align:middle line:84%
So invisibility as a shield is,
if I keep my head down, dress

00:49:37.330 --> 00:49:40.960 align:middle line:84%
very plainly, don't raise
my hand, speak up in class,

00:49:40.960 --> 00:49:42.850 align:middle line:84%
don't speak up in
business meetings,

00:49:42.850 --> 00:49:47.260 align:middle line:84%
maybe the bullies will not
notice me and not pull me out

00:49:47.260 --> 00:49:49.450 align:middle line:84%
to shame me or ridicule
me in some way.

00:49:49.450 --> 00:49:52.390 align:middle line:90%


00:49:52.390 --> 00:49:57.160 align:middle line:84%
And the shield of
people-pleasing is that

00:49:57.160 --> 00:49:59.470 align:middle line:90%
if everyone around me is happy--

00:49:59.470 --> 00:50:02.800 align:middle line:84%
and more importantly,
happy with me--

00:50:02.800 --> 00:50:06.922 align:middle line:84%
then perhaps the bullies
will give me a pass today.

00:50:06.922 --> 00:50:08.380 align:middle line:84%
And the problem
with these last two

00:50:08.380 --> 00:50:10.522 align:middle line:84%
is that they're
not actual shields.

00:50:10.522 --> 00:50:11.980 align:middle line:84%
They don't actually
block anything.

00:50:11.980 --> 00:50:13.772 align:middle line:84%
Invisibility, you're
not blocking anything.

00:50:13.772 --> 00:50:16.660 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately,
you're not an iguana.

00:50:16.660 --> 00:50:20.170 align:middle line:90%
So I can see you.

00:50:20.170 --> 00:50:22.660 align:middle line:84%
But you're trying to
sort of evade attention.

00:50:22.660 --> 00:50:24.160 align:middle line:84%
And the problem
with people-pleasing

00:50:24.160 --> 00:50:26.000 align:middle line:84%
is that it's not
a shield either.

00:50:26.000 --> 00:50:26.800 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't block.

00:50:26.800 --> 00:50:28.210 align:middle line:90%
It's appeasement.

00:50:28.210 --> 00:50:31.095 align:middle line:84%
So in the classroom,
it's the class clown.

00:50:31.095 --> 00:50:32.470 align:middle line:84%
And in real life,
it's the parent

00:50:32.470 --> 00:50:36.200 align:middle line:84%
that is like serving everybody
in the upper generation,

00:50:36.200 --> 00:50:39.190 align:middle line:84%
the in-laws, everyone
in the lower generation,

00:50:39.190 --> 00:50:41.440 align:middle line:84%
serving spouse,
serving the workplace,

00:50:41.440 --> 00:50:44.813 align:middle line:84%
and there's like
nothing left for me.

00:50:44.813 --> 00:50:47.230 align:middle line:84%
And you do this because you
feel like you have to do this,

00:50:47.230 --> 00:50:49.840 align:middle line:84%
or else you will lose love
and not be worthy of love.

00:50:49.840 --> 00:50:52.092 align:middle line:84%
So you'll give
anything for that.

00:50:52.092 --> 00:50:53.800 align:middle line:84%
But again, for me
that's a false premise.

00:50:53.800 --> 00:50:56.290 align:middle line:84%
And when you realize that,
everything around you

00:50:56.290 --> 00:50:58.480 align:middle line:84%
starts to realign,
because you're like,

00:50:58.480 --> 00:51:00.320 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to lose love.

00:51:00.320 --> 00:51:07.280 align:middle line:84%
So if I know that, how does
that change my behavior?

00:51:07.280 --> 00:51:11.150 align:middle line:84%
But of course, the issue is when
you start taking off the mask,

00:51:11.150 --> 00:51:14.240 align:middle line:84%
all of reality starts to
move with it, your then

00:51:14.240 --> 00:51:15.040 align:middle line:90%
current reality.

00:51:15.040 --> 00:51:17.650 align:middle line:90%


00:51:17.650 --> 00:51:19.720 align:middle line:90%
So that's shielding.

00:51:19.720 --> 00:51:21.910 align:middle line:90%
It's just a menu of options.

00:51:21.910 --> 00:51:23.813 align:middle line:84%
Everyone comes up
with their own mix.

00:51:23.813 --> 00:51:25.480 align:middle line:84%
They use different
things in different--

00:51:25.480 --> 00:51:27.370 align:middle line:84%
and there's nothing
wrong with them.

00:51:27.370 --> 00:51:30.340 align:middle line:90%


00:51:30.340 --> 00:51:32.320 align:middle line:84%
If you have a wound--
and we all do--

00:51:32.320 --> 00:51:35.298 align:middle line:90%
you will shield.

00:51:35.298 --> 00:51:37.090 align:middle line:84%
So what I teach is not
an exercise in like,

00:51:37.090 --> 00:51:38.560 align:middle line:84%
how do we get you
to shield less?

00:51:38.560 --> 00:51:39.760 align:middle line:90%
It's like, no, no, no.

00:51:39.760 --> 00:51:40.660 align:middle line:90%
Keep that thing up.

00:51:40.660 --> 00:51:42.310 align:middle line:90%
I don't want you to get hit.

00:51:42.310 --> 00:51:46.990 align:middle line:84%
But it's more a question
of just making sure you're

00:51:46.990 --> 00:51:50.020 align:middle line:90%
getting value for money, right?

00:51:50.020 --> 00:51:52.390 align:middle line:84%
I'm laying out all
this blood and treasure

00:51:52.390 --> 00:51:53.730 align:middle line:90%
to keep the shield up.

00:51:53.730 --> 00:51:54.730 align:middle line:90%
I want it to work.

00:51:54.730 --> 00:51:57.640 align:middle line:90%


00:51:57.640 --> 00:52:02.198 align:middle line:84%
Because you paid all this effort
and blood, sweat, and tears

00:52:02.198 --> 00:52:03.490 align:middle line:90%
for the shield, it better work.

00:52:03.490 --> 00:52:05.440 align:middle line:84%
And if it's not, switch
it up and come up

00:52:05.440 --> 00:52:06.840 align:middle line:90%
with a different one.

00:52:06.840 --> 00:52:09.880 align:middle line:90%
And soothing is similar.

00:52:09.880 --> 00:52:13.390 align:middle line:84%
The usual suspects are
alcohol and substances,

00:52:13.390 --> 00:52:16.360 align:middle line:84%
just the chemical brute force
of hitting the voice to shut it

00:52:16.360 --> 00:52:18.700 align:middle line:90%
up, making this painless.

00:52:18.700 --> 00:52:21.340 align:middle line:90%


00:52:21.340 --> 00:52:22.940 align:middle line:90%
It's sex and relationships.

00:52:22.940 --> 00:52:27.770 align:middle line:84%
So sex as like the physical act,
just the narcotic act of sex.

00:52:27.770 --> 00:52:29.740 align:middle line:84%
But also relationships,
which is like the surge

00:52:29.740 --> 00:52:32.380 align:middle line:84%
of emotional validation you
get the first two or three

00:52:32.380 --> 00:52:34.490 align:middle line:90%
weeks in any relationship.

00:52:34.490 --> 00:52:37.300 align:middle line:84%
Then after that, you kind of
see each other more clearly

00:52:37.300 --> 00:52:40.072 align:middle line:84%
and you say, ah,
and you run away.

00:52:40.072 --> 00:52:41.530 align:middle line:84%
So jumping from
thing to thing just

00:52:41.530 --> 00:52:45.070 align:middle line:84%
to get that, just to kind
of skim the top frosting

00:52:45.070 --> 00:52:48.170 align:middle line:84%
on the cupcake off and
then kind of move on

00:52:48.170 --> 00:52:49.865 align:middle line:90%
is a form of soothing.

00:52:49.865 --> 00:52:50.740 align:middle line:90%
And it's very common.

00:52:50.740 --> 00:52:53.860 align:middle line:90%
People do it all the time.

00:52:53.860 --> 00:52:55.612 align:middle line:84%
And I know it causes
pain, and people

00:52:55.612 --> 00:52:57.820 align:middle line:84%
don't want to get trapped
in these repetitive cycles.

00:52:57.820 --> 00:52:58.620 align:middle line:90%
And I get that.

00:52:58.620 --> 00:53:00.820 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time
I'm like, you're

00:53:00.820 --> 00:53:05.770 align:middle line:84%
not doing it because
you're an idiot.

00:53:05.770 --> 00:53:07.240 align:middle line:84%
There's a reason
you're doing it.

00:53:07.240 --> 00:53:09.700 align:middle line:84%
It's a very reasonable
reason why you're doing it.

00:53:09.700 --> 00:53:11.290 align:middle line:84%
And once you know
that, then it's

00:53:11.290 --> 00:53:14.770 align:middle line:84%
like, OK, well, how do I want
to rearrange things so that I'm

00:53:14.770 --> 00:53:17.740 align:middle line:90%
paying less for my pain relief?

00:53:17.740 --> 00:53:20.800 align:middle line:90%


00:53:20.800 --> 00:53:23.350 align:middle line:90%
And then others, the soothing--

00:53:23.350 --> 00:53:28.520 align:middle line:84%
just sort of texting, gaming,
shopping, gossiping, Netflix--

00:53:28.520 --> 00:53:31.120 align:middle line:90%


00:53:31.120 --> 00:53:33.010 align:middle line:90%
in a good way.

00:53:33.010 --> 00:53:37.630 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is, for
me then, the question--

00:53:37.630 --> 00:53:39.870 align:middle line:90%
exactly the same as shielding--

00:53:39.870 --> 00:53:43.450 align:middle line:84%
is not, how do we get
you to not soothe.

00:53:43.450 --> 00:53:47.710 align:middle line:84%
Even an earthworm is going
to soothe when you poke it.

00:53:47.710 --> 00:53:50.170 align:middle line:84%
So it's not unreasonable
for you to soothe.

00:53:50.170 --> 00:53:53.590 align:middle line:84%
Again, for me it's just a
question of value for money,

00:53:53.590 --> 00:53:56.500 align:middle line:90%
or value for your outlay--

00:53:56.500 --> 00:54:00.280 align:middle line:84%
which is, am I getting
the pain relief

00:54:00.280 --> 00:54:03.350 align:middle line:84%
I need at the lowest
possible cost?

00:54:03.350 --> 00:54:06.172 align:middle line:84%
So when I give talks at
schools and high schools

00:54:06.172 --> 00:54:07.630 align:middle line:84%
and I start talking
about soothing,

00:54:07.630 --> 00:54:09.088 align:middle line:84%
everyone starts to
roll their eyes.

00:54:09.088 --> 00:54:12.490 align:middle line:84%
It's like, ah, this was really
interesting until he turned out

00:54:12.490 --> 00:54:16.150 align:middle line:84%
to be the guy that's just going
to say don't do drugs, right?

00:54:16.150 --> 00:54:17.920 align:middle line:84%
And I say, no, no,
that's not my message.

00:54:17.920 --> 00:54:19.780 align:middle line:84%
I mean, yeah, please
don't do drugs.

00:54:19.780 --> 00:54:21.250 align:middle line:90%
Don't do any of that stuff.

00:54:21.250 --> 00:54:22.330 align:middle line:90%
But that's the other guy.

00:54:22.330 --> 00:54:23.660 align:middle line:90%
That's not me.

00:54:23.660 --> 00:54:25.090 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:54:25.090 --> 00:54:29.890 align:middle line:84%
What I'm here to say
is, you will soothe.

00:54:29.890 --> 00:54:31.870 align:middle line:90%
You will soothe.

00:54:31.870 --> 00:54:35.110 align:middle line:84%
And the only question
is, how do you

00:54:35.110 --> 00:54:39.280 align:middle line:84%
want to soothe to
get the maximal pain

00:54:39.280 --> 00:54:42.760 align:middle line:90%
relief for the least cost?

00:54:42.760 --> 00:54:45.100 align:middle line:84%
And I start going through
the list and I'm like--

00:54:45.100 --> 00:54:46.780 align:middle line:84%
so one thing, if
you were coming up

00:54:46.780 --> 00:54:48.520 align:middle line:84%
