to sit back and enjoy the show,
but I wouldn't do anything.

01:05:23.660 --> 01:05:26.600 align:middle line:84%
I think it was Napoleon who said
the worst thing a general can

01:05:26.600 --> 01:05:29.660 align:middle line:84%
do is interrupt their
rival when they're

01:05:29.660 --> 01:05:33.950 align:middle line:84%
in the process of shooting
themselves in the foot.

01:05:33.950 --> 01:05:38.300 align:middle line:84%
When your enemy is screwing
up, don't interfere.

01:05:38.300 --> 01:05:41.480 align:middle line:84%
So if I really hated you
and you were burning alive,

01:05:41.480 --> 01:05:43.820 align:middle line:90%
I would let you burn.

01:05:43.820 --> 01:05:46.380 align:middle line:84%
And you don't do
that to yourself.

01:05:46.380 --> 01:05:51.320 align:middle line:84%
The more you burn, the more
despicable things you do--

01:05:51.320 --> 01:05:53.260 align:middle line:84%
I'm guilty, I'm
this monster, I'm

01:05:53.260 --> 01:05:55.770 align:middle line:84%
a piece of shit, blah,
blah, blah, blah--

01:05:55.770 --> 01:05:56.810 align:middle line:90%
you still reach out.

01:05:56.810 --> 01:05:59.240 align:middle line:90%


01:05:59.240 --> 01:06:01.550 align:middle line:84%
There's a style, and
there's no accounting

01:06:01.550 --> 01:06:05.030 align:middle line:84%
for-- you may reach for
things that are bad for you

01:06:05.030 --> 01:06:06.710 align:middle line:90%
and don't really work.

01:06:06.710 --> 01:06:09.555 align:middle line:84%
But you do reach for
something, right?

01:06:09.555 --> 01:06:10.430 align:middle line:90%
And that's self-love.

01:06:10.430 --> 01:06:13.585 align:middle line:84%
And that self-love it's
pretty damn unconditional.

01:06:13.585 --> 01:06:16.655 align:middle line:90%


01:06:16.655 --> 01:06:18.660 align:middle line:84%
And I want to be very
careful when I say this,

01:06:18.660 --> 01:06:22.460 align:middle line:84%
but sometimes people are like,
I'm at the end of my rope.

01:06:22.460 --> 01:06:25.280 align:middle line:90%
I just want to end it all.

01:06:25.280 --> 01:06:30.860 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, even that
can at a certain level

01:06:30.860 --> 01:06:34.940 align:middle line:90%
be interpreted as a misguided--

01:06:34.940 --> 01:06:39.650 align:middle line:84%
misguided-- form of
self-love, because you

01:06:39.650 --> 01:06:40.840 align:middle line:90%
want the pain to end.

01:06:40.840 --> 01:06:43.860 align:middle line:90%


01:06:43.860 --> 01:06:45.570 align:middle line:84%
And that is its own
form of self-love.

01:06:45.570 --> 01:06:47.880 align:middle line:84%
Now, I'm not advocating
that, because it's misguided.

01:06:47.880 --> 01:06:49.800 align:middle line:84%
And I'll explain
why in a minute.

01:06:49.800 --> 01:06:54.540 align:middle line:84%
But again, if I'm your enemy
and I'm watching you burn alive,

01:06:54.540 --> 01:06:57.210 align:middle line:84%
my most fervent wish is
for your immortality.

01:06:57.210 --> 01:07:00.400 align:middle line:90%


01:07:00.400 --> 01:07:01.580 align:middle line:90%
I want you to stay alive.

01:07:01.580 --> 01:07:05.140 align:middle line:84%
I don't want you to die, because
I don't want your pain to end.

01:07:05.140 --> 01:07:07.450 align:middle line:84%
And so when I feel
like I'm burning alive

01:07:07.450 --> 01:07:08.950 align:middle line:84%
and I'm like, well,
maybe one option

01:07:08.950 --> 01:07:11.110 align:middle line:84%
would be to just end
everything, that's

01:07:11.110 --> 01:07:14.080 align:middle line:84%
still a misguided
form of self-love,

01:07:14.080 --> 01:07:16.980 align:middle line:84%
because you're still trying
to make the pain go away.

01:07:16.980 --> 01:07:20.210 align:middle line:84%
The only difference is
you've run out of ideas.

01:07:20.210 --> 01:07:22.450 align:middle line:84%
But I mean, as we
all know, if you just

01:07:22.450 --> 01:07:25.120 align:middle line:84%
think about your
own life experience,

01:07:25.120 --> 01:07:27.670 align:middle line:84%
if you sit there
long enough in pain,

01:07:27.670 --> 01:07:30.670 align:middle line:84%
you will come up
with more ideas.

01:07:30.670 --> 01:07:32.697 align:middle line:84%
Necessity is the
mother of invention.

01:07:32.697 --> 01:07:34.280 align:middle line:84%
If you just sit there
for long enough,

01:07:34.280 --> 01:07:41.950 align:middle line:84%
the necessity of your pain will
come up with new ways, at least

01:07:41.950 --> 01:07:44.320 align:middle line:90%
new things to try.

01:07:44.320 --> 01:07:48.660 align:middle line:84%
Your creativity will be fired
up, for better or worse.

01:07:48.660 --> 01:07:52.330 align:middle line:90%
So that's why I'm always like--

01:07:52.330 --> 01:07:54.400 align:middle line:84%
you know, that's
never an answer.

01:07:54.400 --> 01:07:56.650 align:middle line:84%
Because in my opinion, you
were put here for a reason.

01:07:56.650 --> 01:08:00.310 align:middle line:90%


01:08:00.310 --> 01:08:02.120 align:middle line:84%
Your mission, if you
choose to accept it,

01:08:02.120 --> 01:08:07.030 align:middle line:84%
is to find that reason and
fulfill it, if you can.

01:08:07.030 --> 01:08:09.700 align:middle line:90%


01:08:09.700 --> 01:08:11.900 align:middle line:84%
And if you're gone,
then the game's over.

01:08:11.900 --> 01:08:13.120 align:middle line:90%
And that's no fun.

01:08:13.120 --> 01:08:13.960 align:middle line:90%
So just sit.

01:08:13.960 --> 01:08:14.793 align:middle line:90%
I know it's painful.

01:08:14.793 --> 01:08:16.420 align:middle line:84%
Just sit and see
what else comes.

01:08:16.420 --> 01:08:18.729 align:middle line:90%
And something always comes.

01:08:18.729 --> 01:08:20.260 align:middle line:90%
Something always comes.

01:08:20.260 --> 01:08:21.819 align:middle line:90%
>> Or someone comes to you.

01:08:21.819 --> 01:08:24.819 align:middle line:90%
>> Or someone.

01:08:24.819 --> 01:08:28.180 align:middle line:84%
>> One concept that I really
resonated with well and I think

01:08:28.180 --> 01:08:30.729 align:middle line:84%
a lot of people understand--
and I think it's similar to this

01:08:30.729 --> 01:08:35.170 align:middle line:84%
mask ideology, or
this mask theory--

01:08:35.170 --> 01:08:39.819 align:middle line:90%
is this locked up board member.

01:08:39.819 --> 01:08:42.790 align:middle line:84%
I'm a huge fan of it, because I
think it's such a practical way

01:08:42.790 --> 01:08:44.350 align:middle line:90%
to dig into the psyche.

01:08:44.350 --> 01:08:50.560 align:middle line:84%
And if I use different
examples, like my parents

01:08:50.560 --> 01:08:51.939 align:middle line:90%
might have said or someone--

01:08:51.939 --> 01:08:55.870 align:middle line:84%
like, if you go do this,
if you go get a good job,

01:08:55.870 --> 01:08:58.060 align:middle line:90%
we'll love you.

01:08:58.060 --> 01:09:00.160 align:middle line:84%
I used to play in
punk rock bands.

01:09:00.160 --> 01:09:04.779 align:middle line:84%
I love fast, melodic punk, like
Lagwagon, No Use for a Name,

01:09:04.779 --> 01:09:05.939 align:middle line:90%
NOFX, these sort of things.

01:09:05.939 --> 01:09:06.739 align:middle line:90%
Loved it.

01:09:06.739 --> 01:09:09.670 align:middle line:84%
I played with two boys I
connected with really well

01:09:09.670 --> 01:09:10.689 align:middle line:90%
on music.

01:09:10.689 --> 01:09:12.040 align:middle line:90%
We played gigs, recorded albums.

01:09:12.040 --> 01:09:14.979 align:middle line:84%
My parents are like, you can't
make money doing that, Ryan.

01:09:14.979 --> 01:09:17.830 align:middle line:84%
I mean, punk rock is a
niche within a niche, right?

01:09:17.830 --> 01:09:21.502 align:middle line:84%
And it's also like, yeah, no,
you have to go get a real job.

01:09:21.502 --> 01:09:23.710 align:middle line:84%
And when you do that and
get all your qualifications,

01:09:23.710 --> 01:09:25.930 align:middle line:90%
then you're doing a good job.

01:09:25.930 --> 01:09:28.359 align:middle line:90%
AKA, we'll love you.

01:09:28.359 --> 01:09:33.316 align:middle line:84%
Or in the case of
speaking to specificity,

01:09:33.316 --> 01:09:35.649 align:middle line:84%
because it's easy when you
do that, Laurentine, my wife,

01:09:35.649 --> 01:09:38.787 align:middle line:84%
she grew up with this father
who was a banker and a financier

01:09:38.787 --> 01:09:40.120 align:middle line:90%
and living all around the world.

01:09:40.120 --> 01:09:42.223 align:middle line:84%
And he's like, well,
my eldest son--

01:09:42.223 --> 01:09:44.640 align:middle line:84%
it was meant to be a son, but
it was a daughter, you know?

01:09:44.640 --> 01:09:46.510 align:middle line:84%
You will go study
law in Switzerland,

01:09:46.510 --> 01:09:49.790 align:middle line:84%
because that's what
upstanding Dutch families do.

01:09:49.790 --> 01:09:52.353 align:middle line:84%
So she was sent to a
law school at a nunnery.

01:09:52.353 --> 01:09:53.770 align:middle line:84%
And it was taught
in German, which

01:09:53.770 --> 01:09:55.450 align:middle line:90%
is like her fourth language.

01:09:55.450 --> 01:09:57.370 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, go be a
good girl and do that,

01:09:57.370 --> 01:10:00.040 align:middle line:84%
and then you'll
be worthy of love.

01:10:00.040 --> 01:10:03.130 align:middle line:90%
And she's a great artist.

01:10:03.130 --> 01:10:05.320 align:middle line:84%
She wanted to study
psychology or anthropology

01:10:05.320 --> 01:10:08.250 align:middle line:84%
and human behavior, things
that we're into now.

01:10:08.250 --> 01:10:10.900 align:middle line:84%
But that board
member got locked up

01:10:10.900 --> 01:10:12.610 align:middle line:84%
for the sake of
pleasing her father.

01:10:12.610 --> 01:10:14.500 align:middle line:84%
And so did my
creative board member.

01:10:14.500 --> 01:10:16.960 align:middle line:84%
Luckily, I took a guitar
with me on my career.

01:10:16.960 --> 01:10:18.172 align:middle line:90%
So I kept playing.

01:10:18.172 --> 01:10:20.630 align:middle line:84%
But then you get to this stage
where it's like, actually, I

01:10:20.630 --> 01:10:24.700 align:middle line:84%
want to go get that
guy out of the closet

01:10:24.700 --> 01:10:25.930 align:middle line:90%
and say it's OK to come back.

01:10:25.930 --> 01:10:27.305 align:middle line:84%
And when you come
back, you start

01:10:27.305 --> 01:10:29.860 align:middle line:84%
to just angle that
a little bit more

01:10:29.860 --> 01:10:31.807 align:middle line:84%
slightly towards
your bliss, which

01:10:31.807 --> 01:10:32.890 align:middle line:90%
is an interesting journey.

01:10:32.890 --> 01:10:35.100 align:middle line:90%
So I love that ideology.

01:10:35.100 --> 01:10:38.860 align:middle line:84%
I think it should be a
book in and unto itself.

01:10:38.860 --> 01:10:41.560 align:middle line:84%
Tell me about how we
lock up a board member,

01:10:41.560 --> 01:10:43.340 align:middle line:84%
and how that
happens and the cost

01:10:43.340 --> 01:10:47.350 align:middle line:90%
that that can come in our lives.

01:10:47.350 --> 01:10:52.660 align:middle line:84%
>> So the million dollar
question when we talk about

01:10:52.660 --> 01:10:58.660 align:middle line:84%
soothing and shielding is
asked by one in 1,000 people I

01:10:58.660 --> 01:10:59.850 align:middle line:90%
encounter.

01:10:59.850 --> 01:11:00.650 align:middle line:90%
And that's fine.

01:11:00.650 --> 01:11:06.043 align:middle line:84%
It just shows you how not in
the forefront of our minds

01:11:06.043 --> 01:11:06.960 align:middle line:90%
thinking like this is.

01:11:06.960 --> 01:11:10.180 align:middle line:90%


01:11:10.180 --> 01:11:13.000 align:middle line:84%
But every now and
then someone will ask,

01:11:13.000 --> 01:11:15.520 align:middle line:84%
well, it's great to soothe
differently and shield

01:11:15.520 --> 01:11:20.230 align:middle line:84%
differently, to optimize how
we're managing the wound,

01:11:20.230 --> 01:11:22.900 align:middle line:84%
like numbing it
with better value

01:11:22.900 --> 01:11:25.130 align:middle line:84%
and shielding it
with better value.

01:11:25.130 --> 01:11:31.290 align:middle line:84%
But is there a way to actually
just heal the wound itself?

01:11:31.290 --> 01:11:32.790 align:middle line:84%
Because if you could
heal the wound,

01:11:32.790 --> 01:11:36.390 align:middle line:84%
and you wouldn't need to
soothe or shield at all.

01:11:36.390 --> 01:11:38.820 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know if
that's possible, but is

01:11:38.820 --> 01:11:39.690 align:middle line:90%
that even an option?

01:11:39.690 --> 01:11:43.520 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, I want to
talk to you after the talk.

01:11:43.520 --> 01:11:47.220 align:middle line:90%


01:11:47.220 --> 01:11:53.010 align:middle line:84%
I want to take a reading
of your brain to understand

01:11:53.010 --> 01:11:54.840 align:middle line:90%
how that came out.

01:11:54.840 --> 01:12:01.620 align:middle line:84%
And so after we do some
just quick optimization

01:12:01.620 --> 01:12:04.860 align:middle line:84%
of your soothing and
shielding, just so you're good,

01:12:04.860 --> 01:12:09.840 align:middle line:84%
you're stable for like a few
weeks, then we pop the hood

01:12:09.840 --> 01:12:12.980 align:middle line:84%
and go into looking
at the actual wound.

01:12:12.980 --> 01:12:15.194 align:middle line:84%
And the way I describe the
wound is the following.

01:12:15.194 --> 01:12:19.370 align:middle line:90%


01:12:19.370 --> 01:12:20.940 align:middle line:84%
The way I think
about it is that--

01:12:20.940 --> 01:12:23.610 align:middle line:84%
and this is an image
from my corporate days--

01:12:23.610 --> 01:12:26.490 align:middle line:84%
we all have like what
is metaphorically

01:12:26.490 --> 01:12:31.380 align:middle line:84%
like a board of directors
within us, where we're the CEO.

01:12:31.380 --> 01:12:35.112 align:middle line:84%
And there are a number of
characters on this board.

01:12:35.112 --> 01:12:36.570 align:middle line:84%
There's a chief of
security to make

01:12:36.570 --> 01:12:38.310 align:middle line:84%
sure you don't get
hit by a bus when

01:12:38.310 --> 01:12:39.900 align:middle line:90%
you walk out on the street.

01:12:39.900 --> 01:12:42.200 align:middle line:90%
There's your creativity.

01:12:42.200 --> 01:12:44.460 align:middle line:84%
There's the one in
charge of making

01:12:44.460 --> 01:12:48.450 align:middle line:84%
sure you get prestige
and are not humiliated.

01:12:48.450 --> 01:12:51.980 align:middle line:90%
Your body is a board member.

01:12:51.980 --> 01:12:55.050 align:middle line:84%
Your muse, if you
think of it that way,

01:12:55.050 --> 01:12:57.000 align:middle line:90%
can be a board member.

01:12:57.000 --> 01:12:59.820 align:middle line:84%
And basically, all
the sort of major life

01:12:59.820 --> 01:13:05.830 align:middle line:84%
forces you identify as
such are board members.

01:13:05.830 --> 01:13:09.810 align:middle line:84%
So in the more
nuanced cases, money

01:13:09.810 --> 01:13:13.120 align:middle line:84%
itself can be seen
as a board member.

01:13:13.120 --> 01:13:15.600 align:middle line:84%
So if you have money
blocks or fear of money,

01:13:15.600 --> 01:13:17.415 align:middle line:84%
it is that board
member being exiled.

01:13:17.415 --> 01:13:20.310 align:middle line:90%


01:13:20.310 --> 01:13:23.280 align:middle line:84%
And so the way the
wounding happens

01:13:23.280 --> 01:13:28.652 align:middle line:84%
then is that when you're
told to put this mask on

01:13:28.652 --> 01:13:30.610 align:middle line:84%
and you're like, shit,
I'm going to lose love--

01:13:30.610 --> 01:13:33.690 align:middle line:84%
I've got a gun to my
head, so I'll put it on--

01:13:33.690 --> 01:13:37.620 align:middle line:84%
there will be parts
of you that stick out,

01:13:37.620 --> 01:13:39.000 align:middle line:90%
because the mask is not organic.

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:43.800 align:middle line:84%
The mask is fashioned by society
for its own machine purposes.

01:13:43.800 --> 01:13:45.240 align:middle line:90%
And that's fine.

01:13:45.240 --> 01:13:47.555 align:middle line:84%
But when you put it
on, you'll realize

01:13:47.555 --> 01:13:49.680 align:middle line:84%
that there are certain
parts of you that don't fit,

01:13:49.680 --> 01:13:51.760 align:middle line:90%
that stick out.

01:13:51.760 --> 01:13:55.050 align:middle line:84%
And in many cases, allowing
those parts of you to stick out

01:13:55.050 --> 01:14:00.810 align:middle line:84%
is punished as much as
if you took a mask off,

01:14:00.810 --> 01:14:03.550 align:middle line:84%
because it's ruining my
suspension of disbelief.

01:14:03.550 --> 01:14:04.350 align:middle line:90%
You're a good boy.

01:14:04.350 --> 01:14:08.550 align:middle line:84%
You're an upstanding
Swiss legal expert

01:14:08.550 --> 01:14:12.180 align:middle line:84%
that will help manage
the family, our clients

01:14:12.180 --> 01:14:13.060 align:middle line:90%
and everything.

01:14:13.060 --> 01:14:17.640 align:middle line:90%


01:14:17.640 --> 01:14:21.010 align:middle line:84%
You can perhaps paint
as a hobby on the side.

01:14:21.010 --> 01:14:24.150 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to hear
anything about it.

01:14:24.150 --> 01:14:27.780 align:middle line:84%
And certainly, you cannot let
that bleed over and impinge

01:14:27.780 --> 01:14:30.270 align:middle line:84%
and degrade your
professional persona.

01:14:30.270 --> 01:14:35.400 align:middle line:84%
Very standard reading
of the riot act, right?

01:14:35.400 --> 01:14:38.250 align:middle line:84%
And comply with all of this
with a bow on top, or else you

01:14:38.250 --> 01:14:40.830 align:middle line:90%
will lose love.

01:14:40.830 --> 01:14:44.361 align:middle line:84%
And so caddle prod is
hit, and we start running.

01:14:44.361 --> 01:14:48.720 align:middle line:84%
And again, that's
just the fighter jet.

01:14:48.720 --> 01:14:51.900 align:middle line:84%
If you were in her position,
if I were in her position,

01:14:51.900 --> 01:14:54.690 align:middle line:90%
we would do no better.

01:14:54.690 --> 01:14:57.110 align:middle line:84%
I mean, given her path, we
would probably do a lot worse.

01:14:57.110 --> 01:15:01.450 align:middle line:90%


01:15:01.450 --> 01:15:06.990 align:middle line:84%
So the thing is, you get that
cattle prod enough times,

01:15:06.990 --> 01:15:10.260 align:middle line:84%
pretty soon an emergency meeting
of the board of directors

01:15:10.260 --> 01:15:12.350 align:middle line:90%
is called.

01:15:12.350 --> 01:15:14.640 align:middle line:84%
And the chief of security--
in this day and age,

01:15:14.640 --> 01:15:18.180 align:middle line:84%
I might even say the chief
of Homeland Security--

01:15:18.180 --> 01:15:21.000 align:middle line:84%
makes an announcement
and says, look,

01:15:21.000 --> 01:15:22.670 align:middle line:84%
I know we all have
our roles, and we're

01:15:22.670 --> 01:15:25.650 align:middle line:84%
all life tenured members of
the board and everything.

01:15:25.650 --> 01:15:29.070 align:middle line:84%
But we've got a serious
life-or-death situation

01:15:29.070 --> 01:15:30.480 align:middle line:90%
on our hands.

01:15:30.480 --> 01:15:34.170 align:middle line:84%
If our dad looks at
us like that again,

01:15:34.170 --> 01:15:35.340 align:middle line:90%
there could be real trouble.

01:15:35.340 --> 01:15:39.900 align:middle line:84%
If our mom looks at us with
that look of disappointment,

01:15:39.900 --> 01:15:41.190 align:middle line:90%
there could be trouble.

01:15:41.190 --> 01:15:45.510 align:middle line:84%
And there is a part of our
deep biological chassis

01:15:45.510 --> 01:15:48.690 align:middle line:84%
that knows that if we
are rejected enough

01:15:48.690 --> 01:15:52.830 align:middle line:84%
and we don't comply to it
past of certain extreme,

01:15:52.830 --> 01:15:54.660 align:middle line:90%
we could lose our lives.

01:15:54.660 --> 01:15:57.450 align:middle line:84%
We'll be left on the
hillside to freeze or be

01:15:57.450 --> 01:15:59.620 align:middle line:90%
fed to the wolves or whatever.

01:15:59.620 --> 01:16:01.620 align:middle line:84%
And a civilized person
maybe will be like, well,

