01:26:39.200 --> 01:26:40.250 align:middle line:90%
Go to this.

01:26:40.250 --> 01:26:42.020 align:middle line:84%
What if you just
started painting again?

01:26:42.020 --> 01:26:46.790 align:middle line:84%
Does that help you retouch
base with that core essence

01:26:46.790 --> 01:26:47.930 align:middle line:90%
of who you are?

01:26:47.930 --> 01:26:51.380 align:middle line:84%
Can that be a healing process,
to just let that liberate?

01:26:51.380 --> 01:26:52.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

01:26:52.250 --> 01:26:53.050 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

01:26:53.050 --> 01:26:55.205 align:middle line:90%
But there are caveats.

01:26:55.205 --> 01:26:59.780 align:middle line:90%


01:26:59.780 --> 01:27:02.150 align:middle line:84%
So in a sense, you could
say if it were that simple,

01:27:02.150 --> 01:27:03.830 align:middle line:90%
everyone would just do it.

01:27:03.830 --> 01:27:05.870 align:middle line:90%
Many people do.

01:27:05.870 --> 01:27:13.790 align:middle line:84%
But you've got to remember that
this is a board of directors.

01:27:13.790 --> 01:27:17.000 align:middle line:84%
And they all love you,
and they are all sworn.

01:27:17.000 --> 01:27:20.900 align:middle line:90%
They would do anything for you.

01:27:20.900 --> 01:27:23.333 align:middle line:84%
They'll do things that are
monstrous to your own self,

01:27:23.333 --> 01:27:24.500 align:middle line:90%
exiling other board members.

01:27:24.500 --> 01:27:27.167 align:middle line:84%
They will do monstrous things to
other people in the outer world

01:27:27.167 --> 01:27:31.670 align:middle line:84%
to keep you safe and put
you in a thriving position.

01:27:31.670 --> 01:27:37.400 align:middle line:84%
They're very selfish, jealously
guarding and loving you.

01:27:37.400 --> 01:27:39.560 align:middle line:84%
And this is all
the board members,

01:27:39.560 --> 01:27:45.020 align:middle line:84%
even the board members who
exiled your lost board member.

01:27:45.020 --> 01:27:47.060 align:middle line:84%
So when you start
painting again--

01:27:47.060 --> 01:27:50.060 align:middle line:84%
or more likely, when you start
thinking about painting again--

01:27:50.060 --> 01:27:52.580 align:middle line:90%


01:27:52.580 --> 01:27:55.747 align:middle line:84%
the bully, protector
side of the board

01:27:55.747 --> 01:27:57.830 align:middle line:84%
will be like, now wait
just a goddamn minute here.

01:27:57.830 --> 01:28:00.770 align:middle line:90%


01:28:00.770 --> 01:28:04.528 align:middle line:84%
Your dad doesn't need to
be around to remind you.

01:28:04.528 --> 01:28:06.570 align:middle line:84%
You've got your dad within
you as a board member.

01:28:06.570 --> 01:28:10.460 align:middle line:90%


01:28:10.460 --> 01:28:13.880 align:middle line:84%
Even when men and
women are in their 70s

01:28:13.880 --> 01:28:19.610 align:middle line:84%
and their parents are long gone
from this world, they're like,

01:28:19.610 --> 01:28:22.820 align:middle line:84%
I can still hear my dad saying
that damn thing he always

01:28:22.820 --> 01:28:27.320 align:middle line:84%
said like it was yesterday,
like it was half an hour ago.

01:28:27.320 --> 01:28:30.010 align:middle line:84%
And that's your own
inner board member--

01:28:30.010 --> 01:28:32.900 align:middle line:84%
in that case, your inner
masculine board member--

01:28:32.900 --> 01:28:36.740 align:middle line:84%
scripted and
programmed by your dad.

01:28:36.740 --> 01:28:41.073 align:middle line:84%
So the things that says to
you, a, are not your fault.

01:28:41.073 --> 01:28:42.740 align:middle line:84%
They're technically
not your dad's fault

01:28:42.740 --> 01:28:44.782 align:middle line:84%
either, because he wasn't
born talking like that.

01:28:44.782 --> 01:28:46.120 align:middle line:90%
He learned it from someone.

01:28:46.120 --> 01:28:48.500 align:middle line:84%
You inherit it like you inherit
your eye color, your hair

01:28:48.500 --> 01:28:51.170 align:middle line:84%
color, the foods
you eat at holiday,

01:28:51.170 --> 01:28:53.060 align:middle line:90%
what holidays you actually--

01:28:53.060 --> 01:28:55.730 align:middle line:90%
you inherit all these things.

01:28:55.730 --> 01:28:57.110 align:middle line:90%
And it's no one's fault.

01:28:57.110 --> 01:29:02.810 align:middle line:84%
But you get this thing, and
it is a voice within you,

01:29:02.810 --> 01:29:06.450 align:middle line:90%
and it has authority and power.

01:29:06.450 --> 01:29:13.820 align:middle line:84%
So if you can get the board to
even approve the authorization

01:29:13.820 --> 01:29:17.438 align:middle line:84%
to get yourself some
paints and paint,

01:29:17.438 --> 01:29:18.980 align:middle line:84%
oftentimes people
will think about it

01:29:18.980 --> 01:29:23.090 align:middle line:90%
and agonize over it for months.

01:29:23.090 --> 01:29:24.650 align:middle line:90%
It'll put it out.

01:29:24.650 --> 01:29:26.240 align:middle line:84%
Some emergency at
work will happen,

01:29:26.240 --> 01:29:28.922 align:middle line:84%
and they'll forget everything
for another six weeks.

01:29:28.922 --> 01:29:30.380 align:middle line:84%
And then they'll
finally get around

01:29:30.380 --> 01:29:32.380 align:middle line:84%
to some post-it they wrote
to themselves saying,

01:29:32.380 --> 01:29:33.860 align:middle line:84%
maybe I can start
painting again.

01:29:33.860 --> 01:29:36.480 align:middle line:84%
And even then, they'll push
it off three or four times.

01:29:36.480 --> 01:29:39.620 align:middle line:84%
Finally, they'll go
to the art store,

01:29:39.620 --> 01:29:43.160 align:middle line:84%
like, breaking out in hives
while they're doing it.

01:29:43.160 --> 01:29:46.010 align:middle line:84%
Pick up one canvas
and just one starter,

01:29:46.010 --> 01:29:48.030 align:middle line:90%
eight-color acrylic set.

01:29:48.030 --> 01:29:50.030 align:middle line:84%
And they'll bring it home,
they'll put it there,

01:29:50.030 --> 01:29:53.750 align:middle line:84%
and it will go untouched
for another two months.

01:29:53.750 --> 01:29:54.620 align:middle line:90%
Why is that?

01:29:54.620 --> 01:29:56.230 align:middle line:84%
People are like,
what's the big deal?

01:29:56.230 --> 01:29:58.200 align:middle line:90%
It's nothing.

01:29:58.200 --> 01:29:59.905 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is,
it's not nothing.

01:29:59.905 --> 01:30:01.280 align:middle line:84%
You have this
artist board member

01:30:01.280 --> 01:30:03.590 align:middle line:90%
that's like, I just need to--

01:30:03.590 --> 01:30:04.550 align:middle line:90%
I'm turning blue.

01:30:04.550 --> 01:30:07.880 align:middle line:84%
I just need to loosen a little
bit to get a little bit of air.

01:30:07.880 --> 01:30:09.830 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to
threaten the empire.

01:30:09.830 --> 01:30:11.538 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to
threaten the status quo.

01:30:11.538 --> 01:30:13.240 align:middle line:90%
I just need a little bit of air.

01:30:13.240 --> 01:30:16.640 align:middle line:84%
And if not, I will
pull this lever that

01:30:16.640 --> 01:30:20.090 align:middle line:84%
will throw your back out
again so you're lying down

01:30:20.090 --> 01:30:22.400 align:middle line:84%
and I can really
work on you to, like,

01:30:22.400 --> 01:30:24.420 align:middle line:84%
at least get an easel
in your hospital bed.

01:30:24.420 --> 01:30:28.250 align:middle line:84%
I'm making this up, but
it's the physics of it.

01:30:28.250 --> 01:30:34.970 align:middle line:84%
And so there is this constant
back-and-forth debate,

01:30:34.970 --> 01:30:37.340 align:middle line:84%
because it's not just,
oh, rainbows and unicorns,

01:30:37.340 --> 01:30:38.180 align:middle line:90%
let the artist back.

01:30:38.180 --> 01:30:39.630 align:middle line:90%
It's like, let the artist back.

01:30:39.630 --> 01:30:42.240 align:middle line:90%
That's a big deal.

01:30:42.240 --> 01:30:45.500 align:middle line:84%
There's a reason she was
exiled in the first place.

01:30:45.500 --> 01:30:47.690 align:middle line:84%
It's because you have
this hanging sword of,

01:30:47.690 --> 01:30:49.820 align:middle line:90%
you will be unworthy of love.

01:30:49.820 --> 01:30:51.830 align:middle line:84%
You will disappoint
your parents,

01:30:51.830 --> 01:30:54.733 align:middle line:84%
you'll break their hearts, and
you'll be unworthy of love.

01:30:54.733 --> 01:30:56.150 align:middle line:84%
Oh, and by the
way, the spouse you

01:30:56.150 --> 01:30:57.920 align:middle line:84%
married on this
pretext of you will

01:30:57.920 --> 01:31:00.312 align:middle line:84%
be this banker or whatever,
she'll leave you too,

01:31:00.312 --> 01:31:01.520 align:middle line:90%
and you'll break your family.

01:31:01.520 --> 01:31:02.790 align:middle line:90%
You'll hurt your children.

01:31:02.790 --> 01:31:04.457 align:middle line:84%
They'll inherit the
wound going forward.

01:31:04.457 --> 01:31:06.770 align:middle line:90%
You'll fuck them up too.

01:31:06.770 --> 01:31:09.710 align:middle line:84%
It's not a trivial thing to
just go out and start painting

01:31:09.710 --> 01:31:12.230 align:middle line:90%
again.

01:31:12.230 --> 01:31:14.330 align:middle line:84%
So when people say, oh,
just follow your passions,

01:31:14.330 --> 01:31:15.830 align:middle line:84%
follow your bliss,
it's no big deal,

01:31:15.830 --> 01:31:17.955 align:middle line:84%
and they wag their fingers
at them, I'm like, dude,

01:31:17.955 --> 01:31:19.430 align:middle line:90%
don't do that.

01:31:19.430 --> 01:31:22.460 align:middle line:84%
It's not trivial to
do this, and it's not

01:31:22.460 --> 01:31:25.290 align:middle line:90%
a decision to be taken lightly.

01:31:25.290 --> 01:31:29.300 align:middle line:84%
And so for me, from my
corporate days, when

01:31:29.300 --> 01:31:32.490 align:middle line:84%
you have a conflict
at the board level,

01:31:32.490 --> 01:31:35.960 align:middle line:84%
the worst way to solve it is
through a brute force pissing

01:31:35.960 --> 01:31:41.530 align:middle line:84%
match, because you create
strife within the board.

01:31:41.530 --> 01:31:44.710 align:middle line:84%
And you lose sight of the fact
that we're all shareholders

01:31:44.710 --> 01:31:47.080 align:middle line:90%
in this entity.

01:31:47.080 --> 01:31:50.120 align:middle line:90%
We all want it to succeed.

01:31:50.120 --> 01:31:51.700 align:middle line:84%
And when we disagree,
it's not good

01:31:51.700 --> 01:31:55.330 align:middle line:90%
or evil or loving or malicious.

01:31:55.330 --> 01:32:00.400 align:middle line:84%
It is all loving and simply
in disagreement on areas where

01:32:00.400 --> 01:32:02.650 align:middle line:90%
reasonable minds will differ.

01:32:02.650 --> 01:32:04.630 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to lose love.

01:32:04.630 --> 01:32:07.390 align:middle line:84%
I also don't want to not express
my true meaning and purpose

01:32:07.390 --> 01:32:09.140 align:middle line:90%
in life.

01:32:09.140 --> 01:32:09.940 align:middle line:90%
Right?

01:32:09.940 --> 01:32:17.020 align:middle line:84%
So for me, what I am is
a boardroom consultant.

01:32:17.020 --> 01:32:18.970 align:middle line:90%
I'm not a board member.

01:32:18.970 --> 01:32:20.780 align:middle line:90%
I don't have a vote.

01:32:20.780 --> 01:32:22.420 align:middle line:90%
I don't have a vote.

01:32:22.420 --> 01:32:25.840 align:middle line:84%
But I do come in and
help people start talking

01:32:25.840 --> 01:32:30.430 align:middle line:84%
to these parts of
themselves to basically say,

01:32:30.430 --> 01:32:33.250 align:middle line:84%
even if you get to the point
where you just draw the battle

01:32:33.250 --> 01:32:35.770 align:middle line:90%
lines--

01:32:35.770 --> 01:32:36.770 align:middle line:90%
like, we want money.

01:32:36.770 --> 01:32:38.500 align:middle line:90%
We want prestige.

01:32:38.500 --> 01:32:42.010 align:middle line:84%
We want comfort,
material comfort.

01:32:42.010 --> 01:32:45.250 align:middle line:84%
We want the ability
to shut dad up,

01:32:45.250 --> 01:32:47.800 align:middle line:84%
because now he's
asking us for money.

01:32:47.800 --> 01:32:48.670 align:middle line:90%
So that's nice.

01:32:48.670 --> 01:32:50.230 align:middle line:90%
Shuts the old man up, right?

01:32:50.230 --> 01:32:54.330 align:middle line:90%


01:32:54.330 --> 01:32:55.930 align:middle line:84%
But on the artist's
side, it's like, I

01:32:55.930 --> 01:32:59.480 align:middle line:84%
need to express
this, this, and this.

01:32:59.480 --> 01:33:01.870 align:middle line:84%
And if you are so afraid
of it that you only

01:33:01.870 --> 01:33:04.990 align:middle line:84%
take a fleeting
glance, it just looks

01:33:04.990 --> 01:33:11.050 align:middle line:84%
like the irresistible
force hitting

01:33:11.050 --> 01:33:13.360 align:middle line:90%
against the immovable object.

01:33:13.360 --> 01:33:16.150 align:middle line:84%
At 30,000 feet, that's
what it all looks like.

01:33:16.150 --> 01:33:18.790 align:middle line:84%
But if you give yourself
permission to say, look,

01:33:18.790 --> 01:33:19.750 align:middle line:90%
it's the F-16.

01:33:19.750 --> 01:33:21.710 align:middle line:90%
Everyone's-- it's my thing.

01:33:21.710 --> 01:33:23.230 align:middle line:90%
Let me just look at it.

01:33:23.230 --> 01:33:25.540 align:middle line:90%
It will be uncomfortable.

01:33:25.540 --> 01:33:29.080 align:middle line:84%
Because when you heal
something, it itches.

01:33:29.080 --> 01:33:30.550 align:middle line:90%
But that's a good sign.

01:33:30.550 --> 01:33:32.200 align:middle line:90%
It will be uncomfortable.

01:33:32.200 --> 01:33:34.420 align:middle line:84%
But when you get in there,
even drawing up the battle

01:33:34.420 --> 01:33:38.680 align:middle line:84%
lines is huge progress,
because then at least you

01:33:38.680 --> 01:33:40.390 align:middle line:84%
know what each
side wants, and you

01:33:40.390 --> 01:33:45.130 align:middle line:84%
can start the negotiation
and potential compromise.

01:33:45.130 --> 01:33:46.840 align:middle line:84%
And I've found
that there's always

01:33:46.840 --> 01:33:49.150 align:middle line:90%
a way to thread the needle.

01:33:49.150 --> 01:33:55.630 align:middle line:84%
I've never found a
case where it was not

01:33:55.630 --> 01:33:58.123 align:middle line:90%
possible to thread the needle.

01:33:58.123 --> 01:33:59.290 align:middle line:90%
And what I mean by that is--

01:33:59.290 --> 01:34:04.910 align:middle line:90%


01:34:04.910 --> 01:34:13.070 align:middle line:84%
I've never seen the dice
throw of the universe end

01:34:13.070 --> 01:34:18.350 align:middle line:84%
up where a person is
born into this world

01:34:18.350 --> 01:34:22.640 align:middle line:84%
and they're given a bliss that
is completely incompatible

01:34:22.640 --> 01:34:25.610 align:middle line:84%
with life, the
practicalities of life.

01:34:25.610 --> 01:34:26.450 align:middle line:90%
I've never seen it.

01:34:26.450 --> 01:34:28.980 align:middle line:90%


01:34:28.980 --> 01:34:34.980 align:middle line:84%
And the reason why the
occurrence and fulfillment

01:34:34.980 --> 01:34:38.820 align:middle line:84%
of bliss is so low in
humanity at this point--

01:34:38.820 --> 01:34:42.120 align:middle line:84%
and it just is what it
is; we are where we are--

01:34:42.120 --> 01:34:46.267 align:middle line:90%
is that we're shamed.

01:34:46.267 --> 01:34:48.600 align:middle line:84%
We're taught that if you look
at this, if you have this,

01:34:48.600 --> 01:34:49.975 align:middle line:84%
there's something
wrong with you.

01:34:49.975 --> 01:34:54.300 align:middle line:84%
There's something wrong-- we
come from seven generations

01:34:54.300 --> 01:34:56.460 align:middle line:90%
of bankers and lawyers.

01:34:56.460 --> 01:35:01.050 align:middle line:84%
Where did you come from,
this guitar-playing musician?

01:35:01.050 --> 01:35:03.640 align:middle line:90%


01:35:03.640 --> 01:35:04.680 align:middle line:90%
Are you even my son?

01:35:04.680 --> 01:35:07.440 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you look like
me, but I don't know.

01:35:07.440 --> 01:35:10.200 align:middle line:84%
What that's hiding
is there were also

01:35:10.200 --> 01:35:12.000 align:middle line:90%
seven generations of musicians.

01:35:12.000 --> 01:35:16.215 align:middle line:90%


01:35:16.215 --> 01:35:18.090 align:middle line:84%
We just don't talk about
that, and you're not

01:35:18.090 --> 01:35:19.340 align:middle line:90%
going to talk about it either.

01:35:19.340 --> 01:35:22.080 align:middle line:90%


01:35:22.080 --> 01:35:27.587 align:middle line:84%
So basically, we're taught
that if we have this bliss,

01:35:27.587 --> 01:35:28.920 align:middle line:90%
there's something wrong with us.

01:35:28.920 --> 01:35:29.720 align:middle line:90%
We will lose love.

01:35:29.720 --> 01:35:32.570 align:middle line:84%
There's all this
fear surrounding it,

01:35:32.570 --> 01:35:37.370 align:middle line:84%
so that we don't even look
at the sight of the wound

01:35:37.370 --> 01:35:41.190 align:middle line:84%
or area in question, what was
exiled, what was pushed off.

01:35:41.190 --> 01:35:44.030 align:middle line:90%
And that's 99% of the problem.

01:35:44.030 --> 01:35:49.860 align:middle line:84%
And the metaphor I always
use is, even a paper cut,

01:35:49.860 --> 01:35:53.880 align:middle line:84%
if you don't attend to it, and
let it get infected and fester,

01:35:53.880 --> 01:35:55.560 align:middle line:90%
even a paper cut can kill you.

01:35:55.560 --> 01:35:58.290 align:middle line:90%


01:35:58.290 --> 01:36:00.120 align:middle line:84%
It's like the
saying, the cover-up

01:36:00.120 --> 01:36:02.080 align:middle line:90%
is worse than the crime.

01:36:02.080 --> 01:36:05.250 align:middle line:84%
If the original thing was just
a paper cut, just look at it.

01:36:05.250 --> 01:36:06.915 align:middle line:90%
It's a little uncomfortable.

01:36:06.915 --> 01:36:08.040 align:middle line:90%
Put the right things on it.

01:36:08.040 --> 01:36:11.190 align:middle line:84%
Give it some air and light, and
it will just heal on its own.

01:36:11.190 --> 01:36:14.010 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, oh, I can make
gobs of money and do my bliss.

01:36:14.010 --> 01:36:16.923 align:middle line:90%
Haha, let's just do this.

01:36:16.923 --> 01:36:18.340 align:middle line:84%
Why didn't I think
of this before?

01:36:18.340 --> 01:36:19.620 align:middle line:84%
It's like, OK,
bully, sit back down.

01:36:19.620 --> 01:36:20.420 align:middle line:90%
OK, sorry, sorry.

01:36:20.420 --> 01:36:21.700 align:middle line:90%
Let's just keep going.

01:36:21.700 --> 01:36:22.500 align:middle line:90%
Just keep going.

01:36:22.500 --> 01:36:23.300 align:middle line:90%
It's the feast.

01:36:23.300 --> 01:36:25.980 align:middle line:84%
All you can eat,
just keep eating.

01:36:25.980 --> 01:36:27.540 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes it's a bigger wound.

01:36:27.540 --> 01:36:29.610 align:middle line:84%
But that just needs a
little bit more stitching.

01:36:29.610 --> 01:36:34.980 align:middle line:84%
We have miles of thread,
suture, and needles.

01:36:34.980 --> 01:36:38.550 align:middle line:84%
It's the fear of looking at it
that makes even the smallest

01:36:38.550 --> 01:36:42.840 align:middle line:84%
incompatibilities flare up
into life and bliss and meaning

01:36:42.840 --> 01:36:48.960 align:middle line:84%
and purpose of life,
threatening conflagrations,

01:36:48.960 --> 01:36:49.890 align:middle line:90%
if that makes sense.

01:36:49.890 --> 01:36:52.470 align:middle line:90%


01:36:52.470 --> 01:36:55.733 align:middle line:84%
>> It is something
that we don't look at.

01:36:55.733 --> 01:36:57.150 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sure if
you speak to this,

01:36:57.150 --> 01:36:59.170 align:middle line:90%
but I think it is interesting.

01:36:59.170 --> 01:37:03.170 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people have this
sense of lack of self-worth,

01:37:03.170 --> 01:37:07.290 align:middle line:84%
a lack of self-love
from abandonment issues

01:37:07.290 --> 01:37:11.580 align:middle line:84%
or actually being abandoned,
or something significant

01:37:11.580 --> 01:37:13.470 align:middle line:90%
happening to them.

01:37:13.470 --> 01:37:17.550 align:middle line:84%
In that instance, do you
recommend a similar process

01:37:17.550 --> 01:37:20.520 align:middle line:84%
of analysis around it, like
going through and finding out,

01:37:20.520 --> 01:37:21.790 align:middle line:90%
well, that's my core wound.

01:37:21.790 --> 01:37:22.590 align:middle line:90%
OK, that's great.

01:37:22.590 --> 01:37:26.550 align:middle line:84%
And then how can I attend to
that on a needs by needs basis?

01:37:26.550 --> 01:37:28.220 align:middle line:90%
How do you approach that?

01:37:28.220 --> 01:37:29.100 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

01:37:29.100 --> 01:37:33.130 align:middle line:90%


01:37:33.130 --> 01:37:34.960 align:middle line:84%
So one of the
things I tell people

01:37:34.960 --> 01:37:39.700 align:middle line:84%
is that the nature of what
I do, even in healing,

01:37:39.700 --> 01:37:40.990 align:middle line:90%
is just general advising.

01:37:40.990 --> 01:37:42.150 align:middle line:90%
It's not medical.

01:37:42.150 --> 01:37:44.000 align:middle line:90%
It's not any of that.

01:37:44.000 --> 01:37:47.230 align:middle line:84%
And often people will
say, after they've

01:37:47.230 --> 01:37:49.120 align:middle line:84%
done some of these
exercises, they're like,

01:37:49.120 --> 01:37:53.890 align:middle line:84%
I think I understand now
what therapy is meant to do.

01:37:53.890 --> 01:37:55.690 align:middle line:84%
And I think I want
to go to therapy.

01:37:55.690 --> 01:37:57.670 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, that's awesome.

01:37:57.670 --> 01:37:59.170 align:middle line:90%
Go do that.

01:37:59.170 --> 01:38:02.280 align:middle line:84%
And I'll give them some pointers
around, it's like speed-dating.

01:38:02.280 --> 01:38:04.960 align:middle line:84%
You need to try a
lot of different ones

01:38:04.960 --> 01:38:06.560 align:middle line:90%
to find the right chemistry.

01:38:06.560 --> 01:38:09.093 align:middle line:84%
So if the first therapist
you meet is like judgey

01:38:09.093 --> 01:38:11.260 align:middle line:84%
and you don't feel comfortable
with them, that's OK.

01:38:11.260 --> 01:38:11.890 align:middle line:90%
Keep going.

01:38:11.890 --> 01:38:12.690 align:middle line:90%
Keep looking.

01:38:12.690 --> 01:38:20.240 align:middle line:90%


01:38:20.240 --> 01:38:22.040 align:middle line:84%
So what I do is just
general advising

01:38:22.040 --> 01:38:25.890 align:middle line:84%
to give a different kind
of perspective on that.

01:38:25.890 --> 01:38:28.580 align:middle line:84%
And in the framework of lost
board members and things

01:38:28.580 --> 01:38:32.810 align:middle line:84%
like that, the way I
tend to think about it

01:38:32.810 --> 01:38:39.800 align:middle line:84%
is that when a traumatic
event happens--

01:38:39.800 --> 01:38:43.910 align:middle line:84%
at any point in life, but
especially in early life--

01:38:43.910 --> 01:38:47.050 align:middle line:90%


01:38:47.050 --> 01:38:51.370 align:middle line:84%
the key thing that is
the wound, to me, that

01:38:51.370 --> 01:38:55.900 align:middle line:84%
is the aspect that
is of most interest

01:38:55.900 --> 01:38:59.590 align:middle line:84%
to me and the advising work that
I do to get you back on track

01:38:59.590 --> 01:39:05.050 align:middle line:84%
to your bliss, is
the narrative that

01:39:05.050 --> 01:39:12.070 align:middle line:84%
emerges around this
thing that happens, where

01:39:12.070 --> 01:39:15.270 align:middle line:84%
any human being of any
age, their natural reaction

01:39:15.270 --> 01:39:17.330 align:middle line:90%
is like, what the hell was that?

01:39:17.330 --> 01:39:18.730 align:middle line:90%
What the hell just happened?

01:39:18.730 --> 01:39:21.250 align:middle line:90%


01:39:21.250 --> 01:39:26.280 align:middle line:84%
So as a child, it could be
an event that you witness.

01:39:26.280 --> 01:39:30.637 align:middle line:84%
It could be a trauma, an assault
that you are the victim of.

01:39:30.637 --> 01:39:32.470 align:middle line:84%
It could be just something
bad that happens.

01:39:32.470 --> 01:39:35.320 align:middle line:84%
You're a villager, and a
hurricane comes and destroys

01:39:35.320 --> 01:39:36.130 align:middle line:90%
the entire village.

01:39:36.130 --> 01:39:40.870 align:middle line:90%


01:39:40.870 --> 01:39:45.310 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's examples I'm
thinking of where, in one case,

01:39:45.310 --> 01:39:48.070 align:middle line:84%
the traumatic event
for an advisee of mine

01:39:48.070 --> 01:39:50.630 align:middle line:84%
was the fact that
at three years old--

01:39:50.630 --> 01:39:53.200 align:middle line:84%
and he didn't remember any of
this-- but at three years old,

01:39:53.200 --> 01:39:54.880 align:middle line:84%
he had to move
across the Atlantic

01:39:54.880 --> 01:39:57.880 align:middle line:84%
from Britain to
the United States

01:39:57.880 --> 01:39:59.230 align:middle line:90%
and was separated from a parent.

01:39:59.230 --> 01:40:02.020 align:middle line:84%
It was just two careers, and
they were working it out.

01:40:02.020 --> 01:40:05.982 align:middle line:84%
But that for him was
the traumatic event.

01:40:05.982 --> 01:40:07.690 align:middle line:84%
Even though he had no
recollection of it,

01:40:07.690 --> 01:40:09.065 align:middle line:84%
it was the narrative
that grew up

01:40:09.065 --> 01:40:15.230 align:middle line:84%
around this that became
the source of the wound.

01:40:15.230 --> 01:40:17.840 align:middle line:90%
And he didn't remember it.

01:40:17.840 --> 01:40:18.640 align:middle line:90%
It was a narrative.

01:40:18.640 --> 01:40:20.740 align:middle line:84%
But the narrative itself
was just as powerful.

01:40:20.740 --> 01:40:23.620 align:middle line:90%


01:40:23.620 --> 01:40:29.410 align:middle line:84%
Another example is a
man who, when he was 13,

01:40:29.410 --> 01:40:31.930 align:middle line:90%
his mother committed suicide.

01:40:31.930 --> 01:40:37.000 align:middle line:84%
And the day before,
she had asked

01:40:37.000 --> 01:40:43.000 align:middle line:84%
him to show him how to use the
gun that she then the next day

01:40:43.000 --> 01:40:44.530 align:middle line:90%
used to commit suicide.

01:40:44.530 --> 01:40:48.346 align:middle line:90%


01:40:48.346 --> 01:40:55.900 align:middle line:84%
He was a gun owner, a competent
marksman trained by his father.

01:40:55.900 --> 01:41:00.400 align:middle line:84%
And at 13, he bore
the burden of that.

01:41:00.400 --> 01:41:04.600 align:middle line:84%
All of the sort of power
and energy around that event

01:41:04.600 --> 01:41:08.540 align:middle line:84%
was in the narrative that
grows up around that,

01:41:08.540 --> 01:41:11.372 align:middle line:90%
where it's like, my mom--

01:41:11.372 --> 01:41:13.330 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can come up
with an infinite number

01:41:13.330 --> 01:41:14.920 align:middle line:90%
of permutations.

01:41:14.920 --> 01:41:18.510 align:middle line:84%
But on one extreme, you
could say, I was just 13.

01:41:18.510 --> 01:41:20.620 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know any better.

01:41:20.620 --> 01:41:24.010 align:middle line:84%
Your mom tells you to show her
how to work the can opener,

01:41:24.010 --> 01:41:26.482 align:middle line:90%
you do it.

01:41:26.482 --> 01:41:28.690 align:middle line:84%
You're a good son, your mom
loves you and everything,

01:41:28.690 --> 01:41:32.640 align:middle line:84%
as opposed to like,
I helped kill my mom.

01:41:32.640 --> 01:41:33.440 align:middle line:90%
That was me.

01:41:33.440 --> 01:41:34.360 align:middle line:90%
I'm a bad person.

01:41:34.360 --> 01:41:35.950 align:middle line:90%
There's something wrong with me.

01:41:35.950 --> 01:41:37.480 align:middle line:90%
I'm too gullible.

01:41:37.480 --> 01:41:40.960 align:middle line:84%
I'm too stupid, and I'm
not looking out for things

01:41:40.960 --> 01:41:43.220 align:middle line:90%
that I need to be aware of.

01:41:43.220 --> 01:41:45.250 align:middle line:90%
And so for me--

01:41:45.250 --> 01:41:48.370 align:middle line:84%
>> So really, to add to this,
because this is interesting,

01:41:48.370 --> 01:41:50.190 align:middle line:90%
narrative is meaning, right?

01:41:50.190 --> 01:41:51.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

01:41:51.080 --> 01:41:54.618 align:middle line:84%
>> So we're appending a
meaning to a situation,

01:41:54.618 --> 01:41:55.660 align:middle line:90%
whether it's true or not.

01:41:55.660 --> 01:41:56.830 align:middle line:84%
And then we live
our lives by that.

01:41:56.830 --> 01:41:57.630 align:middle line:90%
Is that correct?

01:41:57.630 --> 01:41:59.450 align:middle line:84%
Can you connect the
meaning/narrative thing

01:41:59.450 --> 01:42:00.250 align:middle line:90%
together?

01:42:00.250 --> 01:42:04.370 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, from the perspective
of the board of directors,

01:42:04.370 --> 01:42:05.170 align:middle line:90%
that's your intel.

01:42:05.170 --> 01:42:07.947 align:middle line:90%


01:42:07.947 --> 01:42:09.280 align:middle line:90%
So we're the board of directors.

01:42:09.280 --> 01:42:11.830 align:middle line:84%
We will defend, hell
or high water, you,

01:42:11.830 --> 01:42:16.210 align:middle line:84%
your path in life, your safety,
security, your prestige--

01:42:16.210 --> 01:42:19.900 align:middle line:90%
all of the Maslow kind of--

01:42:19.900 --> 01:42:21.530 align:middle line:90%
survival, security.

01:42:21.530 --> 01:42:22.330 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

01:42:22.330 --> 01:42:24.670 align:middle line:84%
Relationships,
prestige, and some form

01:42:24.670 --> 01:42:26.483 align:middle line:90%
of personal development.

01:42:26.483 --> 01:42:28.900 align:middle line:84%
We're going to take care of
all those basic needs for you,

01:42:28.900 --> 01:42:30.800 align:middle line:90%
no matter what.

01:42:30.800 --> 01:42:32.450 align:middle line:84%
And now we're
scanning the horizon.

01:42:32.450 --> 01:42:34.840 align:middle line:84%
Oh, this huge
mushroom cloud just

01:42:34.840 --> 01:42:39.130 align:middle line:84%
went off over there in the
form of some traumatic event.

01:42:39.130 --> 01:42:41.260 align:middle line:90%
That impacts us.

01:42:41.260 --> 01:42:44.050 align:middle line:84%
And we need to
understand, we need

01:42:44.050 --> 01:42:48.560 align:middle line:84%
to come up with a narrative
of what the hell happened,

01:42:48.560 --> 01:42:51.020 align:middle line:84%
why it happened, and
what our role was

01:42:51.020 --> 01:42:54.850 align:middle line:84%
in it to make sure we come
up with a contingency plan

01:42:54.850 --> 01:42:58.900 align:middle line:84%
to make sure that shit
never happens again.

01:42:58.900 --> 01:43:01.920 align:middle line:90%
That's the job of the board.

01:43:01.920 --> 01:43:05.350 align:middle line:84%
Economic recession-- that's
definitely bad for us.

01:43:05.350 --> 01:43:07.463 align:middle line:84%
How do we make sure
we don't contribute

01:43:07.463 --> 01:43:08.380 align:middle line:90%
to the next recession?

01:43:08.380 --> 01:43:09.090 align:middle line:90%
It's absurd.

01:43:09.090 --> 01:43:10.070 align:middle line:90%
You have no control over it.

01:43:10.070 --> 01:43:12.290 align:middle line:84%
But it's like, maybe we'll
consult with the president

01:43:12.290 --> 01:43:14.260 align:middle line:84%
and put our cronies
in Congress and make

01:43:14.260 --> 01:43:16.420 align:middle line:84%
sure they pass the
right laws to make

01:43:16.420 --> 01:43:19.130 align:middle line:90%
sure this never happens again.

01:43:19.130 --> 01:43:26.020 align:middle line:84%
So narrative becomes
the intel by which

01:43:26.020 --> 01:43:29.110 align:middle line:84%
the board runs your
company and navigates

01:43:29.110 --> 01:43:30.900 align:middle line:90%
the path of your life.

01:43:30.900 --> 01:43:32.830 align:middle line:84%
And this is a human
phenomenon, right?

01:43:32.830 --> 01:43:36.610 align:middle line:90%
So forget about children.

01:43:36.610 --> 01:43:40.920 align:middle line:84%
Grown adults,
members of a tribe--

01:43:40.920 --> 01:43:45.750 align:middle line:84%
a hurricane comes by twice a
year and wipes out the village.

01:43:45.750 --> 01:43:48.760 align:middle line:84%
If you and I are in that
village, how would we react?

01:43:48.760 --> 01:43:49.560 align:middle line:90%
Oh yeah, whatever.

01:43:49.560 --> 01:43:51.260 align:middle line:90%
That happens every six months.

01:43:51.260 --> 01:43:52.060 align:middle line:90%
No big deal.

01:43:52.060 --> 01:43:53.352 align:middle line:90%
Let's just rebuild the village.

01:43:53.352 --> 01:43:54.840 align:middle line:90%
Hell no.

01:43:54.840 --> 01:43:58.620 align:middle line:84%
We're like, we have to
come up with a narrative.

01:43:58.620 --> 01:44:00.030 align:middle line:90%
The gods are angry with us.

01:44:00.030 --> 01:44:01.710 align:middle line:90%
We need to sacrifice more.

01:44:01.710 --> 01:44:05.160 align:middle line:84%
The next village's
shaman did a thing on us.

01:44:05.160 --> 01:44:07.800 align:middle line:90%
We gotta go take care of him.

01:44:07.800 --> 01:44:10.610 align:middle line:84%
We must come up
with a narrative,

01:44:10.610 --> 01:44:15.990 align:middle line:84%
because in the absence of that
narrative we have no control.

01:44:15.990 --> 01:44:18.340 align:middle line:84%
If we have no control,
we're unshielded.

01:44:18.340 --> 01:44:21.090 align:middle line:84%
We're unsoothed,
and a lightning bolt

01:44:21.090 --> 01:44:23.090 align:middle line:84%
can hit us at any time--
which is actually true.

01:44:23.090 --> 01:44:24.600 align:middle line:84%
A lightning bolt can
hit you at any time.

01:44:24.600 --> 01:44:26.225 align:middle line:84%
But we come up with
a narrative saying,

01:44:26.225 --> 01:44:29.580 align:middle line:84%
oh, it's more dangerous riding
in your car, so don't worry.

01:44:29.580 --> 01:44:31.500 align:middle line:84%
Even lightning bolt,
which will never happen,

01:44:31.500 --> 01:44:32.958 align:middle line:84%
we have to come up
with a narrative

01:44:32.958 --> 01:44:34.573 align:middle line:90%
to soothe and shield ourselves.

01:44:34.573 --> 01:44:35.490 align:middle line:90%
This is a human thing.

01:44:35.490 --> 01:44:37.290 align:middle line:90%
Similarly then, as a child--

01:44:37.290 --> 01:44:40.260 align:middle line:90%


01:44:40.260 --> 01:44:44.100 align:middle line:84%
as a child, you're
also not stupid.

01:44:44.100 --> 01:44:46.980 align:middle line:84%
Parents are all the time
like, I don't get how

01:44:46.980 --> 01:44:48.280 align:middle line:90%
my kid understands all this.

01:44:48.280 --> 01:44:49.340 align:middle line:90%
You're explaining this to me.

01:44:49.340 --> 01:44:50.140 align:middle line:90%
I was like, no way.

01:44:50.140 --> 01:44:53.000 align:middle line:84%
And then I tell them, you're
loved unconditionally,

01:44:53.000 --> 01:44:54.750 align:middle line:84%
and they understand,
and they brighten up,

01:44:54.750 --> 01:44:56.570 align:middle line:84%
and all these things
just fall away.

01:44:56.570 --> 01:44:57.570 align:middle line:90%
I don't even understand.

01:44:57.570 --> 01:44:59.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, dude, he's your kid.

01:44:59.730 --> 01:45:01.410 align:middle line:90%
Did you go to Princeton or what?

01:45:01.410 --> 01:45:06.780 align:middle line:84%
He is smart like
you, and it's OK.

01:45:06.780 --> 01:45:08.610 align:middle line:84%
So kids are going
to be like this too.

01:45:08.610 --> 01:45:11.880 align:middle line:84%
And when something bad
happens in their life--

01:45:11.880 --> 01:45:15.210 align:middle line:84%
my mom commits suicide, I
get moved across the Atlantic

01:45:15.210 --> 01:45:18.060 align:middle line:90%
against my will--

01:45:18.060 --> 01:45:21.240 align:middle line:84%
they can't just take it
as a random occurrence.

01:45:21.240 --> 01:45:24.060 align:middle line:90%
It's too frightening.

01:45:24.060 --> 01:45:27.120 align:middle line:84%
They have to come
up with a narrative.

01:45:27.120 --> 01:45:31.500 align:middle line:84%
And in my experience, my kind
of unprofessional observation

01:45:31.500 --> 01:45:34.890 align:middle line:84%
of these things,
what I notice is

01:45:34.890 --> 01:45:36.900 align:middle line:84%
that the narrative
that a child comes up

01:45:36.900 --> 01:45:40.470 align:middle line:84%
with in the absence of
guidance from the elder

01:45:40.470 --> 01:45:44.100 align:middle line:90%
is almost always self-negative.

01:45:44.100 --> 01:45:47.850 align:middle line:84%
And when I've talked actually
to children and I've talked

01:45:47.850 --> 01:45:51.240 align:middle line:84%
to grown-ups and asked them
why they came up with that

01:45:51.240 --> 01:45:53.940 align:middle line:84%
narrative when
they were children,

01:45:53.940 --> 01:46:01.450 align:middle line:84%
what I've pieced together
is that if there is a choice

01:46:01.450 --> 01:46:06.490 align:middle line:84%
between a narrative where I had
no control versus I had some

01:46:06.490 --> 01:46:11.770 align:middle line:84%
control, I will always-- because
I'm smart and I'm capable

01:46:11.770 --> 01:46:15.070 align:middle line:84%
intrinsically, because
I'm not an idiot--

01:46:15.070 --> 01:46:18.010 align:middle line:84%
I will always skew
toward the narrative that

01:46:18.010 --> 01:46:21.340 align:middle line:90%
put more control in my hands.

01:46:21.340 --> 01:46:24.250 align:middle line:84%
And the reason I prefer that is
because it gives me something

01:46:24.250 --> 01:46:31.180 align:middle line:84%
to do to make me feel like I'm
preventing the next occurrence.

01:46:31.180 --> 01:46:33.250 align:middle line:84%
Even if it's rubbing
my lucky rabbit's foot

01:46:33.250 --> 01:46:36.580 align:middle line:84%
or putting baby powder
on my hockey stick,

01:46:36.580 --> 01:46:38.560 align:middle line:84%
I need something to
do to feel like I'm

01:46:38.560 --> 01:46:40.102 align:middle line:90%
at least doing something.

01:46:40.102 --> 01:46:43.040 align:middle line:90%


01:46:43.040 --> 01:46:46.000 align:middle line:84%
Even if you're like, well, it's
not true, it doesn't matter.

01:46:46.000 --> 01:46:48.190 align:middle line:84%
Given the choice between,
yeah, can't do anything.

01:46:48.190 --> 01:46:48.990 align:middle line:90%
Could happen again.

01:46:48.990 --> 01:46:51.358 align:middle line:84%
Any minute, you could be
eating your chocolate pudding

01:46:51.358 --> 01:46:52.400 align:middle line:90%
and it could just happen.

01:46:52.400 --> 01:46:53.260 align:middle line:90%
It's like, fuck, OK.

01:46:53.260 --> 01:46:54.888 align:middle line:84%
That's not the world
I want to live in.

01:46:54.888 --> 01:46:57.430 align:middle line:84%
I want to live in a world where
I can do something to prevent

01:46:57.430 --> 01:46:59.590 align:middle line:90%
these things from happening.

01:46:59.590 --> 01:47:01.120 align:middle line:90%
I will choose that.

01:47:01.120 --> 01:47:03.430 align:middle line:90%
And in these bad instances--

01:47:03.430 --> 01:47:05.590 align:middle line:84%
the kid whose mom
killed themself

01:47:05.590 --> 01:47:08.410 align:middle line:84%
with the gun he showed
her how to use--

01:47:08.410 --> 01:47:10.690 align:middle line:84%
what is the narrative
where he has control,

01:47:10.690 --> 01:47:13.630 align:middle line:84%
where it's like, no, I was just
this helpless kid and my mom

01:47:13.630 --> 01:47:15.645 align:middle line:90%
like--

01:47:15.645 --> 01:47:17.770 align:middle line:84%
there's a lot of things my
mom shouldn't have done.

01:47:17.770 --> 01:47:21.130 align:middle line:84%
But one of the things is that
she shouldn't have used me

01:47:21.130 --> 01:47:22.360 align:middle line:90%
as a means to helping her.

01:47:22.360 --> 01:47:25.067 align:middle line:90%


01:47:25.067 --> 01:47:25.900 align:middle line:90%
Putting that on her.

01:47:25.900 --> 01:47:30.493 align:middle line:84%
Or putting it on me, it's
like, if I had paid attention,

01:47:30.493 --> 01:47:32.910 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't have shown her and
I would have gone to my dad.

01:47:32.910 --> 01:47:36.310 align:middle line:90%


01:47:36.310 --> 01:47:38.590 align:middle line:84%
And the reason why a kid,
in the absence of guidance,

01:47:38.590 --> 01:47:42.010 align:middle line:84%
will pick that is because it
gives his board of directors

01:47:42.010 --> 01:47:45.070 align:middle line:84%
something to do to
prevent the next one.

01:47:45.070 --> 01:47:51.250 align:middle line:84%
Now, the very painful and
damaging byproduct of that

01:47:51.250 --> 01:47:55.720 align:middle line:84%
is that it puts
the blame on him,

01:47:55.720 --> 01:47:59.870 align:middle line:84%
because the price of
control is responsibility.

01:47:59.870 --> 01:48:02.605 align:middle line:84%
So to protect myself, I'm
going to take on the narrative

01:48:02.605 --> 01:48:03.480 align:middle line:90%
where I have control.

01:48:03.480 --> 01:48:08.230 align:middle line:84%
Then it's like, fucking
it was partly my fault.

01:48:08.230 --> 01:48:11.890 align:middle line:90%
And then that is a wound.

01:48:11.890 --> 01:48:17.600 align:middle line:84%
Because if I caused that, then
there's something in my board.

01:48:17.600 --> 01:48:22.780 align:middle line:84%
And in that case, it might be
inattentiveness, incompetence,

01:48:22.780 --> 01:48:28.030 align:middle line:90%
non-vigilance, gullibility.

01:48:28.030 --> 01:48:31.270 align:middle line:84%
Those board members will
all get shunted down

01:48:31.270 --> 01:48:36.000 align:middle line:84%
to the lowest level of
Guantanamo prison, right?

01:48:36.000 --> 01:48:40.180 align:middle line:90%
And not unreasonably.

01:48:40.180 --> 01:48:44.650 align:middle line:84%
And that boy's compass
will be calibrated 15%

01:48:44.650 --> 01:48:47.380 align:middle line:84%
or whatever it is, and he'll go
through life until he's like,

01:48:47.380 --> 01:48:52.300 align:middle line:84%
I'm nowhere near where I need
to be and I don't even know why.

01:48:52.300 --> 01:48:55.600 align:middle line:90%


01:48:55.600 --> 01:48:58.195 align:middle line:84%
So for me, even
traumatic events--

01:48:58.195 --> 01:49:02.530 align:middle line:90%


01:49:02.530 --> 01:49:05.500 align:middle line:84%
if there's trauma,
narrative absolutely

01:49:05.500 --> 01:49:09.887 align:middle line:84%
has to rise up around that,
because you can't ignore it.

01:49:09.887 --> 01:49:12.220 align:middle line:84%
This Eiffel Tower emerges out
of the ground next to you.

01:49:12.220 --> 01:49:15.940 align:middle line:84%
You have to talk about it
and explain it somehow.

01:49:15.940 --> 01:49:19.210 align:middle line:84%
But in the absence
of trauma, you

01:49:19.210 --> 01:49:21.480 align:middle line:84%
don't need a trauma to come
up with your narrative.

01:49:21.480 --> 01:49:23.410 align:middle line:90%
It's like, put this mask on.

01:49:23.410 --> 01:49:25.300 align:middle line:90%
No, James, put it back on.

01:49:25.300 --> 01:49:27.290 align:middle line:90%
No, I can see it's off.

01:49:27.290 --> 01:49:28.590 align:middle line:90%
Put it back on.

01:49:28.590 --> 01:49:31.660 align:middle line:90%
Cut your hair.

01:49:31.660 --> 01:49:34.003 align:middle line:84%
And you're trying all--
and it's like, oh, fine.

01:49:34.003 --> 01:49:35.920 align:middle line:84%
And then a narrative
will come up right there.

01:49:35.920 --> 01:49:40.360 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't have to be trauma,
but trauma is definitely

01:49:40.360 --> 01:49:46.120 align:middle line:84%
an exceptional case in my
travels what I've seen.

01:49:46.120 --> 01:49:48.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Interesting.

01:49:48.340 --> 01:49:51.100 align:middle line:84%
There are a few other things
I want to speak to at the end

01:49:51.100 --> 01:49:56.440 align:middle line:84%
here, which is sort of
really about wrapping up

01:49:56.440 --> 01:49:58.390 align:middle line:84%
vision, mission, next
step, because we've

01:49:58.390 --> 01:50:00.070 align:middle line:90%
covered a lot of time here.

01:50:00.070 --> 01:50:01.600 align:middle line:84%
So I want to be
respectful of that.

01:50:01.600 --> 01:50:04.870 align:middle line:84%
And you touched on this a
little bit at the start.

01:50:04.870 --> 01:50:06.220 align:middle line:90%
How do we solve this problem?

01:50:06.220 --> 01:50:07.300 align:middle line:90%
I hear these stories.

01:50:07.300 --> 01:50:08.740 align:middle line:90%
I speak with parenting experts.

01:50:08.740 --> 01:50:11.260 align:middle line:84%
I speak with psychologists,
psychiatrists.

01:50:11.260 --> 01:50:13.030 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, oh my goodness.

01:50:13.030 --> 01:50:15.190 align:middle line:84%
We just need to become
conscious parents

01:50:15.190 --> 01:50:18.580 align:middle line:84%
and raise children that don't
have any lack of self-worth.

01:50:18.580 --> 01:50:20.260 align:middle line:84%
But then you can't
always do that,

01:50:20.260 --> 01:50:22.120 align:middle line:84%
because they come up
with their own reasons

01:50:22.120 --> 01:50:23.990 align:middle line:84%
to find a lack of
self-worth, right?

01:50:23.990 --> 01:50:24.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

01:50:24.790 --> 01:50:27.415 align:middle line:84%
>> But then there's meditation,
which you can quiet the chatter

01:50:27.415 --> 01:50:31.210 align:middle line:84%
and start to tap into that more
internal wellspring of peace,

01:50:31.210 --> 01:50:33.490 align:middle line:84%
love, and energy that
resides within all of us,

01:50:33.490 --> 01:50:35.350 align:middle line:84%
which is more of the
spiritual ideology.

01:50:35.350 --> 01:50:38.652 align:middle line:84%
So speaking to all of
this, in your opinion--

01:50:38.652 --> 01:50:41.110 align:middle line:84%
and I'm not going to ask for
a professional opinion or this

01:50:41.110 --> 01:50:41.260 align:middle line:90%
or that.

01:50:41.260 --> 01:50:42.760 align:middle line:84%
Just in your
experience and opinion,

01:50:42.760 --> 01:50:47.200 align:middle line:84%
how do you think we start
to evolve as a species

01:50:47.200 --> 01:50:49.840 align:middle line:84%
to really go, oh,
actually, I am pure love.

01:50:49.840 --> 01:50:50.740 align:middle line:90%
I am pure light.

01:50:50.740 --> 01:50:52.960 align:middle line:84%
I am divinity, as
is everybody else.

01:50:52.960 --> 01:50:55.360 align:middle line:84%
And in that knowledge,
we can start

01:50:55.360 --> 01:50:57.580 align:middle line:84%
to be more
compassionate to others

01:50:57.580 --> 01:50:59.680 align:middle line:84%
and help them to not
develop the wounds

01:50:59.680 --> 01:51:01.600 align:middle line:90%
that we've sort of carried?

01:51:01.600 --> 01:51:02.650 align:middle line:90%
Is that a possibility?

01:51:02.650 --> 01:51:03.920 align:middle line:90%
Is that your vision?

01:51:03.920 --> 01:51:05.890 align:middle line:84%
Or is it more of a
bliss-based ideology

01:51:05.890 --> 01:51:08.680 align:middle line:84%
where people move towards
bliss through meditation,

01:51:08.680 --> 01:51:10.850 align:middle line:84%
chanting, whatever it
is, and then they go,

01:51:10.850 --> 01:51:14.080 align:middle line:84%
oh my goodness, I can
be that person now?

01:51:14.080 --> 01:51:16.330 align:middle line:84%
How do you think we get out
of this mess, essentially,

01:51:16.330 --> 01:51:18.550 align:middle line:84%
and sort of
self-evolved to a place

01:51:18.550 --> 01:51:21.750 align:middle line:84%
where we can operate as better
quality humans on this planet?

01:51:21.750 --> 01:51:25.370 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm, thank you for that.

01:51:25.370 --> 01:51:32.860 align:middle line:84%
So for me, there's really
only one thing out of which

01:51:32.860 --> 01:51:36.550 align:middle line:90%
bliss itself will emerge.

01:51:36.550 --> 01:51:52.900 align:middle line:84%
And that is that sort of the
deeper and deeper understanding

01:51:52.900 --> 01:51:59.810 align:middle line:84%
that I as a person,
whoever you are--

01:51:59.810 --> 01:52:03.620 align:middle line:84%
it's not even that
I'm worthy of love.

01:52:03.620 --> 01:52:09.020 align:middle line:84%
I am actually loved without
condition, period, full stop.

01:52:09.020 --> 01:52:11.720 align:middle line:90%


01:52:11.720 --> 01:52:15.770 align:middle line:90%
There is no condition.

01:52:15.770 --> 01:52:21.540 align:middle line:84%
And that's the only switch
that needs to be flipped.

01:52:21.540 --> 01:52:25.100 align:middle line:84%
And the two things
I'll say with that

01:52:25.100 --> 01:52:27.440 align:middle line:84%
are an example of
what that means

01:52:27.440 --> 01:52:30.680 align:middle line:84%
to be loved unconditionally,
and then once you

01:52:30.680 --> 01:52:33.500 align:middle line:84%
have that, how that starts
to change things around you.

01:52:33.500 --> 01:52:37.370 align:middle line:90%


01:52:37.370 --> 01:52:40.790 align:middle line:84%
Many years ago when I was
walking with my daughter after

01:52:40.790 --> 01:52:45.418 align:middle line:84%
dinner, we would have this
habit of doing one-on-one walks

01:52:45.418 --> 01:52:46.960 align:middle line:84%
for like an hour or
two after dinner,

01:52:46.960 --> 01:52:49.542 align:middle line:84%
like three or four
times a week actually--

01:52:49.542 --> 01:52:53.590 align:middle line:90%


01:52:53.590 --> 01:52:56.860 align:middle line:84%
I would ask her these questions,
just to calibrate and see

01:52:56.860 --> 01:52:58.090 align:middle line:90%
where she was at.

01:52:58.090 --> 01:53:04.870 align:middle line:84%
And I would say, you get that
I love you without condition,

01:53:04.870 --> 01:53:05.670 align:middle line:90%
right?

01:53:05.670 --> 01:53:06.790 align:middle line:90%
She's like, yeah, dad, yeah.

01:53:06.790 --> 01:53:08.650 align:middle line:84%
Because my kids, they roll
their eyes at this stuff.

01:53:08.650 --> 01:53:09.525 align:middle line:90%
They hear it so much.

01:53:09.525 --> 01:53:11.950 align:middle line:90%


01:53:11.950 --> 01:53:14.680 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, so
I mean, you know

01:53:14.680 --> 01:53:19.840 align:middle line:84%
that that means if you get
straight F's on your report

01:53:19.840 --> 01:53:24.580 align:middle line:84%
card, you drop out of school
and you're a street person,

01:53:24.580 --> 01:53:27.775 align:middle line:90%
you don't lose any love.

01:53:27.775 --> 01:53:29.650 align:middle line:84%
I'm worried about your
safety and everything,

01:53:29.650 --> 01:53:31.810 align:middle line:90%
but you don't lose any love.

01:53:31.810 --> 01:53:34.395 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't matter if you fail.

01:53:34.395 --> 01:53:35.770 align:middle line:84%
And she's like,
yeah, I got that.

01:53:35.770 --> 01:53:36.570 align:middle line:90%
I got that.

01:53:36.570 --> 01:53:38.050 align:middle line:90%
I'm good.

01:53:38.050 --> 01:53:39.760 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, OK.

01:53:39.760 --> 01:53:46.150 align:middle line:84%
Well, do you get the converse,
where if you get straight A's--

01:53:46.150 --> 01:53:48.280 align:middle line:84%
ace everything, get into
all the best schools,

01:53:48.280 --> 01:53:51.070 align:middle line:90%
and win the Nobel Prize--

01:53:51.070 --> 01:53:52.420 align:middle line:90%
your stock price doesn't go up?

01:53:52.420 --> 01:53:55.000 align:middle line:84%
I don't love you any
more, because your love

01:53:55.000 --> 01:53:56.470 align:middle line:90%
is unconditional.

01:53:56.470 --> 01:54:01.690 align:middle line:84%
And she was like
[MIMICS EXPLOSION]

01:54:01.690 --> 01:54:03.730 align:middle line:90%
So it's like, yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:54:03.730 --> 01:54:10.780 align:middle line:84%
If you don't get into Harvard,
as an example, or Stanford,

01:54:10.780 --> 01:54:13.290 align:middle line:90%
you don't lose any love.

01:54:13.290 --> 01:54:17.100 align:middle line:84%
But if you do get in,
you don't gain any love,

01:54:17.100 --> 01:54:20.760 align:middle line:90%
because love is not conditional.

01:54:20.760 --> 01:54:21.960 align:middle line:90%
It's not a stock price.

01:54:21.960 --> 01:54:22.930 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't go down.

01:54:22.930 --> 01:54:25.320 align:middle line:90%
It also doesn't go up.

01:54:25.320 --> 01:54:28.670 align:middle line:90%
I already would die for you.

01:54:28.670 --> 01:54:31.680 align:middle line:90%
It's maxed without condition.

01:54:31.680 --> 01:54:33.852 align:middle line:90%
Similarly, I'll ask my son.

01:54:33.852 --> 01:54:36.060 align:middle line:84%
I'll ask him every now and
then still just for kicks.

01:54:36.060 --> 01:54:40.150 align:middle line:84%
But when he was younger, we
would be doing all this stuff

01:54:40.150 --> 01:54:40.950 align:middle line:90%
for him.

01:54:40.950 --> 01:54:42.040 align:middle line:90%
I'm basically his butler.

01:54:42.040 --> 01:54:43.420 align:middle line:84%
I'll cook for him
and everything.

01:54:43.420 --> 01:54:44.980 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, how you doing?

01:54:44.980 --> 01:54:45.780 align:middle line:90%
Do you feel loved?

01:54:45.780 --> 01:54:47.155 align:middle line:84%
He's like, oh
yeah, I feel loved.

01:54:47.155 --> 01:54:49.710 align:middle line:84%
He's eating his mac
and cheese or whatever.

01:54:49.710 --> 01:54:55.530 align:middle line:84%
And when he was younger, I would
say, I'm glad you feel loved.

01:54:55.530 --> 01:55:01.020 align:middle line:84%
So do you know what you
need to be doing in order

01:55:01.020 --> 01:55:05.430 align:middle line:90%
to continue having this love?

01:55:05.430 --> 01:55:08.710 align:middle line:90%
And he was like, what?

01:55:08.710 --> 01:55:12.780 align:middle line:90%
And I was like, nothing.

01:55:12.780 --> 01:55:14.930 align:middle line:90%
You don't earn your love.

01:55:14.930 --> 01:55:17.760 align:middle line:90%
You get it.

01:55:17.760 --> 01:55:21.540 align:middle line:84%
And a big smile cracked
across his face.

01:55:21.540 --> 01:55:24.180 align:middle line:84%
And now of course,
he's a teenager.

01:55:24.180 --> 01:55:26.938 align:middle line:84%
So when I even dare to voice
it, I'm like, do you know?

01:55:26.938 --> 01:55:27.980 align:middle line:90%
He's like, yeah, nothing.

01:55:27.980 --> 01:55:30.600 align:middle line:90%


01:55:30.600 --> 01:55:32.050 align:middle line:90%
Which is really annoying.

01:55:32.050 --> 01:55:37.050 align:middle line:84%
But that's exactly where
you want them to be.

01:55:37.050 --> 01:55:39.930 align:middle line:84%
So when you realize your
love is unconditional--

01:55:39.930 --> 01:55:44.100 align:middle line:84%
and when I teach, there's
like 50 different ways

01:55:44.100 --> 01:55:47.910 align:middle line:84%
of trying to reach in and flip
the switch within any given

01:55:47.910 --> 01:55:53.040 align:middle line:84%
advisee, because there's a lot
of defenses and countervailing

01:55:53.040 --> 01:55:55.380 align:middle line:84%
knowledge and
teaching and scripting

01:55:55.380 --> 01:55:57.360 align:middle line:84%
and conditioning
that's against that.

01:55:57.360 --> 01:56:00.265 align:middle line:84%
But once you can
reach in and kind of

01:56:00.265 --> 01:56:01.890 align:middle line:84%
help the person flip
that switch, where

01:56:01.890 --> 01:56:04.615 align:middle line:90%
they realize the reality--

01:56:04.615 --> 01:56:06.990 align:middle line:84%
or even where they're like,
oh my gosh, I'm out of ideas.

01:56:06.990 --> 01:56:08.240 align:middle line:90%
I'm just going to hurt myself.

01:56:08.240 --> 01:56:10.660 align:middle line:84%
Even that is out of a
misguided sense of self-love.

01:56:10.660 --> 01:56:14.620 align:middle line:90%


01:56:14.620 --> 01:56:17.950 align:middle line:90%
That's what that feels like.

01:56:17.950 --> 01:56:21.670 align:middle line:84%
And then from that
feeling, the way

01:56:21.670 --> 01:56:27.280 align:middle line:84%
that changes the physics
of your life is that--

01:56:27.280 --> 01:56:30.940 align:middle line:84%
I mean, a very
fundamental level,

01:56:30.940 --> 01:56:35.290 align:middle line:84%
you're, first of all,
not afraid of anything.

01:56:35.290 --> 01:56:37.690 align:middle line:84%
Because if I quit my job
and I don't make any money,

01:56:37.690 --> 01:56:40.520 align:middle line:84%
it means, well, I'm
making less money,

01:56:40.520 --> 01:56:42.790 align:middle line:84%
so I need to tighten my
belt. For most people,

01:56:42.790 --> 01:56:45.400 align:middle line:90%
it doesn't mean they'll starve.

01:56:45.400 --> 01:56:49.810 align:middle line:84%
And even if they do
starve, friends, family,

01:56:49.810 --> 01:56:51.640 align:middle line:84%
the government,
whatever-- typically,

01:56:51.640 --> 01:56:55.570 align:middle line:84%
there's a level of money below
which all the shame factors

01:56:55.570 --> 01:56:59.320 align:middle line:84%
and loss of love kick in, which
is way above what you actually

01:56:59.320 --> 01:57:01.620 align:middle line:90%
need to live and survive.

01:57:01.620 --> 01:57:02.500 align:middle line:90%
That delta is fine.

01:57:02.500 --> 01:57:04.310 align:middle line:84%
It's fine to have
that difference there.

01:57:04.310 --> 01:57:12.580 align:middle line:84%
But the key is that
the things you do out

01:57:12.580 --> 01:57:17.090 align:middle line:90%
of a fear of loss of love--

01:57:17.090 --> 01:57:19.250 align:middle line:84%
when you truly flip
the switch to say,

01:57:19.250 --> 01:57:22.810 align:middle line:84%
actually, it's not possible
for me to lose love--

01:57:22.810 --> 01:57:25.610 align:middle line:90%


01:57:25.610 --> 01:57:30.440 align:middle line:84%
all the things you were
doing based on that fear

01:57:30.440 --> 01:57:33.410 align:middle line:90%
instantly fall away.

01:57:33.410 --> 01:57:35.900 align:middle line:84%
And if we go back to
soothing and shielding,

01:57:35.900 --> 01:57:37.520 align:middle line:90%
let's just look at the list--

01:57:37.520 --> 01:57:42.500 align:middle line:84%
money and prestige,
perfectionism, anger,

01:57:42.500 --> 01:57:54.260 align:middle line:84%
invisibility, people-pleasing,
sex and drugs, shopping,

01:57:54.260 --> 01:57:58.610 align:middle line:84%
alcohol, unhealthy sex
and relationships--

01:57:58.610 --> 01:58:01.830 align:middle line:90%
all those things fall away.

01:58:01.830 --> 01:58:03.830 align:middle line:84%
Actually, at a business
school talk I was doing,

01:58:03.830 --> 01:58:08.210 align:middle line:84%
someone circled a number of the
items on soothing and shielding

01:58:08.210 --> 01:58:10.400 align:middle line:84%
and said, what I've
just circled constitutes

01:58:10.400 --> 01:58:15.710 align:middle line:84%
around 85% of US gross
domestic product.

01:58:15.710 --> 01:58:18.350 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, yeah,
and I'm OK with that.

01:58:18.350 --> 01:58:19.850 align:middle line:84%
I love the world
without condition.

01:58:19.850 --> 01:58:21.380 align:middle line:90%
I love it as it is.

01:58:21.380 --> 01:58:25.130 align:middle line:90%
I play the ball as it lies.

01:58:25.130 --> 01:58:27.800 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is,
because that's the case--

01:58:27.800 --> 01:58:30.350 align:middle line:90%
the world is driven by fear--

01:58:30.350 --> 01:58:32.723 align:middle line:84%
when you flip the switch
within yourself to realize,

01:58:32.723 --> 01:58:33.890 align:middle line:90%
actually, I can't lose love.

01:58:33.890 --> 01:58:35.932 align:middle line:84%
I can bang my head against
the wall all day long,

01:58:35.932 --> 01:58:38.870 align:middle line:90%
I can't lose love.

01:58:38.870 --> 01:58:42.653 align:middle line:84%
All the things you
were doing fall away,

01:58:42.653 --> 01:58:44.320 align:middle line:84%
because you were doing
that out of fear.

01:58:44.320 --> 01:58:48.190 align:middle line:84%
You realize, 80% of my life,
I'm doing things out of fear.

01:58:48.190 --> 01:58:52.532 align:middle line:84%
All those things fall away, and
then you shift into neutral.

01:58:52.532 --> 01:58:54.490 align:middle line:84%
There's typically a two-
or three-week period--

01:58:54.490 --> 01:58:58.720 align:middle line:84%
for some people longer,
which is delicious--

01:58:58.720 --> 01:59:02.530 align:middle line:84%
where they're sitting
there and they're like,

01:59:02.530 --> 01:59:04.810 align:middle line:90%
I'm not doing anything.

01:59:04.810 --> 01:59:06.630 align:middle line:90%
I've lost all motivation.

01:59:06.630 --> 01:59:11.700 align:middle line:84%
I'm going into work like Neo,
Keanu Reeves in "The Matrix."

01:59:11.700 --> 01:59:14.380 align:middle line:84%
He's, like, fighting
kung fu with one hand

01:59:14.380 --> 01:59:15.880 align:middle line:90%
and still pulling in the money.

01:59:15.880 --> 01:59:17.047 align:middle line:90%
He's still getting promoted.

01:59:17.047 --> 01:59:18.060 align:middle line:90%
Everything's fine.

01:59:18.060 --> 01:59:19.060 align:middle line:90%
He's not driven by fear.

01:59:19.060 --> 01:59:20.260 align:middle line:90%
He's just phoning it in.

01:59:20.260 --> 01:59:22.450 align:middle line:84%
And everyone still
gathers around him,

01:59:22.450 --> 01:59:24.324 align:middle line:84%
because there's this
weird light around him

01:59:24.324 --> 01:59:27.340 align:middle line:84%
now, because he's
impervious to fear.

01:59:27.340 --> 01:59:29.220 align:middle line:84%
And people smell that
and gather around you.

01:59:29.220 --> 01:59:32.260 align:middle line:90%


01:59:32.260 --> 01:59:36.180 align:middle line:84%
But they're like, it's like
I've lost all motivation.

01:59:36.180 --> 01:59:37.594 align:middle line:90%
And I'm just sitting here.

01:59:37.594 --> 01:59:40.370 align:middle line:84%
Everything's fine, and I
kind of don't give a shit.

01:59:40.370 --> 01:59:41.170 align:middle line:90%
Is this OK?

01:59:41.170 --> 01:59:42.090 align:middle line:90%
There's something wrong with me.

01:59:42.090 --> 01:59:43.048 align:middle line:90%
And of course, it's me.

01:59:43.048 --> 01:59:46.130 align:middle line:84%
So I'm like, no, there's
nothing wrong with you.

01:59:46.130 --> 01:59:50.950 align:middle line:84%
But what has happened is
you've lost your fear.

01:59:50.950 --> 01:59:53.860 align:middle line:84%
So all the things you were
doing motivated by the fear

01:59:53.860 --> 01:59:56.500 align:middle line:90%
have stopped dead in the water.

01:59:56.500 --> 02:00:00.340 align:middle line:90%
And voila, you're still alive.

02:00:00.340 --> 02:00:01.960 align:middle line:84%
People who love
you still love you.

02:00:01.960 --> 02:00:02.500 align:middle line:90%
Everything's fine.

02:00:02.500 --> 02:00:03.333 align:middle line:90%
You're not starving.

02:00:03.333 --> 02:00:04.970 align:middle line:84%
No one's come to
your rescue, yet.

02:00:04.970 --> 02:00:07.600 align:middle line:90%


02:00:07.600 --> 02:00:11.770 align:middle line:84%
And then, as you sit
there for long enough,

02:00:11.770 --> 02:00:15.880 align:middle line:84%
this other muscle will start to
flex that had previously been

02:00:15.880 --> 02:00:20.120 align:middle line:84%
quite atrophied, which is
not the muscle of fear,

02:00:20.120 --> 02:00:24.010 align:middle line:84%
which is very strong, but the
muscle of-- there are many

02:00:24.010 --> 02:00:24.810 align:middle line:90%
words--

02:00:24.810 --> 02:00:28.150 align:middle line:90%
desire, love, bliss, vision.

02:00:28.150 --> 02:00:32.740 align:middle line:90%


02:00:32.740 --> 02:00:37.600 align:middle line:84%
And you realize, it's not
that you have no motivation

02:00:37.600 --> 02:00:39.050 align:middle line:90%
to do anything.

02:00:39.050 --> 02:00:41.622 align:middle line:84%
It's just that all the usual
menu options in society

02:00:41.622 --> 02:00:42.580 align:middle line:90%
are all driven by fear.

02:00:42.580 --> 02:00:45.080 align:middle line:84%
And you're like, yeah, but I
don't have any fear, so I'm not

02:00:45.080 --> 02:00:46.600 align:middle line:90%
going to check that box.

02:00:46.600 --> 02:00:48.765 align:middle line:84%
I don't have any fear, I'm
fine with my body image.

02:00:48.765 --> 02:00:52.270 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to check that box.

02:00:52.270 --> 02:00:53.912 align:middle line:84%
And you leave all
these boxes unchecked

02:00:53.912 --> 02:00:55.870 align:middle line:84%
and you're sitting at
home alone doing nothing,

02:00:55.870 --> 02:00:58.870 align:middle line:90%
and you have gobs of free time.

02:00:58.870 --> 02:01:00.310 align:middle line:84%
And your mind will
naturally work.

02:01:00.310 --> 02:01:05.770 align:middle line:84%
Other board members will be
like, hey, now can we paint?

02:01:05.770 --> 02:01:08.570 align:middle line:90%


02:01:08.570 --> 02:01:14.940 align:middle line:84%
The board is like,
sure, whatever.

02:01:14.940 --> 02:01:15.740 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

02:01:15.740 --> 02:01:18.400 align:middle line:84%
Do we still have those paints
we bought like three years ago?

02:01:18.400 --> 02:01:19.573 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, let's pull them out.

02:01:19.573 --> 02:01:21.240 align:middle line:84%
And before you know
it, you're painting.

02:01:21.240 --> 02:01:24.070 align:middle line:84%
In other words, nature
abhors a vacuum.

02:01:24.070 --> 02:01:28.270 align:middle line:84%
So when fear is
taken off the table,

02:01:28.270 --> 02:01:29.780 align:middle line:84%
the vacuum doesn't
last very long.

02:01:29.780 --> 02:01:30.925 align:middle line:90%
You can hear the hissing.

02:01:30.925 --> 02:01:34.000 align:middle line:84%
And the thing that's coming
in, the only other thing aside

02:01:34.000 --> 02:01:36.100 align:middle line:90%
from fear is love slash desire.

02:01:36.100 --> 02:01:39.910 align:middle line:90%


02:01:39.910 --> 02:01:46.030 align:middle line:84%
And so your radar starts
to lock on things--

02:01:46.030 --> 02:01:50.687 align:middle line:84%
it sounds corny, but you do
out of love, not out of fear.

02:01:50.687 --> 02:01:52.270 align:middle line:84%
And when you do
something out of love,

02:01:52.270 --> 02:01:54.310 align:middle line:84%
you're doing it
for no good reason.

02:01:54.310 --> 02:01:55.810 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't make money.

02:01:55.810 --> 02:01:58.240 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't burnish my baseball
card or my reputation.

02:01:58.240 --> 02:02:01.750 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't look good or not
good on Instagram or whatever.

02:02:01.750 --> 02:02:04.960 align:middle line:84%
I'm just doing it because
I'm just this stupid nerd,

02:02:04.960 --> 02:02:08.900 align:middle line:84%
and I like collecting a
certain kind of stamp.

02:02:08.900 --> 02:02:09.700 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

02:02:09.700 --> 02:02:11.402 align:middle line:90%
I don't know, so sue me.

02:02:11.402 --> 02:02:12.610 align:middle line:90%
I don't know why I like this.

02:02:12.610 --> 02:02:14.410 align:middle line:90%
I just like it.

02:02:14.410 --> 02:02:16.750 align:middle line:84%
And you start doing
things for that reason.

02:02:16.750 --> 02:02:19.360 align:middle line:84%
And then those things
then, when you take them

02:02:19.360 --> 02:02:21.970 align:middle line:84%
through the bliss
process of, so these

02:02:21.970 --> 02:02:23.140 align:middle line:90%
are all the things you like.

02:02:23.140 --> 02:02:26.820 align:middle line:90%
Which happen to create value?

02:02:26.820 --> 02:02:31.360 align:middle line:84%
And then of those people
it creates value to,

02:02:31.360 --> 02:02:35.350 align:middle line:84%
who are the ones who feel the
most intrinsic empathy toward?

02:02:35.350 --> 02:02:38.640 align:middle line:90%


02:02:38.640 --> 02:02:40.370 align:middle line:84%
Then, if you wish--
you don't have to.

02:02:40.370 --> 02:02:41.170 align:middle line:90%
There is no should.

02:02:41.170 --> 02:02:42.253 align:middle line:90%
There's no finger-wagging.

02:02:42.253 --> 02:02:44.020 align:middle line:84%
If you wish, you can
start to craft that

02:02:44.020 --> 02:02:45.760 align:middle line:84%
into actually your
livelihood from there

02:02:45.760 --> 02:02:48.422 align:middle line:90%
forward, if you want.

02:02:48.422 --> 02:02:50.380 align:middle line:84%
Some people, they've
lived in fear for so long,

02:02:50.380 --> 02:02:52.630 align:middle line:84%
they've got a huge bank
account from all the companies

02:02:52.630 --> 02:02:54.280 align:middle line:84%
they've started and
sold or whatever,

02:02:54.280 --> 02:02:56.050 align:middle line:90%
and it doesn't matter as much.

02:02:56.050 --> 02:02:59.230 align:middle line:84%
But you still do it not
because you need the money,

02:02:59.230 --> 02:03:02.410 align:middle line:84%
but because money is
also a board member.

02:03:02.410 --> 02:03:03.617 align:middle line:90%
It's a valid life force.

02:03:03.617 --> 02:03:05.200 align:middle line:84%
Everything around
us-- the microphone,

02:03:05.200 --> 02:03:06.690 align:middle line:84%
the camera, you
guys flying here,

02:03:06.690 --> 02:03:08.590 align:middle line:84%
me being here-- it's
all enabled by money.

02:03:08.590 --> 02:03:11.500 align:middle line:90%


02:03:11.500 --> 02:03:13.960 align:middle line:84%
And if you see it only
as a necessary evil,

02:03:13.960 --> 02:03:15.730 align:middle line:84%
you're exiling
that board member.

02:03:15.730 --> 02:03:17.948 align:middle line:90%


02:03:17.948 --> 02:03:19.990 align:middle line:84%
We're not saying go in
the other direction, where

02:03:19.990 --> 02:03:22.930 align:middle line:84%
it is the dictator
running the whole show.

02:03:22.930 --> 02:03:25.600 align:middle line:90%
That's out of fear too.

02:03:25.600 --> 02:03:28.610 align:middle line:84%
But there is a balanced, healthy
place for money on the board.

02:03:28.610 --> 02:03:31.987 align:middle line:84%
And so you'll often end
up doing your bliss,

02:03:31.987 --> 02:03:33.820 align:middle line:84%
and there will be money
involved, because it

02:03:33.820 --> 02:03:36.370 align:middle line:90%
does create value for people.

02:03:36.370 --> 02:03:41.110 align:middle line:90%
And that's OK.

02:03:41.110 --> 02:03:46.820 align:middle line:84%
So the move from
fear to love feels

02:03:46.820 --> 02:03:48.800 align:middle line:84%
like that, where
you do great things

02:03:48.800 --> 02:03:51.290 align:middle line:90%
and you don't get more love.

02:03:51.290 --> 02:03:54.860 align:middle line:84%
So you don't do anything out
of fear anymore, to get love,

02:03:54.860 --> 02:03:55.990 align:middle line:90%
or to avoid losing love.

02:03:55.990 --> 02:03:58.710 align:middle line:84%
The love is just
maxed all the time.

02:03:58.710 --> 02:04:01.430 align:middle line:84%
And then from that, the
love which is maxed--

02:04:01.430 --> 02:04:04.385 align:middle line:84%
which you're actually
acknowledging exists now--

02:04:04.385 --> 02:04:06.010 align:middle line:84%
it starts to have
its own opinion over,

02:04:06.010 --> 02:04:07.710 align:middle line:90%
like, well, let's go do that.

02:04:07.710 --> 02:04:09.668 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, well, that
won't make any money.

02:04:09.668 --> 02:04:11.308 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, but that's OK.

02:04:11.308 --> 02:04:13.100 align:middle line:84%
If we don't make money,
we won't lose love.

02:04:13.100 --> 02:04:14.000 align:middle line:90%
Oh yeah, never mind.

02:04:14.000 --> 02:04:16.380 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to go
back to my cupcake.

02:04:16.380 --> 02:04:18.080 align:middle line:90%
Oh yeah, so let's go paint.

02:04:18.080 --> 02:04:19.290 align:middle line:90%
Let's go paint.

02:04:19.290 --> 02:04:21.538 align:middle line:84%
And you paint, and you do
all the stuff mindlessly.

02:04:21.538 --> 02:04:22.580 align:middle line:90%
You don't think about it.

02:04:22.580 --> 02:04:24.550 align:middle line:90%
It just kind of happens.

02:04:24.550 --> 02:04:25.490 align:middle line:90%
You talk about flow.

02:04:25.490 --> 02:04:26.750 align:middle line:90%
Things just flow out of you.

02:04:26.750 --> 02:04:29.540 align:middle line:84%
It was like someone was
doing it through my hands.

02:04:29.540 --> 02:04:35.150 align:middle line:84%
That's love, surrender, and
all of those related things.

02:04:35.150 --> 02:04:36.200 align:middle line:90%
>> That's beautiful.

02:04:36.200 --> 02:04:37.640 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

02:04:37.640 --> 02:04:39.680 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

02:04:39.680 --> 02:04:40.550 align:middle line:90%
>> I get it.

02:04:40.550 --> 02:04:41.570 align:middle line:90%
I totally get it.

02:04:41.570 --> 02:04:42.980 align:middle line:90%
Switch off the switch.

02:04:42.980 --> 02:04:45.290 align:middle line:90%
And meditation, can that help?

02:04:45.290 --> 02:04:48.890 align:middle line:90%
>> Meditation can help.

02:04:48.890 --> 02:04:52.580 align:middle line:84%
So what I do is, I'm a nerd
of trying to sort of figure

02:04:52.580 --> 02:04:55.040 align:middle line:84%
out, in this global chess
game, how to get in there

02:04:55.040 --> 02:04:56.355 align:middle line:90%
and switch off the switch.

02:04:56.355 --> 02:04:58.730 align:middle line:84%
That's why when I told you I
don't really do interviews--

02:04:58.730 --> 02:05:00.605 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to do an
interview where they're

02:05:00.605 --> 02:05:03.680 align:middle line:84%
going to use what I'm saying to
wag a finger at the audience,

02:05:03.680 --> 02:05:06.500 align:middle line:84%
saying now you need to do
this, because Artie said this.

02:05:06.500 --> 02:05:10.100 align:middle line:84%
I just can't be a part of
that, because my whole point is

02:05:10.100 --> 02:05:13.880 align:middle line:84%
to flip the switch, where
it's like basically--

02:05:13.880 --> 02:05:16.760 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it sounds
weird to say this.

02:05:16.760 --> 02:05:21.290 align:middle line:84%
My teaching philosophy is you
don't need to do anything.

02:05:21.290 --> 02:05:25.940 align:middle line:84%
You don't owe anybody
a goddamn thing.

02:05:25.940 --> 02:05:28.318 align:middle line:84%
And you're loved
without condition.

02:05:28.318 --> 02:05:31.360 align:middle line:90%


02:05:31.360 --> 02:05:33.070 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I tell my kids--

02:05:33.070 --> 02:05:35.360 align:middle line:90%
I hesitate saying this.

02:05:35.360 --> 02:05:36.160 align:middle line:90%
I'll soften it.

02:05:36.160 --> 02:05:39.430 align:middle line:84%
So what I'd tell my kids
when they were younger was,

02:05:39.430 --> 02:05:44.920 align:middle line:84%
you can go out and commit
crimes all day long--

02:05:44.920 --> 02:05:47.620 align:middle line:84%
horrendous, monstrous
crimes-- and you

02:05:47.620 --> 02:05:53.300 align:middle line:84%
will not lose one
iota of love from me.

02:05:53.300 --> 02:05:56.520 align:middle line:84%
Now, that having been
said, please don't do that.

02:05:56.520 --> 02:05:58.220 align:middle line:90%
Please don't do that.

02:05:58.220 --> 02:06:01.280 align:middle line:84%
But for all these other reasons,
you'll have a crappy life.

02:06:01.280 --> 02:06:02.190 align:middle line:90%
You'll go to jail.

02:06:02.190 --> 02:06:03.360 align:middle line:90%
You'll break my heart.

02:06:03.360 --> 02:06:04.250 align:middle line:90%
You'll be unhappy.

02:06:04.250 --> 02:06:05.292 align:middle line:90%
You'll hurt other people.

02:06:05.292 --> 02:06:07.190 align:middle line:90%
Why would you want to do that?

02:06:07.190 --> 02:06:09.590 align:middle line:84%
So there are a bazillion
reasons why you wouldn't

02:06:09.590 --> 02:06:13.370 align:middle line:90%
do those bad, harmful things.

02:06:13.370 --> 02:06:17.660 align:middle line:84%
But please don't let
one of those reasons

02:06:17.660 --> 02:06:19.720 align:middle line:84%
be that you fear
losing love for me,

02:06:19.720 --> 02:06:21.290 align:middle line:90%
because that's not on the table.

02:06:21.290 --> 02:06:23.760 align:middle line:90%


02:06:23.760 --> 02:06:24.560 align:middle line:90%
It's not.

02:06:24.560 --> 02:06:27.023 align:middle line:90%


02:06:27.023 --> 02:06:28.940 align:middle line:84%
That's why I like the
monstrous serial killer.

02:06:28.940 --> 02:06:31.160 align:middle line:84%
The mother is still like,
please, take me instead.

02:06:31.160 --> 02:06:31.960 align:middle line:90%
He's a good boy.

02:06:31.960 --> 02:06:33.970 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, well,
that's unconditional love.

02:06:33.970 --> 02:06:36.160 align:middle line:90%


02:06:36.160 --> 02:06:36.960 align:middle line:90%
You know?

02:06:36.960 --> 02:06:39.710 align:middle line:90%


02:06:39.710 --> 02:06:46.220 align:middle line:90%
And so my way of looking at it--

02:06:46.220 --> 02:06:47.990 align:middle line:84%
and this is
horrifying for people

02:06:47.990 --> 02:06:49.910 align:middle line:84%
who are all about law
and order, because it's

02:06:49.910 --> 02:06:51.170 align:middle line:90%
suppression and control.

02:06:51.170 --> 02:06:52.490 align:middle line:90%
And I get that.

02:06:52.490 --> 02:06:54.680 align:middle line:90%
I'm a fan of law and order.

02:06:54.680 --> 02:07:02.930 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is, if you
really flip that switch

02:07:02.930 --> 02:07:06.128 align:middle line:84%
and you know you're
loved without condition,

02:07:06.128 --> 02:07:07.670 align:middle line:84%
then everything else
flows from that.

02:07:07.670 --> 02:07:11.810 align:middle line:90%


02:07:11.810 --> 02:07:15.440 align:middle line:84%
If there is a young
man who feels,

02:07:15.440 --> 02:07:18.830 align:middle line:84%
no matter how weird he
is, no matter what kind

02:07:18.830 --> 02:07:21.230 align:middle line:84%
of weird comics he likes
to read or weird music he

02:07:21.230 --> 02:07:26.270 align:middle line:84%
likes to listen to, that he
is loved without condition--

02:07:26.270 --> 02:07:30.170 align:middle line:84%
without condition, nothing
he does makes him lose love--

02:07:30.170 --> 02:07:36.020 align:middle line:84%
that's a man, I would wager,
who would never pick up a gun,

02:07:36.020 --> 02:07:40.543 align:middle line:84%
unless perhaps it is
to defend the homeland.

02:07:40.543 --> 02:07:41.960 align:middle line:84%
So guns are not
intrinsically bad.

02:07:41.960 --> 02:07:44.780 align:middle line:84%
The military is a sacred
function of society.

02:07:44.780 --> 02:07:47.068 align:middle line:90%


02:07:47.068 --> 02:07:49.610 align:middle line:84%
But when you pick up a gun in
defense of the people you love,

02:07:49.610 --> 02:07:55.730 align:middle line:84%
you're picking up a gun out
of love, not out of fear.

02:07:55.730 --> 02:07:57.950 align:middle line:84%
And so for me, I'm just
like, if I can just

02:07:57.950 --> 02:08:02.810 align:middle line:84%
get in and flip that switch
for as many people as possible,

02:08:02.810 --> 02:08:04.460 align:middle line:90%
then--

02:08:04.460 --> 02:08:06.840 align:middle line:84%
first of all, I don't
think I'm doing any harm.

02:08:06.840 --> 02:08:08.750 align:middle line:84%
And I'm just this
nerdy, like, let's

02:08:08.750 --> 02:08:12.020 align:middle line:84%
just flip as many switches as
we can and see what happens.

02:08:12.020 --> 02:08:14.270 align:middle line:90%
That's my excitement.

02:08:14.270 --> 02:08:19.280 align:middle line:84%
And so for me, what
I teach is the lore

02:08:19.280 --> 02:08:21.270 align:middle line:84%
to get you to start to
think about flipping

02:08:21.270 --> 02:08:23.270 align:middle line:84%
that switch is your meaning
and purpose in life.

02:08:23.270 --> 02:08:25.490 align:middle line:84%
You can't fulfill your
meaning and purpose

02:08:25.490 --> 02:08:27.183 align:middle line:90%
in life out of abject fear.

02:08:27.183 --> 02:08:28.100 align:middle line:90%
You're just too small.

02:08:28.100 --> 02:08:28.970 align:middle line:90%
You're constricted.

02:08:28.970 --> 02:08:31.610 align:middle line:84%
You never opened your
clenched fist of fear,

02:08:31.610 --> 02:08:32.970 align:middle line:90%
so you can never play the piano.

02:08:32.970 --> 02:08:36.890 align:middle line:90%


02:08:36.890 --> 02:08:41.240 align:middle line:84%
With bliss, I get pulled
backwards kicking and screaming

02:08:41.240 --> 02:08:44.510 align:middle line:90%
into healing-related stuff.

02:08:44.510 --> 02:08:47.630 align:middle line:84%
So at an advisory
level, I'm happy to talk

02:08:47.630 --> 02:08:49.910 align:middle line:84%
with people about healing
and help them through that.

02:08:49.910 --> 02:08:51.230 align:middle line:84%
But the minute they're
like, actually,

02:08:51.230 --> 02:08:53.313 align:middle line:84%
I think I'm ready for
therapy, I'm like, right on.

02:08:53.313 --> 02:08:54.120 align:middle line:90%
Do it.

02:08:54.120 --> 02:08:54.920 align:middle line:90%
Do it.

02:08:54.920 --> 02:08:56.120 align:middle line:90%
I'm the air traffic controller.

02:08:56.120 --> 02:08:57.453 align:middle line:90%
Come back whenever you're ready.

02:08:57.453 --> 02:08:59.870 align:middle line:90%
We're not going anywhere.

02:08:59.870 --> 02:09:03.020 align:middle line:84%
For me, I'm working on
getting all my stuff recorded

02:09:03.020 --> 02:09:05.180 align:middle line:84%
so that like the virtual
AR already will still

02:09:05.180 --> 02:09:06.530 align:middle line:90%
be here when I'm dead.

02:09:06.530 --> 02:09:08.480 align:middle line:84%
So if I get hit by a
bus, it's still here.

02:09:08.480 --> 02:09:09.770 align:middle line:90%
Take your time.

02:09:09.770 --> 02:09:10.880 align:middle line:90%
There's no pressure.

02:09:10.880 --> 02:09:12.273 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going anywhere.

02:09:12.273 --> 02:09:15.980 align:middle line:90%


02:09:15.980 --> 02:09:22.610 align:middle line:84%
And then, so all the related
healing stuff, and then

02:09:22.610 --> 02:09:26.480 align:middle line:84%
things like meditation, and
then even helping people

02:09:26.480 --> 02:09:30.500 align:middle line:84%
do things like read their dreams
or recover their lost board

02:09:30.500 --> 02:09:33.140 align:middle line:90%
numbers.

02:09:33.140 --> 02:09:37.130 align:middle line:84%
The key to this healing, for
me, is finding your lost board

02:09:37.130 --> 02:09:38.660 align:middle line:90%
member and recovering it.

02:09:38.660 --> 02:09:41.780 align:middle line:84%
Because the
quintessence within you

02:09:41.780 --> 02:09:48.620 align:middle line:84%
of feeling like a part
of you is not worthy--

02:09:48.620 --> 02:09:51.140 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's probably
deeper, but let's just

02:09:51.140 --> 02:09:54.710 align:middle line:84%
say the musician in you
who was stuffed down.

02:09:54.710 --> 02:09:56.570 align:middle line:90%
When you finally recover him--

02:09:56.570 --> 02:09:59.780 align:middle line:84%
look, we're not going
to quit our lives

02:09:59.780 --> 02:10:02.360 align:middle line:84%
and go join the circus,
because we're not

02:10:02.360 --> 02:10:04.910 align:middle line:90%
going 100% in your direction.

02:10:04.910 --> 02:10:07.432 align:middle line:84%
But also, we're not going
to go in 100% of the bully's

02:10:07.432 --> 02:10:08.890 align:middle line:84%
direction and just
be an accountant

02:10:08.890 --> 02:10:10.132 align:middle line:90%
for the rest of our lives.

02:10:10.132 --> 02:10:12.590 align:middle line:84%
We're going to have to come up
with some kind of compromise

02:10:12.590 --> 02:10:15.200 align:middle line:90%
plan.

02:10:15.200 --> 02:10:18.800 align:middle line:90%
That is stepping away from fear.

02:10:18.800 --> 02:10:22.580 align:middle line:84%
Because if I add a little mix,
maybe increasing over time,

02:10:22.580 --> 02:10:24.910 align:middle line:84%
of musician, I
will not lose love.

02:10:24.910 --> 02:10:26.570 align:middle line:84%
And I slowly get
acclimated to that.

02:10:26.570 --> 02:10:30.808 align:middle line:90%


02:10:30.808 --> 02:10:32.225 align:middle line:84%
For most people,
that board member

02:10:32.225 --> 02:10:35.820 align:middle line:84%
is stuffed down
very, very deeply.

02:10:35.820 --> 02:10:38.150 align:middle line:84%
And it will come up
with all kinds of ways

02:10:38.150 --> 02:10:41.090 align:middle line:90%
to get its message to you--

02:10:41.090 --> 02:10:42.980 align:middle line:84%
pulling the emergency
brake, having

02:10:42.980 --> 02:10:44.870 align:middle line:84%
a big crisis in your
life, getting laid off,

02:10:44.870 --> 02:10:45.828 align:middle line:90%
throwing out your back.

02:10:45.828 --> 02:10:47.990 align:middle line:84%
All these things are
ways of doing it.

02:10:47.990 --> 02:10:51.320 align:middle line:84%
And what I specialize
in as a part

02:10:51.320 --> 02:10:56.030 align:middle line:84%
of helping to flip
the switch is to try

02:10:56.030 --> 02:11:01.340 align:middle line:84%
to give that board member ways
of reaching you without having

02:11:01.340 --> 02:11:03.720 align:middle line:90%
to go to that extreme.

02:11:03.720 --> 02:11:05.690 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm like,
oh, if you just

02:11:05.690 --> 02:11:09.680 align:middle line:84%
wanted me to read the email
that I had marked as spam

02:11:09.680 --> 02:11:12.680 align:middle line:84%
and blocked you and
unfriended you on Facebook,

02:11:12.680 --> 02:11:16.760 align:middle line:84%
and now you're like, I'm lying
in a hospital bed stressing

02:11:16.760 --> 02:11:18.620 align:middle line:84%
about something scary
they saw on an MRI,

02:11:18.620 --> 02:11:21.210 align:middle line:84%
because you're rattling my
cage to get my attention--

02:11:21.210 --> 02:11:22.010 align:middle line:90%
OK, OK.

02:11:22.010 --> 02:11:26.330 align:middle line:84%
So now I acknowledge
you're powerful.

02:11:26.330 --> 02:11:33.300 align:middle line:84%
Can we just take a
moment, and can you just--

02:11:33.300 --> 02:11:34.100 align:middle line:90%
I'm here now.

02:11:34.100 --> 02:11:36.870 align:middle line:84%
Can you just tell me
what you want to tell me?

02:11:36.870 --> 02:11:37.670 align:middle line:90%
And I will sit.

02:11:37.670 --> 02:11:41.570 align:middle line:84%
I will tie myself to
the chair and listen,

02:11:41.570 --> 02:11:44.060 align:middle line:84%
because now I realize,
just hearing it from you

02:11:44.060 --> 02:11:48.000 align:middle line:84%
directly is better than
what happened last month.

02:11:48.000 --> 02:11:48.800 align:middle line:90%
And I get it now.

02:11:48.800 --> 02:11:50.240 align:middle line:90%
I'm here.

02:11:50.240 --> 02:11:52.020 align:middle line:90%
You have my attention.

02:11:52.020 --> 02:11:55.430 align:middle line:90%
What would you like me to say?

02:11:55.430 --> 02:11:59.240 align:middle line:84%
And there are two
very powerful ways

02:11:59.240 --> 02:12:05.900 align:middle line:84%
that lost board number will come
to you when your guard is down

02:12:05.900 --> 02:12:12.020 align:middle line:84%
and you're more
accidentally receptive.

02:12:12.020 --> 02:12:15.350 align:middle line:84%
And the two are when
you're meditating

02:12:15.350 --> 02:12:17.610 align:middle line:90%
and when you're asleep.

02:12:17.610 --> 02:12:19.100 align:middle line:84%
So meditation,
you'll get visions.

02:12:19.100 --> 02:12:21.665 align:middle line:90%


02:12:21.665 --> 02:12:23.540 align:middle line:84%
That lost board member
will come up and start

02:12:23.540 --> 02:12:26.480 align:middle line:84%
talking at you, a
voice that you usually

02:12:26.480 --> 02:12:28.550 align:middle line:90%
don't allow to yourself.

02:12:28.550 --> 02:12:33.620 align:middle line:84%
When you're in full meditation
and those things within you

02:12:33.620 --> 02:12:37.760 align:middle line:84%
are open, that will be the
moment where the guerrilla

02:12:37.760 --> 02:12:38.870 align:middle line:90%
forces are like, OK, now.

02:12:38.870 --> 02:12:40.360 align:middle line:90%
Go, go, go.

02:12:40.360 --> 02:12:41.160 align:middle line:90%
They run up to you.

02:12:41.160 --> 02:12:42.960 align:middle line:84%
And you're like, you're
going to stab me.

02:12:42.960 --> 02:12:45.920 align:middle line:84%
No, they're handing
you an envelope.

02:12:45.920 --> 02:12:48.380 align:middle line:84%
Please don't burn this one
like you did the last 3,000

02:12:48.380 --> 02:12:49.990 align:middle line:90%
we've been trying to send you.

02:12:49.990 --> 02:12:51.650 align:middle line:84%
And then dreams
are the other one.

02:12:51.650 --> 02:12:54.330 align:middle line:84%
Dreams is a whole other
subset we won't get into.

02:12:54.330 --> 02:12:59.570 align:middle line:84%
But I've found that I've
gotten into helping people

02:12:59.570 --> 02:13:00.950 align:middle line:90%
with dreams--

02:13:00.950 --> 02:13:07.610 align:middle line:84%
again, very haltingly,
very begrudgingly.

02:13:07.610 --> 02:13:11.210 align:middle line:84%
But what I've found is that when
people start a healing cycle,

02:13:11.210 --> 02:13:13.910 align:middle line:84%
their dreams will
invariably fire up.

02:13:13.910 --> 02:13:16.160 align:middle line:84%
And even dreams that have
been recurring for 30 years,

02:13:16.160 --> 02:13:17.480 align:middle line:84%
when you start to
remember, oh yeah,

02:13:17.480 --> 02:13:19.850 align:middle line:84%
there's this dream I've had
for 30 years that's recurring.

02:13:19.850 --> 02:13:21.975 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, OK, you just
spent an hour telling me

02:13:21.975 --> 02:13:23.250 align:middle line:90%
you don't dream.

02:13:23.250 --> 02:13:24.050 align:middle line:90%
Which is fine.

02:13:24.050 --> 02:13:24.850 align:middle line:90%
That happens.

02:13:24.850 --> 02:13:27.740 align:middle line:90%


02:13:27.740 --> 02:13:30.990 align:middle line:84%
The most common dream pattern
is someone chasing you,

02:13:30.990 --> 02:13:32.940 align:middle line:84%
a boogie man chasing
you, invading your home,

02:13:32.940 --> 02:13:35.930 align:middle line:90%
breaking into your home.

02:13:35.930 --> 02:13:39.650 align:middle line:84%
And typically, the
way I read that is

02:13:39.650 --> 02:13:43.880 align:middle line:84%
that that is some form of lost
board member running after you,

02:13:43.880 --> 02:13:46.250 align:middle line:90%
trying to get your message.

02:13:46.250 --> 02:13:48.530 align:middle line:84%
And it's so at the
end of its rope,

02:13:48.530 --> 02:13:50.800 align:middle line:84%
because it's tried
everything else--

02:13:50.800 --> 02:13:53.135 align:middle line:84%
it's tried your girlfriend
breaking up with you.

02:13:53.135 --> 02:13:55.010 align:middle line:84%
It's tried your son
telling you you're a jerk

02:13:55.010 --> 02:13:56.370 align:middle line:90%
and not talking to you.

02:13:56.370 --> 02:13:58.078 align:middle line:84%
Nothing's getting
through, because you're

02:13:58.078 --> 02:14:01.502 align:middle line:84%
like, I have to continue
soothing and shielding.

02:14:01.502 --> 02:14:03.710 align:middle line:84%
Finally, it'll come to you
in this dream where you're

02:14:03.710 --> 02:14:06.110 align:middle line:84%
being chased, because
it has resorted

02:14:06.110 --> 02:14:10.125 align:middle line:84%
to pulling the lever of fear,
because unless you wake up

02:14:10.125 --> 02:14:11.750 align:middle line:84%
at 3:00 in the morning
in a cold sweat,

02:14:11.750 --> 02:14:14.450 align:middle line:90%
you won't remember anything.

02:14:14.450 --> 02:14:16.010 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm going
to do that to you.

02:14:16.010 --> 02:14:19.112 align:middle line:84%
Sorry, but I'm going
to hit the button,

02:14:19.112 --> 02:14:21.320 align:middle line:84%
wake you up at 3:00 in the
morning in the cold sweat.

02:14:21.320 --> 02:14:22.970 align:middle line:90%
You'll have this dream.

02:14:22.970 --> 02:14:25.312 align:middle line:84%
And the problem is, it doesn't
know that we're in 2019

02:14:25.312 --> 02:14:27.770 align:middle line:84%
and Western civiliz-- it doesn't
know you can't go anywhere

02:14:27.770 --> 02:14:29.720 align:middle line:90%
to get the dream read.

02:14:29.720 --> 02:14:31.670 align:middle line:84%
You go on the internet
for dream directory

02:14:31.670 --> 02:14:34.940 align:middle line:84%
and it says, oh, boogeyman
is some lost fear of yours.

02:14:34.940 --> 02:14:36.620 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, what
does even that mean?

02:14:36.620 --> 02:14:39.170 align:middle line:90%


02:14:39.170 --> 02:14:43.590 align:middle line:84%
But it's a very ancient
part of ourselves.

02:14:43.590 --> 02:14:47.527 align:middle line:84%
So when people come to
me, I say, OK, OK, fine.

02:14:47.527 --> 02:14:48.860 align:middle line:90%
Have your dreams been firing up?

02:14:48.860 --> 02:14:50.195 align:middle line:90%
And I know the answer.

02:14:50.195 --> 02:14:55.940 align:middle line:84%
Just give me a few, and I'll
just give you the thumbnail,

02:14:55.940 --> 02:14:59.790 align:middle line:84%
but just enough so that you're
like, OK, this is a real thing.

02:14:59.790 --> 02:15:04.400 align:middle line:84%
I get it, and I'm willing to
go find my lost board member.

02:15:04.400 --> 02:15:07.442 align:middle line:90%
And that typically is enough.

02:15:07.442 --> 02:15:09.650 align:middle line:84%
So it's basically, I'm all
about flipping the switch.

02:15:09.650 --> 02:15:12.900 align:middle line:90%


02:15:12.900 --> 02:15:14.870 align:middle line:84%
The byproduct for
everyone else's benefit

02:15:14.870 --> 02:15:17.960 align:middle line:84%
too is that they end up
on track to their bliss.

02:15:17.960 --> 02:15:21.860 align:middle line:84%
But the whole craft of
getting that switch flipped is

02:15:21.860 --> 02:15:26.120 align:middle line:84%
something that just organically,
these other things have come up

02:15:26.120 --> 02:15:30.110 align:middle line:90%
as the need has arisen.

02:15:30.110 --> 02:15:32.090 align:middle line:90%
So I'm having fun all day long.

02:15:32.090 --> 02:15:38.060 align:middle line:84%
I'm like the guy in
his workshop just

02:15:38.060 --> 02:15:41.270 align:middle line:84%
fussing with all these
different things.

02:15:41.270 --> 02:15:44.000 align:middle line:84%
Thankfully, I have
a lot of people

02:15:44.000 --> 02:15:47.060 align:middle line:84%
who come to me for
this kind of thing,

02:15:47.060 --> 02:15:51.450 align:middle line:84%
so I get to ask them
about their experiences.

02:15:51.450 --> 02:15:53.450 align:middle line:84%
I'm in the kitchen and
I'm like, here, try this.

02:15:53.450 --> 02:15:54.380 align:middle line:90%
Is it too spicy?

02:15:54.380 --> 02:15:56.580 align:middle line:90%
What do you think of it?

02:15:56.580 --> 02:15:59.420 align:middle line:90%
So I'm very much in my bliss.

02:15:59.420 --> 02:16:08.180 align:middle line:84%
I'm just a pig in a cool
pond of mud all day long.

02:16:08.180 --> 02:16:10.140 align:middle line:84%
And I get to have
interviews like this.

02:16:10.140 --> 02:16:10.940 align:middle line:90%
>> So great.

02:16:10.940 --> 02:16:12.320 align:middle line:90%
Appreciative of your time.

02:16:12.320 --> 02:16:16.680 align:middle line:84%
It has me thinking of this
term, amor vincit omnia, which

02:16:16.680 --> 02:16:18.800 align:middle line:84%
Laurentine's
grandmother had engraved

02:16:18.800 --> 02:16:20.480 align:middle line:84%
on the inside of
our wedding rings,

02:16:20.480 --> 02:16:22.600 align:middle line:90%
which is like love conquers all.

02:16:22.600 --> 02:16:23.400 align:middle line:90%
So beautiful.

02:16:23.400 --> 02:16:25.750 align:middle line:90%
So yeah, thank you.

